reviews.author: Jasmine J
reviews.text:
Pac Heights Kidz was our first daycare experience for our daughter, who started when she was about 2.5 years old, and it was wonderful - all of the teachers and staff were so friendly, caring and welcoming, and our daughter always came home happy and excited about her day. They sent lots of updates and pics, as well as a weekly newsletter about what the kids had got up to that week, so I always felt like I knew what was happening.

I also liked how they put on lots of events to help you get to know the teachers and other families, and they put so much effort into helping our daughter (and us!) settle in. It really felt like a little community. We sadly had to leave due to relocating, but otherwise we would have happily kept our daughter here until she went to school - we were very sad to leave! Highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Diana Wang
reviews.text: I've been sending both my kids to RA/RHA since 2018 because Jiali and her team have been so wonderful. This review is specifically for my daughter, who has been attending since 2022. First and foremost, the teachers are so caring and wonderful - my daughter excitedly tells me about her day everyday and she is so happy to go to school. I really appreciate the videos/photos that RA will post so we can get an update on what goes on during school.  They've also been so accommodating with us and my erratic work schedule (sometimes I need to suddenly pick up early or drop off late, etc. they've been nothing but accommodating). I feel like both my kids truly thrived here through the nurture and care given by the teachers. Secondly, there's a wonderful parent community at RA which has engaged in sharing updates, set up playdates, etc. You can tell not only do the teachers/Jiali care about the students but so do the parents who send their kids here. Third, the mandarin teaching has been exceptional. In fact, sometimes they need to tell ME what a Chinese word means because they've learned so much. My daughter will be graduating to K soon and we'll truly be sad to leave this place. Would highly recommend RA 1000x over

reviews.author: Thomas Wu
reviews.text:
Jiali and the teachers at Richmond Academy taught our kids everything from the time they were 1 year old. When we applied for private schools in SF, we got into 5 out of 5 schools we applied to, and I attribute how prepared our kids were for the evaluations due to Richmond Academy. If you want your kids to learn Mandarin, math, manners, and kindness ‚Äî this is the spot.

When we were deciding which kindergarten to attend, we decided not to continue Mandarin immersion because, frankly, our kids would be bored waiting for other kids to catch up.
You won‚Äôt need to keep switching schools each year; Richmond Academy handles all levels, including daycare, TK, and PK. They let us focus on our careers, knowing our kids were taken care of 8-5pm. Even when we got off work earlier, we would leave them with Jiali, knowing they were happy and thriving at school. Lastly, while many places were closed during Covid, they didn‚Äôt let us down and found a way to stay safe and open. We had no learning loss to deal with.

Forever grateful for the time our children spent with Richmond Academy!

reviews.author: Jenny Lee
reviews.text:
From the moment I walked into Richmond Academy two years ago, I knew this preschool was perfect for my then two-year-old. Jiali (owner), Jojo (JiaWen), and all the teachers my little one has had over the years have been wonderful. This preschool had everything I wanted: chinese immersion, large open space, food provided, indoor playground, immaculate bathroom, security and convenient drop off location.

I also appreciated that Richmond Academy focused on teaching older children to help younger children, a practice I hoped my little one would learn given they are an only child. Having this ingrained in my little one at school has helped them play well with others, watch out for smaller kids, and also share their toys! Another milestone was potty training. At the beginning of my child's time at Richmond Academy, I brought diapers. However, about a month or so later, I was informed they no longer needed them. I was baffled but so appreciative that they took care of this for me.

As parents and guardians, it can be hard to choose a preschool. For me, I am grateful I chose Richmond Academy to start off my little one‚Äôs education and development. Jiali, her teachers, and staff are very passionate about what they do and I can see they love working with children.

reviews.author: Valerie Lam
reviews.text: I've had 3 kids attend Richmond Academy and can whole heartily¬†attest to the wonderful program and people here. Jiali (the founder), Jiawan and all teachers are very nurturing and have amazing teaching skills. My kids were constantly singing mandarin songs and reciting poetry at home. I couldn't even get them to recite some of the easiest things¬†I was teaching them in english¬†at home yet they were reading mandarin¬†so confidently. I was so shocked I tested them to make sure it wasn't all memorization. They could really recognize the characters. WOW Parents, they potty train! Need I say more?  They do a super job in this area and the new facility has the best kid's¬†restroom space I've ever seen. A few weeks of potty training was all it took them and I was elated the day they returned my diapers. LOL I must also mention they provide lunch and snacks for the kids. The lunch is nutritious and homemade in house. My kids always spoke positively about the lunch and I very often hear soups and veggies included which made this mama very happy.  I can't express enough how nurturing the teachers are and the safe¬†environment they provide.¬† All are so warm and lovely that the kids feel secure¬†and excited to go to school.¬† Hours are very flex, esp for working folks considering they open early and close late. During vacation breaks, the school helps out parents to provide optional school days for an additional fee. This was very convenient vs finding separate care. The first time I toured RA and met Jiali, I knew in my heart of hearts this is where the kids need to go to school. Truth is I forfeited my deposit I placed elsewhere and secured my twins' spot at RA right away. Best decision I made for them. Even if you are touring around, just give RA a chance and I'm confident you'll love the space and school as much as we have. FYI I'm so envious of the play structure Randy, the handy husband built. You'll see all all the dedication and heart they put in the school and kids. RA is a gem and I'm grateful I found this school for my children.

We love the Mandarin immersion aspect, and our son is fully bilingual thanks to the teachers' efforts.

The involved PTA organizes many community events, such as monthly playdates, Easter Egg Hunts, an annual Camp Out, Pumpkin Picking, Santa's Brunch, parents' nights out and more across the Funston and Lombard locations. reviews.text: Could not be happier to have my son at Kids Kingdom! Rosie and the teachers at Kids Kingdom care for my son and the other littles with so much love. reviews.author: Alexa Fibich
reviews.text:
Our 6 month old has been in Rosie and team's care for the last month and as first time parents navigating child care, we could not be happier! It's been incredible to witness how quickly our son has developed in a matter of weeks working with Rosie -- he is starting to really open up with the other babies/toddlers there, he now likes to feed himself his own bottle (incredible!), he is learning how to eat solids (and use spoons), he is extremely social to new people, and he is more mobile and chatty. He's become an all around more independent, social and fun loving baby under her care.

As hard as it is to drop my son off, I know he is in the best hands with her and her team, that he is safe and loved up. We love that we receive consistent updates throughout the day (via the Brigthwheel app they use) on his eating, naps, diaper changes, as well as the daily pictures and videos of him having fun. Rosie also always spends time at pickup or drop off if needed to answer questions, or provide guidance. What also stands out is how well behaved the toddlers are. They are so polite, always eating their snacks together at the table and when I ask how their day is, they are always smiling saying how much fun they are having. It's apparent why so many families that started their babies in Rosie's care continue to work with her for years. If you are looking for a day care for your child in the marina/cow hollow area, Kids Kingdom is a must!

reviews.author: Michelle Toy
reviews.text:
We are SO happy to have found Kid's Kingdom!! Our son has been in Rosie's daycare for 5 months (started at 12 months) and we feel so lucky to have him in her team's care

Like probably many parents, we were nervous about starting daycare for our first child (and in a pandemic!), but working and having childcare at home was not ideal. A weight was completely lifted once we started at Kid's Kingdom. Rosie is really thoughtful about how she runs her daycare and who she hires as her teachers and caretakers. We know our child is safe and so cared for (and extra peace of mind that you can check on your child through the Nest cameras!).

We have seen our son mature so much, he has been more independent, eating better (Rosie rotates the menu of home cooked fresh meals and shares every month!), sleeping so well, and playing well with others. She goes the extra step to think about our child's development and how to encourage his independence and growth - eg has prepared us to move into new stages like 2 to 1 nap and preparing him for the older / toddler room, starting to stage a transition vs moving him all at once. He is happy at drop off and pick-up - waving and giving high fives to Rosie and team before we head home. We really appreciate the daily updates on his meals, sleep schedules, dirty diapers, and pictures from their app! Rosie is also full of great advice and has given us tips at home to help make him more independent and sociable! She is also extremely responsive and it is so easy to get a hold of her via text / app / or call!!

Highly recommend Kids Kingdom if you can get a spot! We thought we might eventually move closer to family but now we are not in a rush since we have wonderful childcare!!

reviews.text: My son had a wonderful first year of preschool at Blueside. The small class size (6 children max) was perfect for attentive care and for forming his first friendships. They spend a lot of time outdoors at the wonderful local playgrounds and museums. Rosa is a very kind caregiver, and I've seen how much independence he's gained over the course of the school year. He now comprehends and speaks Spanish, due to her bilingual program. It's a safe and loving environment for toddlers ~2-4 yrs old. We planned to keep him enrolled, though ended up moving. We'll miss Blueside and Rosa!

reviews.author: Greg Goldblatt
reviews.text:
Just wanted to add my review for Kindercare here as I think it's long overdue. This daycare center has been here in the same location since, I believe, 1959 when current director Mrs. Emily's grandparents opened it as Mother Goose. She still runs it day to day. It was bought by a statewide chain, Kindercare, just 2-3 years ago.

My wife, child and I were living out of state, but in 2021 were moving back to the Richmond District where I grew up. Searching for a Preschool for my kid online was a bit stressful, but we came across Mother Goose/Kindercare and did a Zoom interview. We did luckily get a spot and have been here ever since. Our child is set to graduate to public school Kindergarten in a few months so it is with some sadness that we will be leaving and our kid will be saying goodbye to many of his little buddies soon...

We have been very happy with our experience here, the teachers have been great. Loving, kind, but firm with the kids. There's two big play structures out back and there's always weekly activities going on like mini-train rides and holiday festivals. There's also optional programs like music and soccer. They also serve food & snacks that for some reason my kid actually eats(!) We always felt like our child was safe and secure here and provided with a caring teaching environment. An online app provides daily reports and photos so you can check in on how they're doing.

The best part is the continuity with the older staff, some of whom have been teaching there for decades. My kid literally has a friend in his PreK class who's mom went to Mothergoose as a kid here back in the 1980's. The same teacher who taught her, is now her 5-year old's teacher!

My only complaint is that some of the younger, newer teachers have seen some high turnover. This may not have anything to do with the school and more to do with the cost of living in San Francisco, but many of my kid's younger teachers (some of whom he really adored) moved on after 6 months to a year. But again, not something that is necessarily within the school's control, and maybe this is endemic to all schools across the city right now. Just my two cents.

reviews.author: Al Sargent
reviews.text: Great preschool. Our kids both have gone here, from A level through E level, and have worked with most of the teachers. We are very happy with the school. They find a happy medium between fostering creativity and (later in the program) developing academic skills in preparation for kindergarten. The school is good at retaining teachers that are effective, while cutting loose the few that aren't. Highly recommended.

My son is always excited to go to school in the mornings. He loves his friends and engages with them in plays, crafts, outdoors, circle times, science experiments and many more different activities. I am impressed with the creative environment and curriculum they provide to teach kids in a fun way. I learn a lot as a parent, too :)

Little LYNC has been an inclusive and diverse community for us and getting to know the other parents in occasional events has also been a great experience.

My son is very happy there. So we are. I highly recommend Little LYNC who is looking for a smaller scale, nurturing and play-based education.

reviews.author: Elizabeth Durham
reviews.text: The teachers at Little Lync made school the most positive experience for our son and our family. This was his first experience with school and they were welcoming, warm, caring and have really helped our son grow. He is excited about going and we can see he is learning new things, both educational, and personal with his peers. The smaller atmosphere Little Lync can offer has been a great fit for us. We are very happy with our choice!

reviews.author: EJ Amanda Diamante
reviews.text: We have been a part of the Little Lync family since my son was 2 years old. From the beginning, the teachers were so understanding, caring and helped him transition into daycare. It's a lovely community and my son has met great friends. Overall we have had a great experience and would recommend Little Lync for anyone looking for a caring and nurturing environment.

reviews.author: Khristine Atienza Walker
reviews.text:
We absolutely love Little LYNC!  My daughter has been attending this school since August 2020. She loves her teachers and her friends, and she seriously comes home happy (and full of stories) everyday!

I was really nervous to put my daughter back in school at a time when Covid was raging.  The teachers really put me at ease when I toured the school, and the owner (Timberly) was so gracious in allowing me to decide when to put her in. She wanted to make sure I was comfortable, and I really appreciated that.

One of the great things about this school is the community of parents who band together to help teachers when they need it. For example, during the big fires of 2020 (when the skies turned orange), the parents pitched in to buy the school a bigger air filter.

By far, the very best thing about Little LYNC is the teachers. They are all AMAZING! I am so grateful for them for teaching our kids, keeping them safe, and loving them like they‚Äôre own.

To Amy, Melody, Carina, Marlene, and Rose ‚Äî Thank you for everything you all do!

We‚Äôve been very happy here and would highly recommend it!

reviews.author: Matt & Anne
reviews.text: We have been really happy with our experience at Little LYNC over the last year. The kids are always happy and excited at pick up time and in the photos that get posted to the daily class dojo website. They do lots of fun arts and crafts and activities - the teachers are so creative including making a ballot box to understand voting, and the school celebrated Lunar New Year and St Patrick‚Äôs Day in addition to the usual Halloween, Thanksgiving, and Christmas events. More importantly, the teachers are wonderful and learned how to care for our child with insulin pump dependent diabetes so well that we trust them completely. Thank you Miss Amy, Melody, Carina, Marlene and Rose!

reviews.author: brittney
reviews.text: Incredibly happy to have found this school for our daughter. Every teacher and caregiver is attentive and patient. The play based model allows for kids to learn how to regulate their emotions through free play and imaginative child-led games. Our daughter is confident, kind and prepared for kindergarten next year.

reviews.author: Julie Collins
reviews.text:
I highly recommend Laurel Hill Nursery School! My child attended Laurel Hill for two years, and we have had a wonderful experience.

The teachers at Laurel Hill are truly exceptional. They are caring, knowledgeable, and passionate about early childhood education. They created a warm and supportive environment where my child thrived.

Laurel Hill's play-based curriculum is perfect for young learners. My child loves spending thier days exploring, creating, and learning through play. They developed their social, emotional, and academic skills in a fun and engaging way.

I was also impressed with Laurel Hill's parent community. Everyone was welcoming and supportive, and I quickly made friends with other parents. I also appreciated the opportunity to participate in the school's cooperative program. It been a great way to get involved in my child's education and meet other families.

reviews.author: Natalie Savicke
reviews.text:
Enrolling my son at Laurel Hill has been an incredible decision for our family. From the moment we stepped through the doors, we were warmly welcomed into a nurturing and inclusive community that has truly started to become an extension of our family.

The teachers and volunteers are absolutely incredible. Their genuine care for each child's development and well-being is evident in every interaction. My son, who is naturally reserved and hesitant in new environments, formed a special bond with a few of the teachers within just a few weeks. They have a unique talent for understanding his needs and encouraging his participation in activities at his own pace.

I wholeheartedly recommend Laurel Hill to any parent seeking out a play based preschool. It's been a transformative experience for my son and our entire family.

reviews.author: Micaela Davis
reviews.text: I cannot recommend Laurel Hill enough for families with young children. It is truly a special place and we have had an incredible time here with our kids. The teachers and staff are loving, experienced and professional. The outdoor space at the school is unmatched in the city with multiple levels of decks, sandpits and play areas, climbing structures, a 'cafe' area for cooking sand stew, slides, a biking zone, redwood trees and plenty of water play, digging, art, swinging, imaginary play and any other activities the kids dream up in their self-directed day. And working alongside the teachers and other parents at the school is truly an invaluable learning and community-building experience!

reviews.author: Christine Cantwell
reviews.text: Our family has been a part of Laurel hill in both the afternoon program and the preK and it is a wonderful and home-ly place. Meaning it feels like a home and a place kids can experience wonder and excitement and enthusiasm for their discoveries and I think it is very beneficial to all the family members to experience the co-op nursery school thing if it can work logistically for you. (You have to work one 3 hour shift a week and do other volunteer hours throughout the year). The staff is all caring and thoughtful and I see how the kids just grow more and more into themselves and shine with the Love that everyone (Meaning the other parents workers too) gives to the program because they really care and want the best for all the children.

reviews.author: Amber Eggers
reviews.text:
We love Building Kidz and couldn‚Äôt be happier with our decision to send our son here. From day one, the warmth and dedication of the teachers and staff have made this place feel like a second home. Our son literally runs into school every morning with a huge smile and a wave goodbye‚Äîhe genuinely loves being there, which says everything.

What makes Building Kidz truly special is the way the teachers encourage each child to be their best, all while making learning fun and play-centered. The environment is nurturing, joyful, and filled with positive energy.

We‚Äôve had the pleasure of being in two wonderful classrooms with Ms. Maddie and Ms. Janet, and we absolutely adore them. They bring so much heart, creativity, and care into their teaching.

It‚Äôs a fantastic school, and we can‚Äôt recommend it enough to any family looking for a place where their child will thrive.

reviews.author: Kate Medina
reviews.text:
Building Kidz Clement has been an incredible experience for my daughter and our family. The preschool provides an excellent blend of education and performing arts, fostering both academic and creative growth. The teachers are passionate, caring, and truly dedicated to the children's development.

We feel so fortunate to be part of the Building Kidz Clement community, which feels like a warm and supportive family. Watching my daughter thrive in such a nurturing environment has been a joy. I highly recommend Building Kidz Clement to any parent looking for a place where their child can learn, grow, and flourish!

reviews.author: Megan Dunn Caruthers
reviews.text: Our son has been going to BuildingKidz Clement since he was 2 years old. We feel soooooo lucky to have found such a wonderful, caring school for him. I cannot sing BK‚Äôs praises enough! The teachers are all so, so loving, and the Director is an amazing person. The kiddos do performing arts (and do 2 shows per year for parents!), do tons of arts and crafts, have structured learning time, and also get to play outside. They even do field trips (pumpkin patch, academy of sciences, Salesforce park etc). Our son comes home everyday talking about his friends, his teachers & singing cute little songs that they sing at school. They even helped potty train!!! We love BK so much!!!! Highly recommend ü§ç

reviews.author: Tayler Gaffney
reviews.text: Building Kidz has been such an amazing school for my daughter. The owner, director, and teachers are all so kind, welcoming, and loving towards the children. I get daily photos and updates via the Building Kidz app and it‚Äôs so fun to see what they‚Äôre up to throughout the day. They consistently have performing arts classes that have taught my daughter so much. We could not have asked for a better preschool experience!

reviews.author: Meg
reviews.text: Our child has been attending Buildingkidz since he was almost 3. He will be graduating at the end of July! We have been thrilled be the care he has received and watching him grow into himself. He loves all of time for playing and doing art as well as the theater, music and dance classes. We love seeing what he‚Äôs learning at home. Thank you to all the teachers who make him feel so loved and have supported his growth!!

reviews.author: Esther Oh
reviews.text: Our experience at SOMACC is a bit more personal. About a year ago, my husband and I noticed that our son (now in the toddler class) was not meeting his communication milestones. A professional evaluation led to a diagnosis of Speech Delay. We sought help immediately through the resources that SOMACC connected us with, but to our dismay (due to the short supply of speech therapists in the city), we had to wait indefinitely (several months) to be paired with a speech therapist. Inevitably, we became very concerned that the developmental gap would widen between our son and his peers. In the meantime, my husband and I did our best at home to help encourage our son's language by being resourceful and accessing any materials that would teach us tools. However, it was the additional attention and support given to him by our son's teachers that motivated him to speak, even more. They would also send us video clips of his progress and keep track of each new word he spoke. We are happy to report that our son's speech development is now age-appropriate, and even excelling! Thank you to the teachers, who stood beside us throughout this journey. And thank you to the administration and staff for always making our family feel like a part of theirs.

reviews.author: Alex P
reviews.text: Amazing staff

reviews.author: Tiger Muda
reviews.text: Good place

reviews.author: Carole C
reviews.text: As a family daycare owner, I have known Fran for many years. She is a dedicated and passionate provider who creates a calm and engaging environment where young children can thrive. Your child will be in wonderful hands!

reviews.author: Alexis Hanley
reviews.text:
We can‚Äôt say enough about how wonderful Petite Journey and the director and lead teacher, Carole, are. We were hard-pressed to find a daycare we loved in the city for our daughter and we were incredibly lucky to find the Petite Journey community.

Carole and her team of expert teachers pay attention to every detail, from each child‚Äôs interests and preferences to helping navigate potty training and consistency at home vs. school. She was so welcoming that our daughter immediately felt at home. Initially, our daughter struggled with language and Carole was so helpful when it came to providing support with this.

We highly recommend Petite Journey to any family, especially those interested in French immersion and an engaging and joyful environment for their little ones to thrive in!

reviews.author: Molly Hammer
reviews.text: We couldn't ask for a better daycare! My son started when he was 19 months, and I was so nervous about naps or whether he would get enough attention, and our experience with Carole has exceeded every expectation. It's such a relief to know when we can't be with him during the day, he is in the best hands and learning and thriving from Carole's loving and child-centered teaching approach. Besides Carole, the other teachers are all so warm and engaged with our son and update us every day with the news things he is learning. We also love the parent community that Carole has cultivated and is very unique to Petite Journey. We couldn't be more grateful that we found Petite Journey and recommend it to any family, French speaking or not!

reviews.author: Vanick Der Bedrossian
reviews.text:
We feel very lucky to have our son at Petite Journey. Carole brings all of her heart into making her daycare welcoming, nourishing and stimulating for the children.
Her teaching approach is both kind and encouraging for our son to grow up and become more independent and curious. She offers cooking, dance, art, yoga and music classes in a beautiful space, and her back yard is perfect for them to play in.

reviews.author: Susanna Ask
reviews.text:
Carole is a once-in-a-lifetime educator, a nurturing caretaker, and an extremely competent administrator. It's very rare to find all these qualities in one person and, combined with her passion for kids, it makes for an ideal preschool / daycare environment.
We were interested in a language exposure program for our 18-month old and even though neither of us speak French, we decided Petit Journey just felt right.  We've doubled down on that decision twice and kept our daughter there through age 3, as she continues to flourish. She's now speaking French, entirely learned from days with Carole and her wonderful staff.!

reviews.author: Tarik O'Regan
reviews.text: Petite Journey provides a very homey and nurturing environment where Carole, who runs PJ, provides daily French language exposure for 18 to 36 month-olds. Our little one (19m) is really thriving and soaking up the play-based activities, visits to local parks, and loving atmosphere. He had never been out to daycare before but Carole has managed the transition for him with incredible patience, care, and professionalism. This is a truly wonderful environment and we could not be happier.

reviews.author: Dana Bishara
reviews.text:
It breaks my heart that we are leaving Helen's daycare, moving to PreSchool.
Helen is a caring loving caregiver, where I felt safe leaving my daughter. She also provided babysitting services when needed showing understanding and care for young parents, too. We were lucky finding such a warm nice place- we are more than grateful, Helen ‚ù§Ô∏è Thank you, and we all will miss you.

reviews.author: Kyle Chapin
reviews.text: Helen & Angel Baby Childcare are awesome! They took such great care of my child for which I am eternally grateful.  It is a small group of children, so if there is an opening grab it, because your child will get lots of individualized attention. They provide good healthy meals, lots of updates with pictures throughout the day, and take them outside to play at the playground every day. My son would get a big smile on his face when dropping him off & I always knew that he was in good hands.  Thank you so much Helen & Angel Baby Childcare üëçüëç

reviews.author: M
reviews.text: We had a fantastic experience with Angel Baby Childcare. If you are reading this, you are lucky to have found them. Helen and her team are simply amazing. After multiple unsatisfying trails with nannies for our then 3.5 month old daughter, we decided to work with Helen because she seemed great from the beginning. Such a great decision. Our daughter loved Helen and always gave her a big smile when we drop her off in the morning. She is sweet, loving, and professional. She sends us pictures and videos of our daughter during the day, which made me feel at ease during the time that all those hormones gave me unrealistic fears and anxieties. We stayed with her for over 8 months. Our daughter got accepted to a preschool a bit earlier than expected and we were sad to leave Angel Baby Childcare. Otherwise we would have stayed longer. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Lauren Bryant Alhart
reviews.text:
I cannot say enough about our wonderful experience with Angel Baby. We started our baby there at 4 months and now at 10 months he leaps from my arms into hers every morning. He has benefitted from the socialization with a mix of babies and toddlers and has grown immensely. They take wonderful care of him, and he is not an easy baby!

It's a small group, which I really like. They take the kids out every day to a different park or to the library and feed them healthy meals. We will be staying as long as we possibly can. Thank you, Helen and May!

reviews.author: Michael Rossi
reviews.text: We've had an incredible experience with Helen and her staff at Angel baby. As first time parents, it's been really important to us to drop our baby off somewhere where he feels happy, where the staff looks happy to have him, and where they will take amazing and attentive care of him everyday. Helen has absolutely created that exact environment. Our son is beaming and giggling when he sees her everyday, and she and her staff look at him the same way, which truly makes it feel like she's an extension of our family. Her and her staff's demeanor is so cheery, pleasant, and caring, it makes me so happy to know our son has the opportunity to spend time with her and other little ones each day. Highly recommend!

name: Au P'tit Monde de San Francisco

reviews.author: Touran Taj Samii
reviews.text: We couldn't be happier with our experience at APM, it's truly a special preschool. The teachers and staff are dedicated to making your child feel loved, cared for, and at home. Their carefully curated French curriculum keeps your child engaged and constantly learning new skills. And the fact that they have a dedicated cook who cooks organic and nutritious meals everyday is unbelievable. If you're considering APM for your child, consider that you'll be part of a supportive and loving community of teachers and parents who will be with you every step of your journey

reviews.author: allison filice
reviews.text: This is our fourth year with Au P'tit Monde (two children have attended preschool here) and it truly feels like a second home to us. The teachers and the entire team are so loving and wonderful. The food is amazing, the crafts and creative projects are adorable, and it's so amazing to hear my children speaking french. Most of all my children have experienced so much love and care at APM. I'm truly grateful for this wonderful school.

reviews.author: Akhil Gupta
reviews.text: We've been with APM for three years, and wish the school had more grades so we could stay longer! Our son has attended APM since he was two. To say he has flourished under APM's care would be an understatement! The teachers, the curriculum, the community, the wonderful staff, the language immersion - each is A+ on its own. Together they create the warmest and most engaging environment for our son to thrive in. We highly highly recommend APM!

reviews.author: Tara Holmes
reviews.text:
I simply cannot say enough wonderful things about APM. This is now our 4th year at the school, with my son starting preschool this past fall (my 6 year old daughter attended APM all three years and still speaks highly of the school and staff and often returns to pick up my son to enjoy spending time with her old teachers!). Ultimately, both of my children have thrived here ‚Äî the curriculum is thoughtful and diverse, the staff feel like family, and the parent community is warm and engaged. The school-provided lunches and general celebration of cuisine and culture is a rich touch!

You simply cannot go wrong enrolling your child at APM, and if you‚Äôre looking for bilingual education (and/or you just want your child to have a fantastic and supportive preschool expertise) look no further!

reviews.author: Scott Booth
reviews.text: APM is the best! My wife and I have had both our children attend and we have known the teachers and staff for three years now. Their teachers are highly qualified and amazing with kids. Most of the teachers have been working there for a long time. My kids love going to school. They are learning French! I cannot speak more highly of this program. The community they create is supportive. Their communication is frequent and they get back to you within minutes! I can‚Äôt recommend APM more! Send your kid(s) here!!!

name: UCSF at Laurel Heights Child Development Center

reviews.author: Liz Winter
reviews.text: Kind and loving teachers, and beautiful classrooms with lots of natural light. People smile and say hello in the hall, feels very welcoming. I feel so good about taking my grandkids there.

reviews.author: Freddy Juarez
reviews.text: A very beautiful and clean place where you can let your child be taken care of.

reviews.author: Jasmine J
reviews.text:
Pac Heights Kidz was our first daycare experience for our daughter, who started when she was about 2.5 years old, and it was wonderful - all of the teachers and staff were so friendly, caring and welcoming, and our daughter always came home happy and excited about her day. They sent lots of updates and pics, as well as a weekly newsletter about what the kids had got up to that week, so I always felt like I knew what was happening.

I also liked how they put on lots of events to help you get to know the teachers and other families, and they put so much effort into helping our daughter (and us!) settle in. It really felt like a little community. We sadly had to leave due to relocating, but otherwise we would have happily kept our daughter here until she went to school - we were very sad to leave! Highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Bex Meagher
reviews.text:
We call it **Adventure School** because they take your little ones on the most incredible outings across the city‚Äîall included in your tuition! Not only that, but they also serve delicious, nutritious meals and snacks, and the owners, along with their children, are incredibly kind and welcoming.

They recently won **Best Daycare in San Francisco**, and it‚Äôs so well deserved!

Victor and Fabiana care for and celebrate each child as if they were their own. Every day, they create a safe, engaging environment filled with outdoor adventures, creative crafts, enriching learning topics, and wholesome organic meals. Their dedication to safety and well-being is impeccable. Our child absolutely loves spending time with his friends and affectionately calls Fabiana and Victor "Mamai and Papai." Seeing his excitement each morning is the best testament to the love and energy they pour into this daycare.

Without a doubt, I would **highly recommend** this incredible daycare to any parent with a child from infancy to around 4 or 5 years old.

Thank you, Victor and Fabiana, for taking such amazing care of our little one‚Äîwe are beyond grateful!

reviews.author: Abby McBeth
reviews.text: Victor and Fabiana are wonderful caretakers. Our 2-year-old daughter has attended Childcare 94133 full time for a little over a year and loves seeing her friends and going on adventures all over the city. They frequently go to the Exploratorium, the Aquarium, music hour, the library, and playground after playground. I love knowing our daughter is exploring her city and discovering play outside of a fluorescent lit classroom. She frequently tries new foods, comes home singing new songs, and new Spanish words every day. They care for our daughter as one of their own and we‚Äôre lucky to be a part of the community they‚Äôve built.

reviews.author: Rachel Carney
reviews.text:
This family-run daycare is a gem in the city! When we were looking for childcare for our 6 month old son a year ago we immediately felt at ease meeting Fabiana and Victor in their love-filled home. They treat each child in the daycare like their own. Their own youngest children are in the daycare and the older kids help out before and after school, so we feel like our baby is one of the family!

This daycare is truly unique in that they take the children out for adventures every day. They go to one of several playgrounds or museums in the area. It‚Äôs always adorable to see pictures of the babies in their 4-seat stroller or wagon. We‚Äôve loved that our kiddo has so much fun both in the daycare and outside.

They keep a great schedule with the kids and have helped our baby through big transitions such starting solid foods and going from two naps to one. They provide diapers, home cooked healthy lunches and two snacks a day plus cow‚Äôs milk if your baby drinks that. My kid eats so good there!

We have also loved getting to know the other families at the daycare with birthday parties and family festivals or holiday celebrations we‚Äôll all attend together.

Fabiana and Victor have made such a welcoming, caring, and nurturing home- away-from-home for our son. If we were not moving out of state we would definitely keep him here as long as we could!

reviews.author: Puck Wilkes
reviews.text:
The best daycare for your loved little ones! If I could give 6 stars I would.
My daughter has been going to Fabiana and her fantastic family for 1.5 years now and she always comes home SO happy. Before putting her into daycare, I used to see so many disengaged nannies and caregivers spending more times looking at their phone screens than engaging with the kids. Until I met Fabiana and Victor; taking care of the kids so lovingly, like they are truly part of their family. My daughter comes home bubbling with positive energy, because she learns so much at the professional preschool methods they follow and teach (singing the alphabet at age 2!), she loves the fresh homemade meals, she learns and enjoys going to museums, playgrounds and beaches, all the beautiful arts and crafts she makes every day, the costumes she wears, the dance parties and music she listens to every day, the way she feels so loved. She talks about her friends and Fabiana and Victor EVERY day of the year because she absolutely adores them.
A day at the Edmundo family (Childcare 94133) is a day guaranteed for the most fun and a happy child!! I could go on and on and on. Happy to do so, just let me know :).
So if you‚Äôre looking for the best caregivers for your child? Look no further. Just make sure to schedule that interview and reserve your spot on time, because they‚Äôre the best in SF (North Beach)

reviews.author: Justin Brandt
reviews.text: Our daughter has been going here for the last year and is really blossoming.  Fabiana and Victor are so great for her and to her.  They do tons of activities with the kids which is great for their development!

reviews.author: Jon Roman
reviews.text: Our two boys have been going to the Montessori School of San Francisco since they were very young and we could not be happier with our experience at the school. The teachers are not only loving, but truly are invested in the children‚Äôs education and development. The environment is friendly, warm, and welcoming; and both our boys have thrived from an early age. They are now ages 3 and 5 and we feel that each of the classrooms have fostered their curiosity for learning. Ms. Vasi has truly been a mentor to us, and has become a part of our family. She has helped us navigate through some challenging stages of parenting and has partnered with us to achieve specific outcomes (potty training, naps, etc). This school is a place where children feel accepted and loved, and we highly recommend it for any family looking at schools for their children.

reviews.author: nicole wilson
reviews.text:
I am so happy that I enrolled my toddler daughter in this school. She started when she was 15 months and will be turning 2 in a few weeks. She enjoys her time and is excited when we arrive. Everyday she does new activities and her teachers are always so kind and caring. Ms. Vasi has a heart for the children and runs the school in a professional and empathetic way.

This school provided me with such confidence when I am at work because I know my daughter is in a place that cares for her and will help her grow!

reviews.author: Joshua Marcy
reviews.text:
I would highly recommend Montessori School of San Francisco. My son has been attending this daycare for the past 3 months and I have been extremely impressed with the quality of care he has received.

The facilities are clean, well-maintained, and age-appropriate. There is plenty of space for the children to play and explore, both indoors and outdoors. My son has made so many new friends at daycare and he loves Ms. Vasi.

reviews.author: Bex/Marcus Nguyen/Chlopek
reviews.text: As new parents we were extremely nervous to leave our son with someone we did not know. Ms. Vasi put us at ease during the interviewing process because it was clear to us that she and all of the teachers are so loving and caring with every single student. Our son, at 5 months old, is excited to get to school where his mind is stimulated and he is well taken care of. We feel extremely lucky to have found this safe and caring team. We highly recommend the Montessori School of San Francisco!

reviews.author: Isaac Gate√±o
reviews.text:
Our daughter has been in Miss Mirna‚Äôs class since last year. She absolutely LOVES it. When we get to school she always has a big smile on her face and doesn‚Äôt even say goodbye to me as she walks in.

Ms Vasi and all of the teachers are super communicative. They tel us what‚Äôs going on at school and collaborate with us on things like moving past baby bottles and pacifiers.

We‚Äôre really happy with Montessori SF and would (and have!) recommend to family and friends.

reviews.author: Stephanie Sheehan
reviews.text: We have had a wonderful experience at Mama Bear Daycare. Maria provided a loving and nurturing environment for our first daughter from when she was 8 months old until about 2.5 years old. Our daughter absolutely loved her time with both Maria and Lupe. Now, our son has also started at Mama Bear at around 10 months old. We love the daily updates on how the kids are doing during the day including photos, details on their naps, meals, etc. Maria has been a huge help working with both of our kids helping them reach developmental milestones such as walking and talking and she works with each family on their preferred nap schedule. The kids enjoy the playtime, neighborhood outings and especially outside play. We highly recommend Mama Bear Daycare!

reviews.author: Danielle DeLong
reviews.text: I can't recommend Mama Bear daycare enough! Our son started when he was 9 months old and it has been a wonderful experience. Maria provided a nurturing and loving environment for her kids and our son quickly adapted to loving daycare. He has learned valuable skills and has become a fabulous eater with Maria's help! Maria provides daily updates regarding his meals, naps and overall mood. Maria is a very calm and caring person. It give us tremendous relief our son is in good hands every day. Thank you Mama Bear!

reviews.author: Kyna Wise
reviews.text: Mama Bear Home DayCare is a wonderful environment for any kid. I worked with Maria for seven years in a childcare so I not only know her loving, nurturing personality with children but I also know her outstanding work ethic. When she opened up her own childcare it made perfect sense to all of us, her family of childcare co-workers. Not only did it make sense, but we all fought to get placement for our own kids with her since we trust her to be clean and careful and kind.  If we had a friend with a new baby we would recommend Maria's care. She has an incredible watchful eye so we knew our kids were safest with her. She has a calm and effective way of managing kids of all ages. My godchildren have been in her care and they always were picked up with smiles on their faces and usually a new letter they were learning how to identify. A sweet memory I have is coming to pick up my kid and another child in the care was learning to identify A, B, and C. Maria made an announcement and gave the child a chance to present what he's learned. He said the letters loud and clear and all the parents and kids cheered him on and celebrated his win. These experience, while very special, are part of the normal day in Mama Bear Day Care. She truly celebrates the growth of every child that steps in her care.

reviews.author: David Duchen
reviews.text: Happy Trails is an amazing daycare! Crystal and her team are processional, kind, caring, responsive and so very helpful. Our child had an incredible experience here, and was so excited to arrive each day. Since our home was located in a different part of the city, we literally spent 30min driving each way to Happy Trails, and it was worth every moment. The team is so wonderful and nurturing, and it is awesome that the daycare is also Mandarin immersion. The only reason we left is because we relocated to a new city, but we talked often about wishing Crystal would open an additional Happy Trails location in the new city to which we moved. We cannot recommend this daycare enough.

reviews.author: Deepika Desai
reviews.text:
Happy Trails was the best decision we made as parents!

Crystal, Bella and Amma genuinely take great care of the children  their own. The kids are mentally and physically active, focus on music and arts - all while learning to be bilingual!

It was a teary goodbye once we left the daycare and feel that we have said goodbye to not only incredibly kind and professional team, but an extended family.

We prioritized a feeling of warmth and inspiration over beige toned daycares that charge an arm and a leg and couldn't be more glad.

Miss the team at daycare and Diya still asks about everyone!

reviews.author: Stevie Holden
reviews.text: This place was our gem while we lived in SF we hated leaving we had unfortunate family circumstances that moved us back east. This school is PRECIOUS! I loved when my little would teach me words in mandarin. I got pics every day of all of the fun activities and learning they were doing. Crystal has the best team, loves the kids and wants them to thrive! The best communication and always so gracious with my family. 10/10 would recommend!

reviews.author: Katie Soltis
reviews.text: We loved having our son at Happy Trails! Crystal, Lorraine, and the rest of the teachers are all wonderful. Our son started very young, and Crystal and the team eased the transition for us as first time parents. Our baby lit up whenever he arrived at daycare. They sent us great pictures throughout the day and did a lot of fun activities. We couldn't recommend it more!

reviews.author: Bingying Wang
reviews.text: My son started going to Happy trial daycare when he was 18 months old. At first, he had a hard time adjusting to the new environment, Crystal and the team were very patient and always stayed by his side.  During those early days, Crystal sent me a lot of  photos every day to keep me updated on how my child is doing at daycare, which made me feel very reassured. After about a month, my son really like going to daycare. They provide three meals a day, which is very convenient for parents. All the staffs are so friendly and supportive.  My son has learned and grown so much with these wonderful staffs!

reviews.author: Lisa Abdilova Andresen
reviews.text: Sandy & the team are so warm & compassionate towards our 3yo boy. He's been thriving. From his first day, his mood lifted. His social interactions are encouraged. There's so many activities, including structured circle time and independent play. The facility is beautiful with a lovely selection of toys. Our son is learning entrepreneurship from the lemonade and ice cream stand! The staff are all familiar with behavioral interventions, integrate occupational therapy into activities, and update us daily on their activities and Cody's development through an app with photos and comprehensive summaries of his participation and things they're working on with Cody specifically. The ratios are small. They even started potty training him in his first 2 months and encouraged us to bring that home. This place is a gem!

reviews.author: YONGLI WU
reviews.text: Our child has received exceptional care at this daycare since April this year.The teachers and the owner are incredibly attentive and nurturing. Our little one has grown so much, both in skills and confidence, and enjoys interacting with the other children. It‚Äôs truly heartwarming to see our child so happy, and that happiness brings us joy as well. We‚Äôre very grateful!‚Äù

reviews.author: Maricel P
reviews.text:
A safe, loving and nurturing environment that support healthy growth and development, challenging young children to learn and prepare them for kindergarten.
My son kenzo was been here for 8 months, and he improved a lot. I love this place.

reviews.author: Chloe Kuang
reviews.text: My daughter loves the school very much. She is very happy and active here. The school activities are rich and interesting. She enjoys everything here, including the teachers. They are very patient and responsible. Thank you for all!

reviews.author: Michelle Rong
reviews.text: The modern play space is a fun and creative early development education place. Teachers are very nice and patient. They teach kids singing, crafting, drawing...so many activities. The kids will have a lot of fun in this play group. I would highly recommend the modern play space to parents for your toddler child!

reviews.author: Ana Harris-Padley
reviews.text: Highly recommend. Our daughter has attended for two years (ages 2.5 to 4.5). Fabulous staff from teachers to those that run the school. Great student/teacher ratio, attentive and caring, and good mix of social and educational learning. They use Brightwheel for communication and photos which is great to get updates on your little one(s). We'll be sad to leave the school as our daughter heads to public school/TK but PE has definitely prepared her well!

reviews.author: Lisa Mendelman
reviews.text: Echoing everyone's rave reviews! I have had two children at PE Nopa over the past two years -- my son started in the Petite Room at age 2.5 last August and is now in the Discover Room at age 4.5, my daughter started in the Petite Room at age 2 this August. We have been thrilled with everything about the school. The teachers are phenomenal--nurturing, engaged, and well-educated. The husband and wife owners/admins Vickie and Andy equally thoughtful, experienced, and caring (they are very involved and often sub in when teachers are out, so they really know my kids, which I love). Communication is seamless. The site is also great--up to date facilities, indoor-outdoor space, and (most important to my children) endless activities. The project-based learning is perfect: my kids have learned so much about bees (my son) and airplanes (my daughter). I really can't say enough good things about our experience and recommend it without reservation.

reviews.author: Amanda Webb
reviews.text: My son is nearing the end of his second year at Petite Explorer NOPA. He started at just over two years old and only spoke a handful of words at that time. He has blossomed in so many areas thanks to the staff and friends at Petite Explorer. Love the classroom, outdoor space, variety of activities and seeing his interests grow! Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Julia Tanase
reviews.text: Our son Wesley has been going to Petite Explorers for a year and he absolutely adores it.  The teachers are wonderful and the program director Vicky is very organized, responsive and attentive.  It‚Äôs a wonderful preschool that we highly recommend.

name: L‚ÄôAcademy Language Immersion Preschool & Infant Daycare Hayes Valley San Francisco

reviews.author: Arnaud D.
reviews.text: Our little one loves it here. We feel lucky to have found a spot at this daycare!

reviews.author: Ula Popov
reviews.text: We love it!!

reviews.author: Jayson Shmueli
reviews.text:
Sky Bear is an excellent daycare. We have had at least one of our kids at Sky Bear for over the last two years and we could not have asked for anything more.

Shanshan had our kids saying please and thank you after the first week, and that was just the beginning. They foster a great atmosphere of fun and learning.

When our oldest started preschool, they were amazed by how prepared he was, and that was all thanks to Sky Bear.

reviews.author: Austin Bodek Hahn
reviews.text: We looked at various daycares and decided our daughter would thrive in Skybear's smaller and more intimate setting. We're so happy with our decision. Shanshan and James are kind and empathetic. Our daughter who is shy and timid loves going to "school". We plan to send our next kid once he's old enough.

reviews.author: Jan Crisostomo
reviews.text:
Our son started going to Sky Bear since he was one year old. Shanshan runs an amazing program (her daycare is much more like a play-based preschool than the traditional home daycare), and in the short time our son has been in her care, he's thrived and learned to interact well with other kids. It's always a good feeling when your kid is happy to arrive and sad to leave daycare!!!

I was so lucky to have found them on a whim via Google Maps shortly after they opened. I was having a tough time finding an available or adequate program around Noe Valley and Bernal. If you get a spot at this wonderful place, don't hesitate!

reviews.author: Dave Reed
reviews.text: called to inquire about Thats So Raven since the hous ewas used in the show. The owner was not pleased nor a fan of the show. However I do respect the fact she was strictly only would speak on her business. Which to me, it showed she is very caring and serious on her business. Seems like a great daycare and pleasant owner. Just wish she would answer a few more questions. But i appreciated the time she spent to answer a few during her business hours. I apologize and i do know some people in san fran that i will be referring to you for services. Thank you!

reviews.author: neha vyas
reviews.text: Since joining this amazing daycare, our daughter has picked up so many good habits, speaks a lot, is learning so many things daily. Before the daycare, she used to be a picky eater but since joining - she eats much better - all thanks to Vika‚Äôs amazing food. Our daughter has also become more social and confident around other children and adults. Thanks for all you do for the children!

reviews.author: Linda
reviews.text: I can‚Äôt say enough good things about Garden Daycare (and their sister center, Three Bears Childcare). The director, Mama Vika and her team are so passionate about children and their development, it shows in everything they do! I had our oldest (who‚Äôs 6 now) there and through their Reggio Emelia inspired approach, despite having since been in only language immersion programs, remembers her ABCs, songs, etc. I now have our youngest there (who‚Äôs one) and she is so excited at drop off, it warms my heart. Not only do they take excellent care of the children, they also send constant updates that make my day. I highly recommend Garden Childcare - they‚Äôre more than a place to send your kids, they become family.

reviews.author: Monica Turner
reviews.text: Our daughter has been in Garden Daycare for about a year and a half and absolutely loves it. She learns a lot, eats healthy and loves the time with all of her friends.  We also get lots of pictures throughout the day and even a periodic date night which is awesome. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Kristen Cunanan
reviews.text: We started our 10 mo old son in March 2021 and are so happy we found this place!!  We were nervous to start daycare in COVID, but the staff have been very professional about the children's health and safety - they are all vaccinated but continue to wear masks and all the parents are good about keeping kids home to reduce the spread of any illnesses.   My son loves going to daycare here - he greets Vika with a hug and during the day, we get some photos of him playing with his friends.  We have noticed our son has learned a lot of new skills from watching/interacting with the other kids.  We can also tell he is clearly loved there, which is always reassuring when you leave your kid 8 hrs/day.  He eats 5 home cooked, organic meals a day and we know he is getting good food (he only likes tasty home cooked meals, I've tried to give him some plain things or packaged food at home and he won't eat it).  He has also been going to Three Bears some days (the sister daycare center) and loves it there too. It is really nice because Stacey has connected the parents of children who are friends at daycare, to help facilitate play dates since it has been difficult in COVID.  Stacey and Vika are amazing care takers and wonderful people to work with. When our second son was born, we didn't have any family nearby to help.  But Vika and Stacey have been incredibly flexible in helping us find extra days at daycare so our son could stay there while my husband was with me at the hospital, since sibling children are not allowed in the hospital during COVID. We don't know what we would have done without their help in this situation.  It is clear to us they genuinely care about each child and we feel like they are part of our family.  They've also helped us with advise on baby's care/schedule too. We will be starting our second son there in 2022 when he is old enough.  We highly recommend Garden and Three Bears to parents looking for a place for their children to be safe, loved and thrive socially.

reviews.author: Tyson Redenbarger
reviews.text: Garden Daycare is great. My daughter goes there and everyone in my family loves the school and everyone who works there. Its a great place for children. There are many activities and the kids eat well. Truly highly recommended.

reviews.author: Jane Herrmann
reviews.text: Our daughter Emmy has been attending Tuya's daycare for the last month, and I have nothing but good things to say. She is so incredibly attentive and caring with my daughter - and treats her, as if she were her own. Every day when we drop Emmy off, she greets Tuya with a big, bright smile, which serves as a huge testament to how she is being cared for. Thank you, Tuya for taking such good care of our little girl!

reviews.author: Gloria Wee
reviews.text: Anyone would be blessed to be able to send their children to Tuya's daycare. She genuinely cares deeply for all the children, including our daughter Lana, who has never had a single day of separation anxiety since I started sending her to Tuya's daycare since she was 8 months old. She extends the warmth of her family to the small but tight community of families that are lucky to send our children to Tuya's family home. Her assistant, husband and two young teenage children all chip in to help care for the babies and shower them with love. We couldnt have asked for more. Tuya also home cooks great, healthy breakfast and lunches. She is flexible and understanding, and is 100% fluent in English (many surrounding Mongolian daycares aren't). Our daughter is 'graduating' to pre-school soon, but we honestly can't bare to leave!

reviews.author: Katie Watson
reviews.text: We have absolutely loved Tuya‚Äôs Daycare for our daughter, Maya! Tuya has taken such good care of her, and Maya gets so excited every morning when she sees Tuya. Tuya has created a safe, colorful, happy space for Maya and the other kids and daycare and we feel so grateful to have found her. She gives Maya so much close attention, feeds her wonderful meals, and has taught her so much. Maya is even saying new words in Mongolian now! I would highly recommend Tuya‚Äôs Daycare to anyone looking for a homey daycare environment with a low ratio of kids to providers where their child will be loved like they‚Äôre family.

reviews.author: Amber Eggers
reviews.text:
We love Building Kidz and couldn‚Äôt be happier with our decision to send our son here. From day one, the warmth and dedication of the teachers and staff have made this place feel like a second home. Our son literally runs into school every morning with a huge smile and a wave goodbye‚Äîhe genuinely loves being there, which says everything.

What makes Building Kidz truly special is the way the teachers encourage each child to be their best, all while making learning fun and play-centered. The environment is nurturing, joyful, and filled with positive energy.

We‚Äôve had the pleasure of being in two wonderful classrooms with Ms. Maddie and Ms. Janet, and we absolutely adore them. They bring so much heart, creativity, and care into their teaching.

It‚Äôs a fantastic school, and we can‚Äôt recommend it enough to any family looking for a place where their child will thrive.

reviews.author: Kate Medina
reviews.text:
Building Kidz Clement has been an incredible experience for my daughter and our family. The preschool provides an excellent blend of education and performing arts, fostering both academic and creative growth. The teachers are passionate, caring, and truly dedicated to the children's development.

We feel so fortunate to be part of the Building Kidz Clement community, which feels like a warm and supportive family. Watching my daughter thrive in such a nurturing environment has been a joy. I highly recommend Building Kidz Clement to any parent looking for a place where their child can learn, grow, and flourish!

reviews.author: Megan Dunn Caruthers
reviews.text: Our son has been going to BuildingKidz Clement since he was 2 years old. We feel soooooo lucky to have found such a wonderful, caring school for him. I cannot sing BK‚Äôs praises enough! The teachers are all so, so loving, and the Director is an amazing person. The kiddos do performing arts (and do 2 shows per year for parents!), do tons of arts and crafts, have structured learning time, and also get to play outside. They even do field trips (pumpkin patch, academy of sciences, Salesforce park etc). Our son comes home everyday talking about his friends, his teachers & singing cute little songs that they sing at school. They even helped potty train!!! We love BK so much!!!! Highly recommend ü§ç

reviews.author: Tayler Gaffney
reviews.text: Building Kidz has been such an amazing school for my daughter. The owner, director, and teachers are all so kind, welcoming, and loving towards the children. I get daily photos and updates via the Building Kidz app and it‚Äôs so fun to see what they‚Äôre up to throughout the day. They consistently have performing arts classes that have taught my daughter so much. We could not have asked for a better preschool experience!

reviews.author: Meg
reviews.text: Our child has been attending Buildingkidz since he was almost 3. He will be graduating at the end of July! We have been thrilled be the care he has received and watching him grow into himself. He loves all of time for playing and doing art as well as the theater, music and dance classes. We love seeing what he‚Äôs learning at home. Thank you to all the teachers who make him feel so loved and have supported his growth!!

name: Friends of St Francis Child Cr

reviews.author: Thip R
reviews.text:
From head master/director Sally to every teachers, they offer loving and caring environment here. My niece came here when she's about to turn 3, and barely spoke English because she's learning two languages. The teachers and care givers are super gentle and warm.

The classes and space are small. They manage and can handle all groups very well. The management and teachers encourage community based environment, and involve parents into children activities.

My niece is a very happy 4 years old who love coming to this school.

reviews.author: soumya sastry
reviews.text: My son has been so happy with these caring teachers. We will miss this charming, low key place.

reviews.author: Anthony Thomas
reviews.text: Its in a Great environment.

reviews.author: star ella
reviews.text: I used to go here üòÅ

reviews.author: Irene Sun
reviews.text:
Apple Tree Daycare has exceeded all expectations for our family. As a parent, I was incredibly anxious about my son's transition from being at home to attending daycare at 21 months. He was very attached to both me and my husband, so I worried about how he would adjust to this new environment.

From our very first interaction, Jasmine, the owner, was exceptionally warm and welcoming. She immediately put us at ease and worked with us to make the transition as smooth as possible. We also appreciate how hands-on Jasmine is; seeing her greet the kids at drop-off and say goodbye at pick-up every day, and how incredibly responsive she is to any emails or messages, makes us feel connected and informed.

What has impressed me most is the truly loving atmosphere all the teachers at Apple Tree create - you can genuinely feel how deeply they care about each child. Especially Ruby, whose gentle approach and consistent care have helped my son feel so secure and happy in this new environment.

My son has thrived under their care, and the peace of mind this has given us is truly priceless. Seeing him happy and excited to go to daycare each morning absolutely confirms we made the right choice. I would recommend Apple Tree with all my heart to any parent looking for a nurturing environment where their child will be loved and supported.

reviews.author: Kristen Wang
reviews.text: Our family couldn‚Äôt be happier that we found the perfect bilingual (Mandarin and English) daycare for our little one. Our 19 month old son has been going to Apple Tree since he was 14 months old, and the teachers at Apple Tree have taken excellent care of him and we are so grateful that he is healthy, happy and learning everyday. He was a sensitive, shy little boy at first and it took him two weeks to adjust to daycare settings, but Jasmine and her crew were so patient and sweet to him that he now can‚Äôt wait to go to Apple Tree in the morning to see his friends and teachers. The outdoor space is nice and big, and the curriculum is amazing, we are so pleasantly amazed by the new words our son learns from Apple Tree every week and he even learned to count! They also have outdoor soccer classes, music classes, arts and crafts, sensory plays every week, our son absolutely loves those classes and he would sing us the tunes that he learned from music classes, how adorable! The meals they provide at Apple Tree are nutritious and delicious, and they save us a ton of time to meal prep at home, we couldn‚Äôt be more grateful. I would highly recommend Apple Tree to any family who wants their kids to flourish in a safe, caring, and loving environment.

reviews.author: Leeyen Rogers
reviews.text:
I cannot imagine a better place to send my son full-time. My toddler has been going to Apple Tree since he was 6 months old and has loved it since day one. He practically flies out of my arms in excitement when I drop him off in the morning, he has big smiles for his warm and caring teachers and is so happy to be there.

Jasmine and her staff are the best. Their communication is great- we get updates of anything relevant from that day. There‚Äôs also an app where we can message anytime. The photos that my husband and I receive make our day and get shared with the grandparents.

The school is run so professionally with a weekly newsletter detailing activities and menus (breakfast, lunch and snacks are provided!). The facilities are clean and beautiful with a private backyard and garden, and our baby has developed so well in their care!

He is learning and growing so much, and we love that he is getting Mandarin exposure. They certainly keep the kids busy with a variety of creative, fun and developmentally beneficial activities that go beyond what I have the bandwidth to provide! I love receiving the art he‚Äôs made at school.

We are so thankful for Apple Tree!!

reviews.author: Deborah
reviews.text: My son first attended Apple Tree back in 2018 at their old location. Jasmine and the teachers are so kind and good at what they do so when we had our second child, there was no doubt that she would attend Apple Tree as well. Jasmine is a wonderful caregiver and their new facility on Folsom St is great with lots of outdoor space. Facilities are kept clean and they offer breakfast, snacks and lunch! They also host a once a month Parent‚Äôs Day on Saturdays so parents can enjoy some quality time to themselves. My whole family loves Apple Tree! If you are looking for a safe clean nurturing environment for your young child to thrive in (with the additional benefit of being in a Mandarin immersion program) please consider Apple Tree. You won‚Äôt regret it!

reviews.author: Julia Barbarino
reviews.text: Our daughter has been attending Apple Tree for over three years, and we couldn't be happier with our experience. From her first day at just a year old, Jasmine and the other teachers have been incredibly kind, loving, responsive and communicative. There seems to be very low turnover - many of the same teachers who were there when she started are still there today. As working parents we love that they provide breakfast, lunch and snacks there, and that they offer backup care on most holidays! They just moved to a new facility which is absolutely wonderful, with an amazing outdoor play area and a cheerful, clean and well-organized indoor space. They just started offering preschool, allowing us to keep our daughter there until kindergarten. We have been very pleased with her progress on her letters, numbers, counting, etc., as well as her social and emotional development. They do soccer class every week and we have been very impressed by the lesson plans as well. For example, last week was all about planet Earth and our daughter has been talking about planets every day since. We originally chose Apple Tree because it had excellent reviews and we lived close by in the Mission. Since then, we moved to Inner Sunset making the commute three times as long, but we never even considered switching daycares; Apple Tree really does feel like a part of our family at this point. We just started our 6 month old there (which could not have gone more smoothly, thanks to Jasmine and all the wonderful teachers!!) and we are so glad that he has so many years ahead of him at Apple Tree!

name: Suen An Child Care (Learn n Play)

reviews.author: Peitong Duan
reviews.text: Great drop-in daycare service. Very flexible.

reviews.author: E Dyer
reviews.text:
Fantastic Daycare Experience!

We absolutely loved sending our child, Rio, to Carmen‚Äôs daycare for his first ever daycare experience: from 6 months to almost 1 year old. Carmen‚Äôs daycare felt like an extension of our family. From day one, it was clear that Carmen is deeply invested in the children she cares for‚Äîher personal attention to each child made us feel completely at ease, knowing Rio was in the best hands. Her home was always safe, clean, and well-maintained, and she often took the kids out for engaging activities that Rio really enjoyed.

Rio absolutely adored Carmen. He thrived under her care, and it was amazing to see his development, especially when she introduced him to basic sign language! Her dedication to the children‚Äôs growth and well-being shines through in everything she does. Sadly, we had to move too far away, otherwise, we would still be taking him to her today.

Carmen was also a joy to communicate with. She was always open, direct, and easy to talk to. She gave us updates at every pick-up, making sure we were informed of Rio‚Äôs day and any new milestones. She would also send us tons of cute photos throughout the day. It was so reassuring to hear how happy and engaged he was throughout the day, and he was always excited to see Carmen each morning.

The space Carmen created for the kids was wonderful. She constantly thought of ways to improve the environment for the children, and it was clear she put so much love into her daycare practice. Rio gained so much from being there, both socially and developmentally.

I would highly recommend Carmen to any parent looking for an incredible daycare. If we were still living in the Tenderloin, we would never have left. Carmen, thank you for the love and care you gave Rio‚Äîhe misses you so much! You are a truly wonderful person with so much to offer the children in your care.

reviews.author: Carmen Rodriguez
reviews.text:
I highly recommend this place for childcare. They are very well cared for, they have the attention they need. Carmen is a great person.
Unfortunately, my baby changed daycare because of his age, but I would have loved for the Papalote staff to have been able to take care of my child for much longer. They learn a lot, something I loved: before he was two years old, he already outgrew putting his plate and cup together where he ate. Thanks to the Papalote team, he taught himself many more things... We really miss going because both my son and I felt that place was our home! ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ú®ü•π

reviews.author: Reyna Cortazar
