I've had the pleasure of knowing Carmen for a few years now, and I can assure you that Carmen is not only an excellent teacher and nanny, but also an excellent person. She has cared for two of my children since they were one year old. As a professional, Carmen puts a lot of effort, dedication, and love into caring for children. I know that this new project Carmen is undertaking will be very successful!
100% recommended.

reviews.author: Fredy Cob
reviews.text: I feel fortunate to have met Carmen, my daughter's teacher from the age of 6 months to 3 years old, and she bonded well with her, making significant progress in her learning and education. Thanks to Carmen, my daughter is very independent in everything she does.

reviews.author: maria paz
reviews.text: I am happy and grateful for the work that teacher Carmen does with my little girl. She has been very attentive to her learning and also keeps us informed about the activities that each girl does, and I recommend her 100%.

reviews.author: Carly Bittman
reviews.text: We met Bibi after visiting several daycares in the neighborhood, and we knew immediately that Little Seeds would be a great fit for our son.  Bibi is so warm, kind, and patient.  Our son has now been with Bibi for over a year and a half and we couldn‚Äôt be more grateful for the care she and the other teachers have given our son.   Bibi provides healthy food and teaches the kids skills like how to share and express themselves.  They are always doing fun art projects and Bibi has a yard where they go out and play.  They also go on adventures in the neighborhood.  We get pictures throughout the day but also get longer updates when our son reaches milestones or accomplishes a skill they‚Äôve been working on.  Our son is heading to preschool soon, but we‚Äôll be back at Little Seeds with our younger child next year!  Thank you Bibi for everything!

reviews.author: My Luu
reviews.text: Little Seeds is amazing! Bibi, the owner and former preschool teacher, truly loves the kids and it shows. In a matter of weeks, my 2-year-old went from not feeding herself independently and struggling with separation anxiety and sharing, to putting on her own shoes, taking turns, and playing beautifully with others. She comes home happy, proud, and full of stories (and artwork!). We only left Little Seeds because my daughter started preschool, otherwise, we‚Äôd be here forever! No concerns ever about my daughter's care, and received photo updates throughout the day. Bibi was very responsive to questions we had and provided amazing care that we felt very safe dropping our child off. Highly recommend!  Cannot say enough great things about this special place and Bibi.

reviews.author: Alexandrea Schmidt
reviews.text: Bibi and her team are wonderful! Our son thrived in their care and transitioned smoothly to a Mandarin immersion preschool thanks to his time at Little Seeds. They provide healthy daily lunches, structured naps, weekly activities, a very clean environment, and speak only Mandarin during the day. Bibi is gentle, respectful, and truly understands children. We felt completely at ease knowing our son was in such good hands.

reviews.author: Alexandra Race
reviews.text:
Our son August (11 months) has been attending Little Seeds Childcare for about 4 months now, and we have been so happy with his care. Bibi and her team of outstanding teachers create a safe, fun, and engaging environment, all while supporting developmental milestones. Within one week of attending Little Seeds, our son had improved his verbal skills (like saying MAMA, so you know I was happy :) ) and gross motor skills. He is always so excited to go to Little Seeds, and from the many photo updates we receive, we can tell how much fun he is having with the other children.

Bibi is incredibly kind, caring, and professional. She has been very accommodating of our part-time schedule, working with us to meet changing nap and feeding needs. I would 100% recommend Little Seeds Childcare to other local parents.

reviews.author: Ben Ng
reviews.text:
We have been taking our child to Little Seeds since last year (2023).

Over that time, the progress in his cognitive, motor & social skills has been nothing short of remarkable. I give a ton of credit to owner Bibi and the staff at Little Seeds for providing a warm, nurturing and caring environment for our kid to develop in his infant and toddler years. Bibi will provide constant updates and photos throughout the day of your child's time & activities at the daycare.

Your child will learn, be well fed and cared for while having a ton of fun in a diverse and fully equipped setting here.

reviews.author: Jessica Rodriguez
reviews.text: My daughter has been going here almost a year and a half and she will remain at this daycare until she starts school. So glad I came across Keydins family day care and I would recommend this day care to others.If I have another kid they will be coming here ! They do arts and crafts, my daughter loves it.

Kim and the team are going above and beyond to create an incredible experience for the kids. From personal and loving care, to delicious home made food, variety of learning activities, and making sure every kid is heard and loved.

reviews.author: Katelyn Gaines
reviews.text: A great loving place for all children.

reviews.author: Jianni Meyer
reviews.text:
This school is absolutely fantastic! It‚Äôs small in size, which allows the children to get wonderful care and attention. They aren‚Äôt just a daycare they‚Äôre a true preschool that focuses on learning through fun and engaging activities. The children enjoy daily park time, and they celebrate birthdays, holidays, and special occasions together. The teachers make learning exciting by incorporating songs, recycling, and so much more into the curriculum.

What really makes this place special is the balance of education, socialization, and care. The staff go above and beyond, and they even use an app to update parents and communicate throughout the day. I would highly recommend taking a tour this is hands down one of the best centers you can choose for your child‚Äôs early learning and development.

If you‚Äôre worried about your baby or toddler not speaking yet and are considering whether a nanny is enough, this preschool is likely a great solution. The teachers focus on socialization, language development, and learning through fun activities. Children are surrounded by peers, songs, stories, and daily conversations all of which encourage them to talk and grow.

reviews.author: Anusha Venkatramani
reviews.text:
SOMA has been an incredibly special place for our family and, most importantly, for our son . We joined the SOMA community after moving to San Francisco from Houston, and it was a year filled with big changes and emotions for our little one. From day one, the teachers at SOMA welcomed him with open arms, creating a warm, nurturing, and joyful environment where he could truly thrive.

The care, empathy, and intention the staff brings to each child is remarkable. The teachers took the time to understand our son as an individual‚Äîhis personality, his sensitivities, his interests‚Äîand supported him through his transitions with patience and love. Under their guidance, we saw him blossom socially, emotionally, and intellectually. He is always  full of stories about his teachers and friends.

SOMA is more than just a preschool‚Äîit's a place that values connection, creativity, and growth. We‚Äôre so grateful to the entire team for such a strong and loving foundation. While we‚Äôre sad to be leaving due to a move, SOMA will always have a very special place in our hearts.

reviews.author: Vijay Narasiman
reviews.text:
Our daughter started at SOMA when she was 2 years 10 months and is still in the school today at age 4.5. From the very first day, our experience has been absolutely wonderful! This is all thanks to the incredible efforts of teachers Ngoc, Kelly, Tiana, Geraldine, Izabella, and Chloe. Some highlights:

1. I assume other parents, like us, are nervous about the transition from home care to preschool. The teachers at SOMA made this incredibly easy. After dropping our daughter on the first day, she was so happy and really never looked back! SOMA also took care of us parents that first week, sending super frequent, individualized updates to put us at ease.
2. Our daughter LOVES going to school. It's really a testament to the environment the teachers create at SOMA. She loves the teachers and has formed such cute bonds with them. I've heard from tons of parents how dropoff can be a daily burden, but we've never experienced this!
3. The teachers do a great job sending daily updates on what the children did, along with numerous pictures and videos of the day's activities. I continue to be impressed by the creativity of the curriculum. The kids do such cool things. A quick sample off the top of my head: a unit about traveling the world, learning to run a smoothie stand business, various hands-on science experiments, yoga, dancing, etc.
4. Every 6 months, we've had a parent-teacher conference on our daughter's progress. The teachers prepare a whole slide deck just about your kid, including detailed anecdotes (with video clips!) of how your kid is learning.
5. I've never heard of families leaving SOMA because of their experience with the school. If families leave, it's always because of some other life circumstance. We have kept in touch with a few of these families, and they almost universally speak of SOMA more favorably than their new school. SOMA really is a magical place!

reviews.author: Piyush Choudhry
reviews.text:
SOMA Daycare is more than just a daycare, it's a nurturing haven! My daughter thrived in their loving environment. Teachers Kelly, Ngoc, Geradine, and Tiana showered the kids with care, and my daughter constantly woke up excited to see them.

The activities were fantastic! From weekly cooking classes and music sessions to dance, reading, and yoga, face painting there was always something engaging to spark their curiosity. SOMA even incorporated the nearby park, teaching valuable street smarts like navigating crosswalks.

We recently had to relocate, and leaving SOMA was heartbreaking. My daughter still talks about her teachers and friends! If you're searching for a daycare that prioritizes both play and learning in a warm, nurturing environment, look no further than SOMA. Absolutely recommend!

reviews.author: Chester Pidduck
reviews.text: We sent our daughter to Soma preschool and we loved the experience. The teachers are tireless, creative, kind and caring to the degree that our daughter was drawing them in cute faces and colorful drawings and was talking about them all the time. The environment is healthy and friendly. Our daughter made so many good friends there. The school is very inclusive and inviting to all different cultures and reflects this inclusivity on the kids as well. They encourage involvement of parents of any backgrounds to participate in activities and bring different cultural education to their school. We highly recommend Soma preschool.

reviews.author: Vencant Yakopian
reviews.text: We had such a wonderful experience at Twinkle Star daycare. Our daughter looked forward to going every day, and we could see how much she was learning and growing. The teachers are warm, patient, and truly care about the kids. They made such a positive impact on her, and we feel so lucky to have found a place that felt like a second home. I highly recommend Twinkle Star daycare.

reviews.author: Katia Dasari
reviews.text: I can't speak highly enough to the level of attention and care kids receive with Flora and Zhanna. It's a great place for little ones to learn and grow. Our son started at Twinkle Star when he was 9 months and we couldn‚Äôt be happier with our choice. Amazing teachers who care about him and show connection with him, always so kind and welcoming, they feel like family. They've been really careful during COVID and have gone above and beyond to keep everyone safe. Can't recommend this gem of a daycare enough!

reviews.author: Kevin Brereton
reviews.text: Twinkle Star Day Care has been an unbelievably wonderful experience for our first time using a daycare service for our son. Flora has the perfect atmosphere for children of all ages. The location is perfect and the facility itself is so warm and inviting. Our son started at around 6 months old and he has had everything he needed to grow, learn and play. Flora does a fantastic job following nap and feeding schedules and keeps us updated throughout the day with pictures, naps taken and food eaten. With the HiMama app, we can follow along all day and receive a full breakdown of the whole day. We would recommend Twinkle Star Day Care to anyone!

reviews.author: Taleen Moughamian
reviews.text: Twinkle Star Day Care was the perfect place for my son! They loved him and took care of him like he was their own. His verbal skills really took off there and I really appreciated the time they spent doing activities, music, art, reading, etc. They even helped with potty training once he was ready. Having him at Twinkle Star also really helped his transition into school. We were sad to leave but highly recommend Twinkle Star Daycare!

reviews.author: Tansy Mak
reviews.text: We feel lucky to have found Flora and her wonderful team to care for our son. They truly care for him like family and it is evident in how often he wants to stay longer after we arrive to pick him up! They provide breakfast, hot lunch, and afternoon snack, which is a lifesaver for working parents. The activities are creative and educational - we love that movement and dance is also built into the lesson plan. It is a small mixed age group, so our son has the benefit of being exposed to both younger and older children. We are also so thankful for the photos they share of the kiddos during the day, more than any other daycare we observed.

reviews.author: Elaine
reviews.text:
We have been part of this incredible daycare since our son was 5 months old, and now, as he approaches his 3rd birthday, I cannot say enough good things about Veronica and her amazing team of teachers. Their passion for teaching, creativity, and nurturing approach have created such a positive environment for the kids.

The program is thoughtfully designed to foster curiosity and growth, incorporating a variety of activities like engaging projects, storytime, yoga, music and more. It‚Äôs clear how much care and dedication goes into every aspect of their teaching. My son is so happy to go every day‚Äîhe even asks when he can go to school while we‚Äôre on vacation!

Now that we‚Äôve just welcomed our second baby, we cannot wait for her to join this wonderful daycare as well. Knowing she will be surrounded by the same warmth, care, and enriching experiences gives us so much peace of mind.

It has been such a joy to watch our son learn, grow, and thrive here, from infancy through the preschool years. The love and effort Veronica and her team put into their work truly shine through, and we feel so fortunate to be part of this amazing community.

reviews.author: cara natalia
reviews.text:
So happy to finally found a great and suitable day care for our son. Veronica, the owner of the Wonderful Children Day Care is absolutely fantastic.  When we were looking for a day care for our son, we were mainly looking for two things - a bilingual environment and a place where our son can comfortably develop himself emotionally and socially. Veronica is kind and caring towards our son and treats him like one of her own. She talks to children in three languages(English, Russian and Romanian), which makes me so happy that my child can become a bilingual as I am. The healthy, organic hot lunches that are provided make life much easier for me and for our baby. I enjoy the routine updates which we get everyday from Veronica on how my son is behaving, on nap times, what he ate, what they learn and even some photos, videos of the kids during the play, or outdoor activities.
I've always felt that her daycare center feels well organized, clean and safe. Veronica takes our son on walks with other children and small field trips.  Our baby always returns home happy and even during the weekends he asks about Veronica, which we think is a great sign.
We are very glad that we found this daycare and we completely recommend it to anyone who is focused on their children safety and well being.

reviews.author: Vikram Solanki
reviews.text: The day care have been a great place for our kid. The day care have been adding music classes, yoga, story telling and many more for development of the kid. More than the ambience and schedules for kids, teachers in this day care have been really awesome and they give personal attention to each kid. The day care gives personal attention to each kid and provides regular updates on how the kid is doing everyday. There have been new activities like gardening, guitar and piano classes introduced. Really a great environment for the kid to be in and kid love to go day care everyday.

reviews.author: Nina Ceban
reviews.text:
Veronica - the owner of Wonderful Children Day Care, is a kind and responsible person, but most important is that she loves kids and has a connection to everyone.  Her team are experienced and caring teachers, they organize a variety of extra activities like yoga, dance classes. They are serving organic and healthy food.  After a few weeks my 1.8 years old daughter started to sing English songs that they are singing during activities, but most important is that Veronica have taught her to fall asleep by herself in her own bed! During weekends she was sleeping in her own bed, that was such a relief. Our daughter is very allergic to dairy (FPIES acute to dairy) even traces of dairy could lead us to ER. We were trying to find a day care that would accept her. We were very lucky to find Veronica. She has a doctor degree and worked as a doctor in her homeland country. So everything we said about our daughter‚Äôs medical condition was familiar to her and I knew I can trust her.

We have been lucky to find Wonderful Children Day Care where our daughter had a lot of quality time and we knew she is in good hands.

reviews.author: Valentina Shchedrina
reviews.text: Our son stayed with Veronica since December 26, 2017. Initially, Veronica was his nanny, but since July 2, 2018, she became his teacher in Wonderful Children Day Care. Needless to say that Veronica loves children and makes their life comfortable and funny. She always invents something new for them, starting from food, e.g., plums stuffed with meat (I want to test it finally!) or cutlets that have ten ingredients, and finishing with gymnastics lessons with National Level Rhythmic Gymnast from Russia. Wonderful Children Day Care is very clean and very well organized. That is not surprising as Veronica was a very clean nanny for our son. I don't prepare breakfasts and lunches for our son.  He has his bed in Wonderful Children Day Care and sleeps 3-4 hours per day there. He is two years and three months old, and he counts from one to six, dances if he listens to music and singing songs with me. He also misses his nanny on weekends or after hours and repeats "nanny" very often. We taught him that "nanny sleeps" when he left his childcare. We have excellent experience with Wonderful Children Day Care and looking forward to the new achievements of our son.

reviews.author: Roan Kattouw
reviews.text: We've been sending our son to this daycare for 6 months now, and we love it! The teachers are wonderful, our son loves them (Ms Sasa and Ms Andrea in the infant room are his favorites), they communicate well with us and they do fun activities with the kids. We especially love that MB provides lunch and snacks (many other daycares we looked at don't provide food at all) and that they're very flexible about late drop-off or early pick-up.

reviews.author: Caitlin Kattouw
reviews.text: We've been sending our 15-month-old son here since he was 9 months, and we love it! We were really lucky to find such a great daycare so close to where we live, and our son loves going there. The teachers are great, they really care about the kids, they send us photo and video updates every day, and they take the kids outside to play a lot. We like that this daycare is bigger than just an in-home daycare with one teacher, but small enough that we still know all the teachers and most of the other kids and parents.

reviews.author: Johnny Dang
reviews.text:
We‚Äôve been with Meaningful Beginnings Daycare since they first opened in the basement of their home, and I can honestly say this has been one of the best decisions for our family. My first child started there years ago, and now as I toured their brand-new location for my second child, I was so impressed to see how much they‚Äôve grown while still keeping the same warm, caring environment that makes them so special.

What really stands out is their amazing staff retention. Many of the same teachers who cared for my first child are still here today. That says everything about the kind of supportive, nurturing community they‚Äôve built. The teachers truly go above and beyond for their students, not just providing excellent care but also fostering a sense of belonging and love that feels like an extension of family.

Another thing I really appreciate is the flexibility. Their drop-in options and willingness to work with families‚Äô schedules make a huge difference for busy parents. It‚Äôs rare to find a daycare that combines such professionalism, consistency, and heart.

Meaningful Beginnings isn‚Äôt just a daycare‚Äîit‚Äôs a community. I‚Äôm so grateful to have my children grow up here.

reviews.author: Nikos Sarilakis
reviews.text: We are very happy with Meaningful Beginnings on Taraval. The staff is warm, caring, and professional, and the facilities are excellent. Our son has a great time every day‚Äîhe‚Äôs learning a lot, enjoying fun activities, and getting plenty of outdoor play. The meals are good quality and well-balanced. Overall, we couldn‚Äôt be happier. Highly recommended!

reviews.author: Marie-Gabrielle Etcheparre
reviews.text: The teachers are loving and attentive. They come up with wonderful activity and art-craft ideas. Our little boy learns while having fun and socializing in a caring and protective environment.‚Äù

reviews.author: Sara Amaral
reviews.text: We love Veronica and her little school! As soon as we met, we knew this would be an amazing opportunity for our infant daughter. Veronica has cared for her like her own and is so highly regarded in our family.  She provides lunch and we provide fresh fruit and milk. The kids love it and her daughter regularly helps out after school. She is a fantastic provider, helpful with suggestions to new parents like us and a great communicator. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Maria Beltran
reviews.text: I was in need of temporary child care for my 5 year old and I could have not found a better child care professional than Veronica. She made my son feel at home and he learned so much under her care! I couldn‚Äôt be happier and I‚Äôm so thankful for her. I‚Äôve never seen my son so happy to go to day care as he was here. You can definitely tell when they do a great job taking care of your kids, Till this day my son still asks when he will be back there! If I ever needed child care ever again this day care will forever be my go to.

reviews.author: Kenzie Ansari
reviews.text: We had a wonderful experience with Little Crystal Learning Child Care! Our daughter started there at just 9 months old (in May 2024) and stayed until she was 20 months (April 2025). The caregivers were so loving, patient, and attentive throughout her time there. We saw so much growth in her ‚Äî not just in language and social skills, but also in confidence and independence. We‚Äôre so grateful for the care they provided during such an important stage of her development. Highly recommend Little Crystal Learning to any parents looking for a warm and reliable child care option!

reviews.author: Per Karlsson
reviews.text: We feel incredibly fortunate to have discovered Jialing's daycare for our daughter at the age of 1. Recommended by a coworker, this daycare has exceeded our expectations. Jialing (Crystal), who runs it, impresses us with her responsiveness and excellent communication. What's most heartwarming for us is how our daughter is not only safe but genuinely happy here. She's formed cute friendships, and it's evident that she looks forward to going every day. We highly recommend Jialing's daycare to any parents seeking a loving and enriching place for their little ones.

reviews.author: James Cheung
reviews.text:
Jialing (Crystal) has been such a great daycare provider for our daughter for over a year.  She is very organized, tech- savvy (texts photos updates etc.), and up to date on COVID precautions and safety.  Most importantly she is very caring and attentive to the children.  Our young daughter is constantly learning new skills - this includes verbal language skills (English and Mandarin), social skills with other kids, and physical skills such as navigating obstacles and learning how to dance.   She is happy there and it really shows.

The daycare environment is clean and safe, and Crystal provides nutritious food for our child.  Ultimately as parents we feel 100% at ease when our daughter is with Crystal (not an easy task for us!)

Highly recommended!

reviews.author: Aparna Kannan
reviews.text:
We are so incredibly grateful to have Crystal (Jialing) in our lives. Our daughter started going to Little Crystal Learning Child Care at 3-months-old and our experience has been impeccable. Crystal immediately put us at ease as anxious, first-time parents, and new to SF. She has nurtured our daughter and makes it her priority to ensure that all the kids feel comfortable and thrive. She provides us with the most amazing tips and recommendations to help our daughter grow and develop. Our daughter adores Crystal and her eyes light up every morning at drop off.

Crystal prides herself in ensuring the safety of each and every child, and we experienced this firsthand throughout the COVID-19 pandemic with the precautions she has put in place to help ensure the safety and health of the children.

Everyday, Crystal provides us with several photos of our daughter, provides her with delicious meals (started off with sending breast milk/formula at 3-months-old and now we‚Äôve added solids at 11-months-old!) and shares a detailed log of how much milk and solids our daughter ate, how many naps she took and for how long, and her diaper count. At the end of each day, we know what our daughter needs for the next day (diapers, wipes, change of clothes, etc.) based on her log. I‚Äôve never felt so confident about the care our daughter is in.

Her communication is impeccable, she is transparent and has an incredibly warm personality.

We have had the utmost privilege of being able to send our daughter to Crystal for the past year. She is caring, compassionate, is a true professional and provides us with the peace of mind to know our daughter is in the very best hands.

reviews.author: Jane, Ang Li
reviews.text: We started sending him when he was 3 month old. I feel so grateful to have Crystal taking care of our baby! Crystal is very details-oriented, warm and kind, the perfect character to be a daycare teacher. She send us photo everyday, send us baby daily schedules, helped baby preparing me the first mother‚Äôs day gift, etc. We are so grateful to have her and we will definitely recommend Crystal to our friends.

reviews.author: Alessandra Kortenhorst
reviews.text:
Our daughter has been attending Meaningful Beginnings since she was 7 months old, and now at 15 months, I can honestly say we couldn‚Äôt have asked for a more loving, thoughtful, and supportive environment for her. From the very beginning, the care has been warm, transparent, and deeply personal.

Her teachers (Teacher Lane and Ms. Stephanie) are absolute gems. They have nurtured our girl through every milestone, transition, and growth phase with such care and attentiveness. They‚Äôve truly felt like partners in her development and care. One moment that will stay with me forever was walking in one day to find Teacher Lane blowing raspberries on my daughter's tummy while she peeled with laughter. It‚Äôs small moments like that which make your heart overflow as a parent, knowing your child is not just cared for, but genuinely loved.

Meaningful Beginnings has been a place of trust and joy for our family. We drop our daughter off each morning with total peace of mind, knowing she‚Äôs in a safe, welcoming, and enriching space. We love receiving the daily photos and updates; seeing her exploring new activities, playing with friends, and eating the healthiest, most delicious meals (still trying to figure out how to get her to eat that well at home!). The communication is fantastic, and we‚Äôve always felt we can reach her teachers instantly if anything comes up.

We‚Äôre so grateful for everything Meaningful Beginnings has given our family. It‚Äôs more than a daycare; it‚Äôs a true community of care and connection.

reviews.author: Eric Michal
reviews.text:
We absolutely love this Meaningful Beginnings and feel incredibly lucky to have found it through a friend. Everyone is exceptionally caring, attentive, and professional, and it‚Äôs clear that this is a thoughtfully run program where children truly come first. Every time I walk through to get my son everyone knows his name. Ms. Stephanie and Teacher Lane are the best teachers‚Äîso warm, patient, and genuinely invested in each child. Our child feels safe, supported, and excited to go every day, which means everything to us as parents.

Ms. Alma, the facility coordinator, is always welcoming and in addition to doing a great job with the food prep our son loves to reach out to her for a hug.

The facility is clean, safe, and well maintained, with a great balance of learning, structure, and play. This daycare is incredibly well run and full of people who truly care. We recommend it without hesitation to any family looking for a nurturing, high-quality childcare environment.

reviews.author: Jessica Fijolek
reviews.text: We sent both of our sons to this daycare. Our older son started at age 2 in their preschool after transferring from their location on Taraval and our younger son started in their infant room at 4 months old. We‚Äôve had a phenomenal experience with this center. Our older son just graduated and started TK and is already writing and reading short words at 4 years old. He‚Äôs also an empathetic leader in his new classroom thanks to the lessons he learned at daycare. We love the teachers, the hours, the lesson plans, the routine, the school-provided meals, and the extracurriculars they offer like holiday parades, parent meet ups, and lectures. Executive Director Ms. Luisa and her team are terrific parenting partners and have helped us with sleep issues, weaning, and behavioral challenges that have popped up in the early years. We also love the daily photos and updates we get from their app. Highly recommend this daycare.

reviews.author: Olivia Parker
reviews.text:
Our experience with Meaningful Beginnings has been such a positive one. Going back to work and leaving our son at daycare was stressful, especially at such a young age (3 months old).
Ms. Stephanie and Teacher Lane have been so wonderful and supportive. When our son was struggling to nap in the new space, they made adjustments, like moving his crib and changing his position, to see what would work for him. He is now napping longer stretches. We have also started talking about upping his milk per feeding since they‚Äôve been noticing that he still seems hungry after finishing his bottles. It‚Äôs comforting to know that his individual needs are being attended to and discussed. It‚Äôs also sweet to pass him off to caretakers who are genuinely happy to see him in the morning. The teacher aides all know his name and handle him with love and care too.
The regular updates are wonderful. When I miss him, I can look at photos of him that they‚Äôve taken that day. I can also gauge when to pick him up based on his nap/eating schedule.
I have such peace of mind leaving our son at daycare. It‚Äôs lovely to know that he is well taken care of when we go to work!

reviews.author: Ashley Heermann
reviews.text: The whole team at Meaningful Beginnings is on top of it! We are continuously impressed by the dedication to development, engagement, and safety, led by Luisa & Carmen. Our kids love all their teachers, including Ms. Kristana, Emily, Bianca, Mallie, Achala, and Sofia, who show great warmth and care for them. Alma & Sheville are also rock stars at keeping the facilities clean and inviting. We're lucky to have found MB!

reviews.author: Alexander Kazberouk
reviews.text: We sent our son to Magic Kingdom of learning from 3 to 8 months. He received excellent care and love from Nelya, Masha, and the other staff here. They are experienced, knowledgeable, and know what to do with infants, toddlers, and beyond. Really appreciate their care but also their teaching and advice for us as new parents. Nothing but positive things to say about this daycare program - we ended up switching daycares due to proximity to work.

reviews.author: Hazel Bay
reviews.text: My daughter goes here. I am very happy with Nelly and her staff. My daughter picked up on her ABC's. Nelly's staff really focus on educating the children. She really understands on work with people's financial budget. I am very happy that I got referral from a friend to her. I highly recommend this child care.

reviews.author: Sanjana magee
reviews.text:
Our son has been going to Magic Kingdom for 1.5 years, and it has been a wonderful experience for him. The women who run the daycare are excellent caregivers. They genuinely care about the children, and have given invaluable support to our toddler. He looks forward to going to daycare every day, and regularly asks to see his teachers on the weekend.

From an educational perspective, they offer preschool curriculum and music classes, both lead by teachers who come in 1-2 times per week, respectively. Our 2 year old has learned numbers and his ABCs, and has developed a love of music and singing as result. It's been an extremely beneficial experience for him. Some other callouts:

- Russian language exposure
- Breakfast, lunch, and snacks included
- Safe and secure outdoor time in their backyard

I can't emphasize enough how much we've loved going here. Any family would be lucky to enroll their children here.

reviews.author: Alaina Jones
reviews.text: We love Magic Kingdom. Our daughter is excited to go everyday. Ms. Nelly and Ms. Masha are wonderful, caring teachers who love every kid. The smaller, in-home daycare means extra attention for our daughter and less chance of sickness that naturally comes from any daycare. Bonus: The food provided is delicious.

reviews.author: curt crawford
reviews.text: We absolutely love Magic Kingdom of Learning! We‚Äôve been sending our son there since he was nine months old and he‚Äôs always so happy to see everyone. Nellya, Ira, and everyone else are so sweet and attentive and it‚Äôs obvious how much they love the kids there. We highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Linda
reviews.text: What an amazing childcare! Our daughters have grown up from Garden Daycare and Three Bears Childcare and we were thrilled to hear about their expansion! Of course when our youngest came to Little Treasures I knew they‚Äôd be in good hands. Bonus: they share pictures and videos throughout the day so I not only know my child is happy, but I get to see what they‚Äôre working on everyday - still blows my mind to see all the kids sitting for story time and/or doing their own hands on art activities! Olga is incredibly sweet, attentive and caring with just the right amount of firmness in her rules/structure - my kids adore her! I also love that they have themed lessons (similar to Reggio Emelia pedagogy) that are planned out for every month. Our daughters thrived on that and picked up colors, shapes and the alphabet so quickly because of it! We highly recommend Little Treasures and our youngest can‚Äôt wait to go back!

reviews.author: Eleanor Hicks
reviews.text: Nya, the owner of Tiny Steps, used to work at my child's daycare, and I sent my daughter to Tiny Steps for a few weeks when my daughter's daycare was closed. Nya has a wonderful way with young children, is a knowledgable provider and cares deeply about the well-being of the children in her charge. "Nya" was one of my daughter's first words. Over the past two years, Nya has become like a member of her family. She is the only person outside of family who has babysat for my daughter.

reviews.author: Deirdre Lewis
reviews.text: Nya the owner care provider is wonderful with children. She is warm, attentive, and genuinely cares about the children. The environment is clean, safe, and welcoming, with fun activities that keep the kids engaged and learning every day. We highly recommend this daycare to any family looking for a nurturing and trustworthy place for their child.

reviews.author: Eugeniya Wells
reviews.text: Nya, the owner of Tiny Steps Day Care, has been wonderful for our baby. We‚Äôve sent him there since he was six months old and a little nervous as first time parents. Nya is the best thing that could have happened to him and us. She regularly communicates updates with us, even outside hours, and does all sorts of little things that add up, like trying out different types of sippy cups, always sending him home in a clean outfit and washing the dirty ones on site, sending him home with his footprints on a Halloween decoration that we have hung up, and making homemade food to feed him. He gets excited whenever he sees Nya, and he‚Äôs inseparable from his fellow day care friends, so we know we‚Äôve made a good choice. Nya is now the only person outside of our immediate family that we can trust implicitly with our little guy. We feel lucky everyday to have found Nya and Tiny Steps Day Care!

reviews.author: Laura Rosow
reviews.text: We have adored C5 for our children. The teachers are all so kind and patient, and they quickly felt like an extension of our family. I love the school‚Äôs emphasis on child-led play and exploration. Kids are encouraged to get creative and have good, messy fun ‚Äî as they should! Our children blossomed here, and our oldest was very well prepared for kindergarten when he graduated. They have a nice website with daily updates and loads of pictures. Oh, and I love that  food is included!

reviews.author: Min P
reviews.text: We love C5! Both of my kids attended the school and we've been there for more than four years. What we like best about C5 is the teachers. They are truly wonderful and care about the children. The school's focus on professional development ensures the teachers are current on the latest trends in education, plus we've experienced very little teacher turnover. We've had many of the same teachers over the years and of course some great new ones! During our time there, we've gotten to know many families who have been there for as long as we have if not longer, an awesome community.

reviews.author: Jason Holzheimer
reviews.text: Our family's experience at C5 has been fantastic. Our daughter started at 9 months and is now going on 14 months. We were looking for an environment focused on what's best for students (as opposed to parents and staff) and we found it. We feel very fortunate: no complaints and lots of highlights. The staff is energetic but calm, knowledgable but down-to-Earth. It's also been great to get to know the other parents.

reviews.author: Orchid Bertelsen
reviews.text:
We could not be happier with C5. Our daughter loves her teacher, Mitch, who moved classrooms with her as she graduated from baby to toddler. They also provide meals and snacks that are nutrious and provide great variety.

Quinn always has a smile on her face when I drop and pick her up. You really can't ask for more.

reviews.author: Nicole Gorton
reviews.text: This school has been amazing. The staff is so nurturing and kind. They support the family inside and outside of the program. This school has been a lifesaver for a single mother like myself.

reviews.author: Nancy Aguilar
reviews.text:
I went to tour the school, the school is really nice, classrooms spacious and the yard is great. My child is very attached to me and didnt want to be there for the tour. The director Setareh was very business like my child was "$" in her eyes, seemed that way to me and saw how attracted he was and decided my child would be better off in another pre school, because he wouldnt be an easy toddler to drop off so just doesnt want to deal with it( that was discussed during email hours later) . After the tour i definitely knew i didnt want to enroll my child there. I also met Francisco, he was a very nice person and holy family is lucky to have him. It was just too business like in my opinion for a preschool, you want a child to feel welcomed and not just see them as "$". I wouldnt recommend any of my family or friends for a tour there.
Thankfully we found a school that i actually toured before holy family and that is where my child will be going, they saw him just like holy family did, very attached to me and they were very caring towards him even during the tour.

reviews.author: C C
reviews.text: This school is a hidden rare gem!! It is a model for how each school should be. My child had the wonderful opportunity to attend this preschool and she remembers and misses it to this day (she's 9 now).The staff are amazing! I mean from the moment you walk in the doors; the receptionist, the teachers, even the  directors are all so supportive, kind, compassionate, caring and most importantly they are truly sincere. It is just the type of place you feel confident leaving your children in a very safe security gated environment where not just any sicko can walk in or linger around the premises. They have a very good system set up to make sure your children are safe. Don't get me wrong  I don't mean to make it appear as a prison I'm just highlighting that safety is one that is taken seriously, which I highly appreciate especially since many schools don't go the extra mile. Most of the time I see other schools with gates wide open at all times and anyone can come on to the property and youd never know. HFDH is a private school and worth every penny, definitely money well invested for your child to have quality education and a positive nurturing and memorable experience. I could go on and on about so many other great reasons and so many other supportive services etc so instead I suggest you take a tour and see for yourself!

reviews.author: Lucas Crittendon
reviews.text: New director and assistant director are shady and terrible, they care more about money and publicity for the school then they do for the actual kids. Cross contamination by admin, no regard for regulations or procedures, school has bugs and grime everywhere. They recently had an outbreak of COVID-19 in their kitchen and cleaning staff and lied, telling parents and staff it was in the maintenance crew or that they hadn't even been back to work yet. Director and assistant director cut many corners with no care for the health or safety of the children in their care, just whats easiest and quicker for themselves. 3 licensing violations since January, yet they continue to intimidate staff into silence in fear of their jobs and sweep everything under the rug. With over a hundred years of an amazing and honorable reputation, HFDH has gone downhill drastically. You would be better off sending your children literally anywhere but here.

reviews.author: Hope de Groot
reviews.text: I'm 46 yrs old and I went to Holy Family when I was little and all I have are fond childhood memories of this place. I made my very first best friend here, went to St. Anthony's together and to this day we are still friends as well as with many others. Holy Family really made a positive impact in my life and I am truly greatful.

reviews.author: Nicholas Gonzalez
reviews.text: This is an amazing institution that's been around for over 100 years. I went here for preschool, now my daughter is attending! I highly recommend HFDH...but make sure to get on the waitlist!!!

reviews.author: Lindsay Vargo
reviews.text: We have been lucky enough to be a part of the Tiny Giants preschool system for the last seven years. Our daughter started at the Tiny Giants Infant Center when she was three months old and graduated from their preschool Pre-K program last year. Our son is currently in their 3s+ program.  Tiny Giants has an incredibly curious and empathetic setting - and as a result, we see these traits in both our children. The teachers are incredible, and we couldn't have asked for a more caring set of individuals to care for and teach our kiddos. My husband and I moved to Marin County in 2020 and have remained at the school (we work in the city) because it's one of the best in the area. We did explore other options, but nothing compared. The sense of community and support is second to none, which I don't think you get in every preschool. We are grateful to be a part of the Tiny Giants community.

reviews.author: Mason Nelson
reviews.text:
We have been a Tiny Giants family for 3+ years and it has truly changed our lives. I have never experienced such a place of love, inclusivity, consistency and happiness. The teachers are beyond amazing, knowledgeable, so loving and creative.

The families epitomize teamwork, looking out for one another and organizing so many things out of the classroom. This is very RARE.

With the hands on care, our child is thriving in this environment. There is both structure, but also flexibility for the children to spend time learning how they need to learn. The teachers are incredibly proactive in their feedback to us, treating our child as if he's their own.

I could go on and on - bottom line, I cannot fathom not having this preschool in our lives and we are forever grateful for everything Tiny Giants has contributed to our family. We could never thank them enough.

reviews.author: Kevin Farrelly
reviews.text: Tiny Giants is more than just a preschool‚Äîit's a true family. The head of the school, along with her dedicated team of teachers, creates an environment where every child is cherished and nurtured as if they were their own. The warmth and care that they bring into the classroom make Tiny Giants a place where children feel safe, valued, and loved. It‚Äôs comforting to know that my kids are not only receiving an excellent education but are also being guided by individuals who genuinely care about their well-being and development. Tiny Giants is a community where each child is recognized for their unique strengths, and where families can feel confident that their little ones are in the best hands.

reviews.author: William K Downey III
reviews.text: Our son absolutely loves TG.  Teachers are great (they‚Äôve become our go to babysitters as well!), the facility is awesome with the playground and outdoor space, and he‚Äôs growing into a kind, caring, and smart kiddo from his time there!

reviews.author: Catharine Prodromou
reviews.text: 5 stars for Tiny Giants. We‚Äôve sent all three of our kids (the last graduating in 2024). The three most rewarding features of this preschool program, for us have been: 1) the thoughtful and engaging curriculum, 2) the active parent/family community, and 3) the convenience of location and hours. The folks at TG know kids and love kids, and the environment they foster is truly exceptional. I‚Äôm an elementary school teacher at an independent school in San Francisco, so I take this very seriously! The TK program is an added bonus. Our kids entered Kindergarten with readiness (both academic and social), with confidence to boot!

reviews.author: Salome Heusel
reviews.text: Our little girl attended Sandmann from when she was 20 months to 3 years old and we are so sad to be moving on since she will now start preschool. We can't say enough great things about Sandmann, we truly believe it is the best daycare in SF. The owners and caretakers create such a warm and loving environment. The child/teacher ratio is wonderful and ensures all the kids' needs are well taken care of. The days are filled with lots of fun and creative activities: music, arts & crafts, trips to the library and story time, plenty of outdoor play in the garden and nearby playground. Our daughter looked forward to going every morning and would come home beaming from the day's adventures. We very much appreciated the healthy food choices for the daily hot lunch and snacks provided. The staff was always supportive and communicative in all of our little girl's milestones such as nap transitions and potty training. We have seen our daughter grow and thrive socially in no small part thanks to the wonderful team at Sandmann. For two working parents it was such a relief to find a daycare that we knew our daughter loved going to and where she was so well taken care of. We are very grateful for the wonderful experience our daughter had at Sandmann and highly recommend it to other parents in SF.

reviews.author: Ivana Markovic
reviews.text:
Our daughter has been in Sandmann for a year, and we have absolutely loved every single day. She goes to school and cannot wait to wave to me from the window so she can go and play with her friends.

For us, it was important that she is a safe and loving environment, and that is is outdoors as much as possible. Sandmann team takes out the kids to the local park each morning, and they are outdoors for about 2 hours, running and playing. In the afternoons they spend time in the garden. In the mean time, they eat yummy healthy food and snacks, and enjoy singing songs, reading books, doing art projects and playing with other kids. Once a week they visit the local library, and will even do a local outing occasionally.

While we are not German speakers ourselves, we love that our daughter is exposed to another language and culture.

The owners of the daycare are warm and loving people, and they truly care about each kid. They are easy to communicate with, and I feel my daughter is in great hands when I leave her in their care. I would highly recommend Sandmann!

reviews.author: Lucia Devid√®
reviews.text: Our daughter attended Sandmann transitioning from nanny to Day Care at 18 months. She loved it! She looked forward to going every morning and she made a lot of friends there. Owners and caretakers create a loving environment, plenty of indoor and outdoor activities, and very healthy food choices. We left the daycare only because we had to relocate. We truly recommend Sandmann!

reviews.author: Brian Whitlow
reviews.text:
When our daughter turned 18 months old, we were looking for a neighborhood daycare to provide local care, and after visiting a few other daycare providers, we fell in love with Sandmann Family Day Care. Upon our initial visit, we were impressed with the use of space, which was clean and professional, and also had the ‚Äúfeel‚Äù we were looking for: warmth, care, joy and full of arts and crafts activities.  When we came back to fill out paperwork, we brought our daughter and we immediately knew we had made the right decision based on the ease and comfort with which she interacted with the owners as well as the owner‚Äôs young children. Literally, she felt at home.

Throughout the time our daughter was at Sandmann, she grew as a more independent person and her language skills (in both English and German) improved greatly. She would teach us songs she learned at Sandmann, and we credit Sandmann with her independence -- from being able to take off and put on her own shoes, to feeding herself food.  When away from Sandmann, she often spoke of the other students and teachers with excitement and enthusiasm. She looked forward to returning to Sandmann every Monday morning, and one of the best feelings as a parent is to confidently know you are dropping off and picking up a happy child.

As parents, we were thrilled with the ease of communication via emails and texts. We always felt well informed, and upon pick up it was easy to see via the notice board what our daughter ate and drank during the day, as well as her routine and sleep breaks. We could not have been happier with our time spent at Sandmann and give it the highest recommendation! Sandmann provided our daughter with social, emotional and academic tools that have been priceless for her foundational years.

reviews.author: Carina Purer
reviews.text: As a college student, I worked part-time at Sandmann Daycare and had such an amazing experience being one of the teachers there. I taught German to the toddlers and enjoyed working at this daycare tremendously. Sandmann works hard to give each child individual attention and makes them feel at home. It was so nice going into work each day because of how happy the children were even when they had to say goodbye to their mommies and daddies each morning. The daycare always had a plan each day and we often did field trips to parks, libraries, and such to allow the kids to experience something new everyday. I highly recommend this daycare to any parents looking for one in San Francisco, and your child is in an environment where both English and German are being taught!

reviews.author: Caroline Cochran
reviews.text:

DiDiDa Academy is truly a gem in our community! My son attended this preschool from just 9 months old until he started public school, and I can honestly say it has been one of the best decisions we‚Äôve made as parents.

Ada creates a warm, loving, and organized environment. Each child is treated like family, and you can really see how much Ada & the teachers genuinely care about the kids‚Äô overall development‚Äîboth emotionally and physically. The attention they give to each child‚Äôs individual needs is remarkable! We also appreciated the attention to the curriculum and sheer variety of science-based and arts activities that were apart of each week‚Äôs theme ‚Äî not to mention our son getting a chance to learn Mandarin!

One of the highlights of DiDiDa is their commitment to providing delicious, fresh food daily. It‚Äôs such a relief to know that my son was not only eating well but also being introduced to a variety of healthy foods. He often came home raving about the meals!

Another fantastic benefit that we took advantage of was their romantic dinner nights and weekend extra care days. These perks allowed us to enjoy some quality time together as parents while knowing our child was having a blast in a safe, familiar environment.

I loved the sense of community I've found at DiDiDa. Parents bond over our shared experiences, and the connections we‚Äôve built feel like lifelong friendships. The kids grow up together and truly become a family, making it easy to feel supported in this parenting journey.

What I loved most was our son showing how happy he was each day by being excited to go and then gabbing about what happened and how much he loves his friends each day after school. Your child enjoying the experience is the most important.

As a first-time parent, it can be overwhelming at times, but DiDiDa Academy was a blessing for us. We always felt our son was safe, cared for genuinely, and nurtured in the best possible way.

We only left DiDiDa because of my son getting too old, but I‚Äôll forever cherish the memories and experiences we had. If you‚Äôre looking for a nurturing, supportive, and fun preschool, I highly recommend DiDiDa Academy!

reviews.author: Mike Marg
reviews.text: Di Di Da Daycare has been an absolute blessing for our family . We currently have two children enrolled. From the moment we walked through their doors, we felt a sense of warmth, professionalism, and genuine care that immediately put our minds at ease.The staff at Di Di Da are truly exceptional. They are not only highly qualified and experienced but also incredibly loving and attentive to each child's individual needs. Our child always comes home happy, often excitedly recounting the fun activities and learning experiences they had throughout the day. It's clear that the educators foster a stimulating and engaging environment where children can thrive developmentally, socially, and emotionally.The facilities are clean, well-maintained, and thoughtfully designed with various age-appropriate zones for play, learning, and rest. We particularly appreciate their focus on healthy snacks and meals, as well as their commitment to outdoor play and exploration.Communication with parents is excellent. We receive regular updates on our child's progress, daily activities, and any important information. They are always approachable and ready to discuss any concerns or answer questions, which builds a strong sense of trust.Choosing a daycare is a significant decision, and we are incredibly grateful to have found Di Di Da Daycare. They provide a safe, nurturing, and enriching environment that feels like an extension of our home. We wholeheartedly recommend Di Di Da Daycare to any parent looking for high-quality childcare.

reviews.author: Diane Wu
reviews.text:
It took me a month to write this review because it was so hard to find the right words to properly convey just how amazing DiDiDa Academy is for my son.
My son started at 8mo and is now over 1.5yrs old. He was never a good sleeper until Ada (owner) took the time to assess his feeding and sleep schedule and developed a plan for his Daycare routine that we then mirrored at home. She's a miracle worker because he sleeps and eats SO much better at daycare compared to at home, and then he started sleeping better and eating better at home overtime as well.

The children at the daycare are all so loving and kind. They play together so well and I truly feel my son's emotional, physical, and mental development is advanced because of how well Ada plans her meals, the activities, and the program each week. Her meals are home cooked and they even grow fresh produce in the backyard to teach them about where food comes from and to also eat! My son loves to eat bok choy because of that!

Ada also sends updates with videos and photos of my son, and that's literally the highlight of my day.

I trust Ada and all the teachers at this Daycare and know that my son is well taken care of. I know this because my son asks for Ada and her husband Johnathan almost everyday and his face lights up when he sees them.

She's done so much to support me as a first time mom, teaching me how to properly sleep train, how to prepare nutritional food for baby led weaning, and how to enforce good habits into my son. Ada is a rare gem in the daycare world.

reviews.author: Yet Ly
reviews.text:
UPDATE: Our daughter has been with Ada for a year now, and we couldn‚Äôt be happier.  As our baby transitioned into an energetic toddler, we have continued to see her growth with Ada‚Äôs help.  Ada continues to provide daily enrichment activities such as story-time, outdoor play time, library time, arts and crafts, etc.  In addition to that, she goes the extra mile to throw fun holiday events for the families to gather and enjoy as a group with all the parents. Because Ada provides instruction in Mandarin, our daughter is even able to understand and speak Mandarin now even though we don‚Äôt speak that language at home.

Our daughter is always happy to go to daycare, where she also learns singing, counting, letters, feelings, and manners. She eats healthy and balanced meals because Ada really puts thought into her monthly menus. We get to see pictures and videos throughout the day so that we know our child is okay. Ada is caring, knowledgeable, and highly skilled with children. Recently our daughter was giving us a hard time with teeth brushing, but Ada was able to encourage her to do so without any issues. She is a miracle worker!  Ada is not just a daycare provider, she is a true teacher, and we are all grateful for her!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

We've had great experiences at this daycare ever since we started a couple of months ago. Ada provides lots of enrichment activities for our little one, including story time, Mandarin lessons, artwork, library visits, outdoor play, etc. She is also good at helping our baby take naps, which is not easy! Our daughter seems very happy every time she goes to DiDiDa Daycare.  Ada is engaging with the children, keeps us informed with daily activity logs, and is very responsive as well.  I was very nervous about starting a new daycare for our daughter, but Ada helped make the transition easier, which was a definite relief. We truly appreciate all of her hard work and quality care. Highly recommended!

reviews.author: Yvonne Yi
reviews.text: We can't say enough about Ada and her staff. This is the third daycare our son started attending at just under the age of 2 due to a few moves, and it's hands down the best one we've found. Both the staff and kids welcomed him so warmly, and he became quickly attached & picked up Mandarin within a matter of weeks. It's been 1.5 years since he joined and we've watched him grow from a reserved, nervous kid to a confident, curious, social butterfly thanks to DiDiDa's nurturing care. Ada meticulously plans out a curriculum for her students with a different theme each month, and she and her staff provide updates via photos/videos and daily chats during drop-off or pick-up. Our 19 mo old daughter joined DiDiDa a few months ago and she's just as obsessed. We feel lucky to have both kids under Ada's watch as she truly cares for her students as if they're her own.

reviews.author: maryellen
reviews.text: Our baby has been with Liz and Jonathan since he was 2 months old. He‚Äôs 20 months now and attends full-time. The best things about this couple‚Äôs daycare is that they treat our child as their own, are very loving and kind, teach him all the behaviors and skills he  should know at each age, like eating with a fork and spoon, talking, safety, and even potty training. My husband and I have every confidence that our child is safe and happy during the day. We highly recommend Sunshine & Smiles!

reviews.author: Brittany Estrada
reviews.text:
Lizeth and Jonathan, thank you so much for taking care of our little one. You've been wonderful.  Our little one has definitely been in very good hands. Highly recommended. Thank you.üòäüíñ
We are very happy and grateful to you

reviews.author: Jos√© Camargo
reviews.text: Lizet from Sunshine & Smiles used to be my nanny for my now 4YO daughter. She's very loving, caring, and dedicated with everything she does with the little ones. I highly recommend her, since her values & guidelines are still reflected on my daughter's actions. Best of luck on this new journey, Liz!

reviews.author: sheetal patel mehta
reviews.text: My 4 year old daughter had the best time with Liz at Sunshine and smiles daycare. She was loving, attentive and made her do alot of art and craft which my daughter thoroughly enjoys. I highly recommend the place !

reviews.author: brenda luz
reviews.text: I love sunshine & Smiles  Daycare, liz is very loving and creative, my little boy was always very happy with her

reviews.author: Cliff Kuehn
reviews.text: Our son attended from 9 months to 3 years, and we could not have dreamed of a more loving place. The aunties cared for him like family ‚Äî from incredibly detailed daily updates in the infant years to engaging, brain-boosting activities and tons of outdoor play as he grew. We‚Äôll truly miss the sweet birthday celebrations, the adorable art projects, and the fun little snacks and foods they‚Äôd send home, in addition to the daily pic/video updates we‚Äôd receive via app and email He picked up a surprising amount of Mandarin along the way, and we‚Äôre confident he‚Äôll keep building on it. We‚Äôre endlessly grateful for the care, love, and support they gave both our son and us.

reviews.author: Graham Bellefeuille
reviews.text: Our daughter has been attending Angela's since she was 6 months old (she will be 2 years old next week.) She started in the G1 class and moved up to the G2 class (there is also a G3 class, but the size is small and most families move on to preschool rather than G3.) She loves her Aunties (especially Auntie May) and Angela's sends so many pictures and videos of her throughout the day playing. They go to the Academy of Sciences regularly, and take field trips to Golden Gate Park weekly. They also have a weekly music class, which our daughter loves. Overall I highly recommend Angela's Childcare Center. The only issue we have run into is the language barrier, since neither my wife nor I speak Mandarin, so direct communication can be a bit awkward. But really that's a minor issue and Vicky is generally responsive when we communicate via email.

reviews.author: judea contreras
reviews.text: Love this center! My daughter has been coming here since November.

reviews.author: Leticia RD
reviews.text:
I cannot express how grateful I am to all the staff at Angela‚Äôs Child Care Center for everything they have done for our family. My eldest daughter attended from 18 months until she was two years old, when she transitioned to preschool. My youngest son started at ACC when he was just 5 months old and stayed until he was two and a half; he also recently started preschool.

As an educator with nearly 20 years of experience teaching in elementary school and providing professional development for other educators, I can confidently say that the staff at ACC are knowledgeable, intentional, and thoughtful in the care they provide. The level of dedication and expertise they bring to their work is truly remarkable.

We received regular updates through the Kaymbu app, often weekly and sometimes even daily. These updates included pictures of our child engaged in various learning experiences, which was always a joy to see. The communication and transparency offered by the staff gave us peace of mind, knowing our children were in such good hands.

When it was time for my son to leave ACC, they organized a heartwarming ‚Äúgraduation‚Äù ceremony, wishing him luck in preschool. They also provided us with a thick portfolio filled with his work, pictures, and thoughtful notes about his development and learning journey. It was a beautiful keepsake that we'll treasure forever.

Both of my children transitioned easily to preschool, and I‚Äôm certain it‚Äôs because of the confidence and autonomy nurtured at ACC. I cannot imagine trusting my children's care to any other place. The warmth, care, and professionalism at ACC have left a lasting impact on our family. We are forever grateful and will continue to stop by so my child can give hugs to his ‚Äúaunties.‚Äù
