reviews.author: yan huang
reviews.text: Little Learners Daycare is really clean, the teachers are very nice and patient. My child has been here for three months, and I am really happy to have met such a good teacher.

reviews.author: Teresa Beatriz Segura Acereto
reviews.text: If I could give it ten stars, I would. It's a daycare where my son is happy. The teacher is an excellent person and very well-trained in caring for children. I feel completely confident leaving my son and going to work. I recommend it 100 percent.

reviews.author: Mily Ayra casta√±eda
reviews.text: We are so grateful for the love and care you give our little one every day. You are a blessing to our family. Thank you for creating such a warm and nurturing environment for our son. Thank you so much, TEACHER‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.author: Marzena Kruszy
reviews.text:
My family loves The Growing Tree. All the teachers are so caring and dedicated. They are always smiling and positive. My son Thomas is a preschooler now but he started attending at 14 months old and he loved all the teachers at every stage, including his current teacher Jessie. My daughter is 15 months and also loves her teacher Joey. They both go to school happily every day.

The Growing Tree has a nice big playground on one side and a garden on the other, all fenced in and safe. The kids get fresh air every day and learn how to care for plants which I love.

I also really appreciate teacher Eva. She is always there to answer any questions and help with any problem. You can tell she really cares about the kids, the parents and the staff!

reviews.author: Sandra Truong
reviews.text:
Our son has been attending Growing Tree Preschool for almost a year now, and we‚Äôre so grateful for the growth we‚Äôve seen in him during this time. He started in the younger class, where he quickly became attached to Teacher Winnie. The transition to the next class was hard on him at first, but with the support of the teachers and the kindness of Teacher Jessie, he adjusted well and is now thriving.
We‚Äôve seen such a big change in how he feels about going to school. He used to run away when we pulled up to the building and now he runs into school with a smile on his face. It‚Äôs clear that all the teachers truly care about the students and create a warm, loving environment.
Even though we don‚Äôt speak Mandarin at home, it‚Äôs been so encouraging to hear him sing songs in Mandarin.  I love how much he‚Äôs learning through everyday play and activities.
We also really appreciate how proactive the school is when it comes to health and safety. Knowing that our son is well cared for both emotionally and physically gives us a lot of peace of mind.
The app the school uses has also been a great tool for us as parents. We love seeing the daily photo updates, and the ability to notify teachers at pickup time makes the whole process smooth and efficient.
Thank you to everyone at Growing Tree for the love and care you show each and every day!

reviews.author: Ashley Hongisto
reviews.text: My 3.5 year old and 1 year old have both been going to Growing Tree since they were 5 months old. We have been very happy there. My children have liked all their teachers and I feel like they have all been caring and supportive. They have a lot of different age appropriate activities for the kids, and we get occasional photo updates about what they‚Äôre up to in an app. There is a nice outside play area, so the kids get to play outside daily, which is important to me. I‚Äôm also very proud of my daughter, who thanks to the bilingual nature of the school, knows many Chinese words and songs and is already loving the language.

reviews.author: Ling Li
reviews.text:
We've been incredibly happy with Growing Tree. Our son‚Äîwho‚Äôs been going for nearly two years‚Äîcan‚Äôt wait to head off to school each morning. He absolutely loves his teachers and friends, and the staff are genuinely caring and consistent.
I especially look forward to the photo updates, showcasing everything from science experiments and gardening to art. It‚Äôs such a clear window into his joyful learning.
The bilingual environment is thoughtfully designed‚Äîsmall class sizes, bright spaces, and a warm, enriching atmosphere. It truly feels like a second home.
I can‚Äôt wait for my daughter to enroll next!

reviews.author: Michelle Hammel
reviews.text:
We love Growing Tree. Our son has been in their care for 3 years now. Our youngest will start at Growing Tree soon too! They have excellent teachers, a thoughtful enriching curriculum, and a large facility. I love getting photo updates of my son‚Äôs daily activities such as science experiments, gardening, collaborative art projects, cultural celebrations, special guests and so much more. My son loves his friends, and the parent community coordinates group playdates on the weekends too. As an educator myself, I‚Äôm particularly impressed with their teacher retention, and the positive energy their staff maintains from drop off until pickup. It‚Äôs comforting that my son sees so many familiar faces and loving adults each day- his very first teacher from when he was 5 months old, is still there to greet him in the morning, as well as most of
the other lovely teachers he‚Äôs had along the way.

name: Creative Gardens Preschool and Daycare Center

reviews.author: Victoria Li
reviews.text: Teachers here are very sociable and friendly. Kids are also nice with my kids, lots of toys and books for kids to read and play with. Big playground for running and exercise too. Love this preschool!

reviews.author: Eric Solomonson
reviews.text: Every morning our daughter is excited to go to Semillitas and spend her day with Monica and Vilma. They do such an incredible job of emphasizing play, creative expression, learning, and relationship building. Monica and Vilma meet kids where they are at, see and treat them as whole people, and show so much love and care. They provide nutritious snacks and meals, help with potty training, and really care about what's going on at home as well. It also feels like all of us Semillitas families are part of a community -- holiday celebrations and birthday picnics have been such a great way to get to know everyone better. After three great years for our oldest, we'll be sending our youngest here as well and couldn't be happier about.

reviews.author: Dara Carroll
reviews.text: What a BLESSING! Monica is a thoughtful, informed educator. She and her team, including Vilma, have expertly supported our daughter's development from age 6 months through over 3 years. Monica understands what kids need at different stages and effectively creates a joyful learning and growing environment for her multi-age group. She and Vilma also helped build a sense of community among the families and now I can genuinely say we feel part of a bigger family - the Semillitas family.

reviews.author: Laryssa Temnycky
reviews.text: We were fortunate enough to find Semillitas when our daughter was a year old. Monica, Wilma and Rosa have built an incredible community amongst the families (both past and present) with ongoing picnics and get togethers. The environment at the daycare is calm and clean with tons of books and toys. On top of that, they take the kids to different parks (or libraries pending weather) every day.  Our daughter always comes home with a new piece of art or a craft, song or skill. The teachers are great at sending videos, updates and photos during the day so you feel connected.  Our daughter is always smiling when she arrives and when we pick her up. If you can get a spot here, don‚Äôt hesitate.

reviews.author: Yosi Garcia
reviews.text: We started our son with Semillitas Daycare when he was 18-19 months and we had an amazing experience. Miss Monica and Miss Vilma are the most loving, warm and caring people on earth. My son absolutely loves them. He had really bad separation anxiety and they helped him with a smooth transition and I cannot be more thankful for that. They were super good with all the updates through the day and pictures. This helped put our minds at ease. We are very thankful that our son was at Semillitas daycare. I can totally recommend it to any SF families!

reviews.author: Willy Lavadores
reviews.text:
Our son attends Semillitas daycare and absolutely loves it! Monica is warm and attentive and sends us pictures and updates throughout the day.
Our son is immediately smiling and clapping when we pull up to Las Semillitas. It is difficult to leave your little one in the care of others but we feel so comfortable with Monica and Vilma. Knowing he is playing with his peers in the park or making art with his buddies makes us so happy.
When we pick him up in the afternoon, it is clear he‚Äôs had a great time and he even blows kisses on the way out!

reviews.author: Zach & Micaela
reviews.text: We can't say enough positive about Bluebell Kids and Olga. She's an amazing provider, they have a wonderful space with indoor and outdoor play areas, do outings and activities, and delicious food (that our son requests when he's home!). Our son has been there since he was 8 month old baby and is now a busy toddler -- and has had great care through all those phases.

reviews.author: Melissa Kolod
reviews.text: We‚Äôve had such a wonderful experience here! It‚Äôs a small, loving daycare that feels like the best of both worlds, the personal attention of a nanny with the social benefits of a few kids to play with. Olga provides healthy home-cooked meals and takes the kids on fun outings, such as the library for music time, the Presidio, and even the beach! We feel so lucky to have found this spot!

reviews.author: Dana Nikolaeva Chambourova
reviews.text: We absolutely love this daycare! Olga is truly amazing‚Äîshe‚Äôs warm, attentive, and clearly loves what she does. Our child is always happy and well cared for, and we really appreciate the variety of fun activities and the delicious, healthy meals she provides. One of the highlights for us is that the kids get to spend time outdoors at the beautiful nearby parks. It‚Äôs such a nurturing, safe, and enriching environment. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Max Williamson
reviews.text:
We‚Äôve had such a wonderful experience with Bluebell Daycare. Olga is warm, attentive, and incredibly nurturing‚Äîexactly the kind of person you hope to find when leaving your little one for the first time.

Our child (under 2) settled in quickly and clearly feels safe and happy there. The space is cozy, clean, and thoughtfully set up for young children, with just the right mix of play, learning, and care.

We love the updates Olga sends and feel so lucky to have found such a loving, trustworthy environment for our baby.

reviews.author: Lyudmila Vv
reviews.text:
I cannot say enough positive things about this home-based daycare program! The owner Olga,  is a truly wonderful, loving provider who is passionate about working with children. From the moment you step into her beautiful, cozy environment, you can tell that every detail has been designed with the kids‚Äô well-being in mind.
My children absolutely love it here‚Äîthey have formed such a warm, trusting relationship with the teacher. Every day, they engage in fun, developmental activities that not only entertain but also help them grow and learn. I especially appreciate the commitment to health and nutrition: they serve daily fresh, organic meals and delicious snacks, which gives me peace of mind as a parent.
Additionally, the program includes regular walks and plenty of quality outdoor time, allowing the kids to enjoy nature, get plenty of exercise, and simply have fun. It‚Äôs clear that every moment is carefully planned to enrich their day and nurture their development.
If you‚Äôre a parent in need of a caring, engaging daycare for your little ones, I highly encourage you to check out Bluebell Kids Daycare. It‚Äôs a place where children are not only well cared for but also truly cherished.

reviews.author: Marina Ferrer Clotas
reviews.text: Our twins have been going to this family-run daycare for almost two years, and we absolutely love it! There's a warm, familiar atmosphere, and Fatema, who runs the daycare, is like a second mom to our children. It's clear she loves what she does. The activities are fun, educational and age-appropriate, and we love that there's a strong balance between play and learning. Fatema provides delicious homemade food, which is a huge plus, we feel great knowing our children are eating well.  Communication is always excellent, we feel informed of what‚Äôs going on. Most importantly, our kids are genuinely happy to go every day. Highly recommend to any family looking for a nurturing, reliable, and joyful environment for their children!

reviews.author: Sayuri Shimada
reviews.text: My daughter went to there since she was 2 months old and she loved Fatema and friends !! I‚Äôm so happy to find the fun tree day care. Fatema took care of her very well and nicely. There were various activities everyday. We are missing them and I appreciate all support.

reviews.author: Maryam Arab
reviews.text: Best coffee in SF, and super friendly staff

name: Modern Education Family Childcare - Hayes Valley

reviews.author: Diana Salazar
reviews.text: Our daughter has been with Elham for a year and half. Our daughter loves the teachers and her friends at school. Our daughter has learned so much and developed. We noticed this growth quickly upon entry.

reviews.author: Nina Strachan
reviews.text:
Elham is such a wonderful caretaker and we are so happy with her daycare. Our daughter has been with her since 4 months old and it is incredible to see the growth she is going through. Every single day that we drop her off, she always has a giant smile when she sees Elham and her assistants.

Elham is super detail oriented and great at communication. We feel really safe leaving our daughter there and we also knew we made the right choice when we saw how much the other kids love and trust Elham.

reviews.author: Ann Carter
reviews.text: Can't recommend Ellie's Daycare enough! Our son has been at Ellie's Daycare since 2022 and he's so so SO happy there. Elham has created a wonderful environment for little ones of all ages to learn and grow. She provides home cooked meals and lots of space for play, inside and out. She is always doing the cutest seasonal art projects and loves throwing parties for birthdays and holidays. Elham goes all out to make sure the kids feel safe and appreciated, and we love her for it!

reviews.author: Paul Dickens
reviews.text:
Our daughters (1.5 yr old and 4 yr old) have attended Ellie‚Äôs Daycare for the last 6 months. We absolutely love Elham and her daycare! Our daughters adore her, they are thrilled to go everyday and always smiling when we pick them up - we could not be more happy with the care that is provided. With the pandemic we have had to switch daycares a few times in the last year and can say with absolute certainty that Ellie‚Äôs is our favorite.

Elham provides healthy, organic meals and snacks to the girls everyday (even adjusting for our picky eaters at times). Elham provides a wonderful environment of play, art, music, and learning - both of our kids are learning so fast identifying colors, shapes, numbers, letters - absorbing so much information. For our older daughter, Elham also reports to us about ways to make sure she is learning and reaching age-appropriate milestones. The artwork that the girls bring home is fun and creative - we love seeing all of it.

For holidays and each of the kids birthdays, Elham has large celebrations - the kids love it! She sends videos and pictures from these special days and they are some of my favorite photos of our girls.

The hours and flexibility have been great as well. Elham is always very good about advance notice for holiday schedules, and there haven‚Äôt been any long closures for holidays, and no covid issues either, which is a big win over past daycares. Her hours allow my partner and I to easily manage pick-up and drop-off, and we‚Äôve never had a daycare where the kids are so excited to get there every morning. All around it has been a wonderful experience taking our kids to Ellie‚Äôs.

reviews.author: Yvonne Morante
reviews.text:
We are so grateful for having found such an incredible daycare for our daughter! We‚Äôve joined about a year ago when we moved to the sunset and considered ourselves lucky to have found a place that aligned with our parenting style and family values while Offering a safe environment for our daughter. She thrives in this daycare, we can see how well supported she is emotionally and developmentally by Elham and her helper, and it‚Äôs super fun to get to see all of the activities that they do during the day! Our two-year-old has a robust vocabulary, knows a ton of songs, has strong eye/hand coordination and great social skills, we attribute all of this in great part to Elham‚Äô education program. She comes home with a  full belly, very clean, fun art work and lots of pictures with her friends.
Communicating with Elham has been easy from day one, and love knowing that she truly cares about our daughter‚Äôs wellbeing! I definitely recommend this daycare yo any families that are looking for a diverse and warm environment for their kids in the sunset.

reviews.author: Jad Adaimi
reviews.text: We couldn‚Äôt recommend this place enough. Kooky was like an extra grandma that took extreme care of our then 6 month old till she was 2. She is full of love and it shows with the kids. It‚Äôs an in home play based care. Ratio is 4:1 and the help is as nice as Kooky.

reviews.author: Pratik Tandel
reviews.text: Kooky takes excellent care of our daughter. Our daughter is in love with the daycare.

reviews.author: Erin Tuomey
reviews.text: The best daycare. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Sisca H
reviews.text: My daughter went to Lucy‚Äòs daycare from four months old until she was 2 1/2. We felt so fortunate to find Lucys. She and her two other caretakers are attentive, kind and very communicative about any of our or their concerns. My daughter adored them and would always race inside when we dropped her off to give them giant hugs. I felt totally confident leaving her in their care. They also have wonderful gatherings for the families a few times a year and do special things like little photo shoots for the holidays.

reviews.author: Vaishali Desai
reviews.text: My son started going in February 2021. We were nervous since he was home with us during the pandemic. We are extremely pleased and happy with the way Lucy and her team handled the transition and cared for my son thereafter. He has had no issue adjusting to the daycare routine as they have lots of stimulating activities. The space they have created is very thoughtful and they keep changing the toys and setup to keep things interesting for kids age 4 month thru 3 years. They even celebrate all the fun holidays like the Valentines day, St. Patricks day etc. All the caretakers are great and the kids love them dearly. I would highly recommend this daycare.

reviews.author: Karen Gomez
reviews.text: The best small daycare

reviews.author: brittney
reviews.text: Incredibly happy to have found this school for our daughter. Every teacher and caregiver is attentive and patient. The play based model allows for kids to learn how to regulate their emotions through free play and imaginative child-led games. Our daughter is confident, kind and prepared for kindergarten next year.

reviews.author: Julie Collins
reviews.text:
I highly recommend Laurel Hill Nursery School! My child attended Laurel Hill for two years, and we have had a wonderful experience.

The teachers at Laurel Hill are truly exceptional. They are caring, knowledgeable, and passionate about early childhood education. They created a warm and supportive environment where my child thrived.

Laurel Hill's play-based curriculum is perfect for young learners. My child loves spending thier days exploring, creating, and learning through play. They developed their social, emotional, and academic skills in a fun and engaging way.

I was also impressed with Laurel Hill's parent community. Everyone was welcoming and supportive, and I quickly made friends with other parents. I also appreciated the opportunity to participate in the school's cooperative program. It been a great way to get involved in my child's education and meet other families.

reviews.author: Natalie Savicke
reviews.text:
Enrolling my son at Laurel Hill has been an incredible decision for our family. From the moment we stepped through the doors, we were warmly welcomed into a nurturing and inclusive community that has truly started to become an extension of our family.

The teachers and volunteers are absolutely incredible. Their genuine care for each child's development and well-being is evident in every interaction. My son, who is naturally reserved and hesitant in new environments, formed a special bond with a few of the teachers within just a few weeks. They have a unique talent for understanding his needs and encouraging his participation in activities at his own pace.

I wholeheartedly recommend Laurel Hill to any parent seeking out a play based preschool. It's been a transformative experience for my son and our entire family.

reviews.author: Micaela Davis
reviews.text: I cannot recommend Laurel Hill enough for families with young children. It is truly a special place and we have had an incredible time here with our kids. The teachers and staff are loving, experienced and professional. The outdoor space at the school is unmatched in the city with multiple levels of decks, sandpits and play areas, climbing structures, a 'cafe' area for cooking sand stew, slides, a biking zone, redwood trees and plenty of water play, digging, art, swinging, imaginary play and any other activities the kids dream up in their self-directed day. And working alongside the teachers and other parents at the school is truly an invaluable learning and community-building experience!

reviews.author: Christine Cantwell
reviews.text: Our family has been a part of Laurel hill in both the afternoon program and the preK and it is a wonderful and home-ly place. Meaning it feels like a home and a place kids can experience wonder and excitement and enthusiasm for their discoveries and I think it is very beneficial to all the family members to experience the co-op nursery school thing if it can work logistically for you. (You have to work one 3 hour shift a week and do other volunteer hours throughout the year). The staff is all caring and thoughtful and I see how the kids just grow more and more into themselves and shine with the Love that everyone (Meaning the other parents workers too) gives to the program because they really care and want the best for all the children.

reviews.author: Chuck Armstrong
reviews.text: Amazing school very exciting, watching the growth and development of the kids in their school.  Amazing staff who genuinely care about the children.  Excellent all around.

reviews.author: Jennifer Frost
reviews.text: Such an incredible community

reviews.author: Mario Chavarria
reviews.text: cool, quirky staff

reviews.author: F H
reviews.text: Absolutely love Blueside. Rosa is an incredible mentor and encourages all the kids to explore and express their curiosity in a fun filled and safe environment. Our little one is a truly avid walker now since he‚Äôs gotten such good practice at school. We can‚Äôt say enough wonderful things about blueside or Rosa. What a gift.

reviews.author: Lucila P
reviews.text:
Our child loves Blueside! He joined the program in August and has been thriving since.
Rosa has been absolutely wonderful supporting his adaptation and development, sending us regular updates and photos of their adventures.
Speaking of adventures, they get a lot of outdoor time, visiting the nearby playground, park, and museum.
They work on adorable art projects, which our child will proudly bring home.
We highly recommend this gem of a preschool.

reviews.author: Lauren Spragge
reviews.text: My son had a wonderful first year of preschool at Blueside. The small class size (6 children max) was perfect for attentive care and for forming his first friendships. I was nervous about the transition, as he was just under 2 years when he started, though he never complained or cried about going to school, even on the first day! They spend a lot of time outdoors at the wonderful local playgrounds and museums. Rosa is a very kind caregiver, and I've seen how much independence he's gained over the course of the school year. He now comprehends and speaks Spanish, due to her bilingual program. It's a safe and loving environment for toddlers ~2-4 yrs old. We planned to keep him enrolled, though ended up moving. We'll miss Blueside and Rosa!

reviews.author: Shaena Ulissi
reviews.text: We feel really fortunate that a spot opened up at Blueside for our almost-2-year-old when we were planning a move to SF. Rosa takes great care of the children with a lot of positive energy, healthy food, helpful daily structure, and excellent communication. It was particularly difficult to find a childcare where the kids spend time exploring the outdoors, and we love that they spend every morning walking outside and playing at playgrounds and local museums. Our son is happy, safe, and learning a lot!

reviews.author: Vera Kushnir
reviews.text:
My son has been with at Blueside since last year, he was 21 month old when he started.
I like that kids get to play outside daily. Rosa takes a good care of them. We had no accidents, my son always comes back clean. He learned  lots of songs at school, he started counting. I get photo updates daily which is so precious to see him having fun.
Definitely recommending this preschool.

reviews.author: Marina Chen
reviews.text:
The proverb "It takes a village to raise a child" encapsulates the idea that the responsibility of nurturing and guiding a child extends beyond the immediate family to include a broader community. In our experience with JCC Helen Diller , this saying has come to life. The collaborative spirit among teachers, parents, and the dedicated director mirrors the essence of a supportive village.

The outstanding teachers contribute not just academically, but also emotionally, creating a collective atmosphere of care and encouragement. The shared commitment to a child's growth and development fosters a sense of unity among families. The preschool has truly become an extended family where everyone plays a role in shaping the experiences and memories of our child.

The amazing director, Karla sets the tone for this communal approach, fostering a sense of belonging and shared responsibility. This environment has proven invaluable in providing our child with a well-rounded and enriching early childhood education.

In essence, we feel fortunate to be part of this village, where the values of community, support, and collective growth are not just spoken but lived every day. It reinforces the belief that raising a child is not a solitary journey but a shared endeavor enriched by the diversity and strength of the village we are fortunate to call our preschool family.

reviews.author: Corinna Rao
reviews.text: Diller is the preschool jackpot! The community is very welcoming and we've built deep relationships with other families. Our kids' days are filled with joy and discovery. Karla and her phenomenal team of teachers and specialists (art, music, and nature) are incredible and absolutely love the students! From cooking to creative art projects, garden explorations, and walks to the Presidio, every day is filled with joyful learning. We've seen our kids learn and grow a ton in their time here!

reviews.author: Greg Geronemus
reviews.text:
Can‚Äôt say enough about how amazing JCCSF Helen Diller preschool has been for our family. Not only have they delivered an incredible early childhood education for our two (and soon-to-be three) kids, but they have provided us with a wonderful community of warm, kind-hearted families.

The teachers (Hannah, Sandra, Kim, Juliet, Tracy, JT, and more) are second to none, and the leadership (Karla and Karyn) are phenomenal.

And yes, they are great at preparing and helping place kids at their first choice elementary schools.

reviews.author: Adam Glazier
reviews.text: Fantastic community center. Great school, gym, pool, cafe and performances.

reviews.author: Florian Roquet
reviews.text: Amazing place

name: The International School of San Francisco: Maternelle/Preschool

reviews.author: Sol
reviews.text: I highly encourage prospective parents to do research on the Waldorf philosophy, ‚ÄúAnthroposophy‚Äù, and Steiner before deciding to send their children to this school. I did not. While the advertising promises ‚Äúteaching to the whole child‚Äù and ‚Äúoutdoor education‚Äù, many parents have spoken out about their negative experiences in the Waldorf system online - and there‚Äôs a lot of insights that could be helpful in your exploring what works best for your family, and what will best prepare your children for a changing world. Their promotional materials leave out fundamental aspects of their teaching (see: their teaching about heaven, angels, and reincarnation to kindergarteners), and you only discover these aspects once you‚Äôre knee deep in the system. Waldorf may be right for you and your family, and their covert ideology may line up with your own - but please make the decision with open eyes.

reviews.author: Anu Puisto
reviews.text:
My child has been with the San Francisco Waldorf School's Nursery (preschool) program for almost two years. We are very happy with the school:

1) They provide all lunches and snacks!
2) They spend a lot of time outdoors.
3) The teachers go above and beyond. They truly care about the children like they were their own and they are all very knowledgeable about early childhood development.

The children get to sing and bake and climb and get muddy. Such a wonderful experience!

reviews.author: Fuller Family
reviews.text: My daughter is very happy to be dropped off and picked up from this place. Professional, attentive thumbs up!

reviews.author: Gemma Wilde
reviews.text: Phoebe Hearst is an awesome and well run preschool. Our son loved his time here. They also have extra services like speech and occupational therapy readily available.

reviews.author: Charlie Liu
reviews.text: Lots of parking in this area.

reviews.author: Kristen Kelly
reviews.text: We have 4 children, each of whom attended SLS.  Our fourth child is about to graduate this year and we have cherished our past 11 years at the school. I can honestly say that our experience at SLS has been wonderful for each of our children and our entire family. We feel so fortunate that we have been able to be a part of the SLS community. The teachers and administration are extremely high quality, nurturing, caring, patient and place an emphasis on respect and discipline in the classroom.  SLS places a strong focus on Kindergarten readiness in their curriculum, and all our 4 kids were well-prepared for Kindergarten. In addition, SLS has long-standing traditions, including cultural and holiday celebrations, plays, recitals, family zoo days that provide opportunities for parents to engage with their children and the school. My children and my husband and I have made lifelong friends with the families we have met through the warm SLS community and we will always consider our 11 years at SLS truly magical and unforgettable.

reviews.author: Nicole Krouse
reviews.text: My youngest (of 3) is about to graduate from SLS and I could not be more grateful for our time there. SLS is a magical school and my children always loved going there. The teachers are warm and have helped my children excel with early academics as well and social and emotional learning. The community is so welcoming and the friends made there have become like family. It will always have a special spot in my heart and I will cherish our 7 years at SLS.

reviews.author: Dani Dudeck
reviews.text: We've been SLS parents for the last 6 years and can attest to the school's unique strengths. In short - SLS has been amazing for our family. Every morning at drop-off we've seen our kids run, not walk, to get inside and start their school day. What stands out for us as a family is the highly experienced and tenured teachers - the SLS faculty is warm, engaging, hands-on and covers an impressive range of both academic material and creative play to bring joy to the classroom and outdoor experiences. From music class, to languages, to immersive art, to the charming rooftop recess to outdoor school sessions - SLS gives kids a truly holistic education that best prepares them for kindergarten and beyond. SLS excels at preparing kids for their next chapter of education - our daughter attends an all-girls private school in San Francisco and had a wonderfully smooth transition because of her SLS foundation. There's a reason the school has been among the best in the city for 75 years - we could not recommend it more highly for prospective parents looking for a unique mix of both academic and experiential learning.

reviews.author: Lucila Pescarmona
reviews.text: The most wonderful and magical early education one can provide for their kids. A nurturing and loving environment with the best teachers with a strong academic curriculum that ensured both of my kids would strive in Kindergarten. Wonderful community of involved parents that I am happy to call my friends.

name: Tinker Preschool Cole Valley Mandarin Immersion

reviews.author: Mandy Walker
reviews.text: Wendy and her team run the best preschool I have ever experienced. They provide healthy meals, play outdoors at the park everyday, run purposeful activities and take great care of the kids. Not once did my son ever come home dirty, or with items missing this is very well run organisation run by very caring people. Cannot rate them enough.

reviews.author: Justin Chan
reviews.text:
Our family couldn't be happier with the daycare experience that Tinker Cole Valley provided to our daughter. Though we lived quite far from this location, and had nearby daycares that offered more convenience, we were more than happy to make the extra long journey to Tinker. This is because Tinker offers an experience that few other daycares have, which is daily connection to nature at Golden Gate Park. In addition to making friends and learning Mandarin, we wanted our daughter to be imbued with an appreciation for and curiosity about the natural world. That is exactly the type of child she has blossomed into, thanks to her being able to spend each day in a real park as her natural playground. Wherever we go, she loves to dig up the ground beneath her, and inspect every flower and tree.

We were also incredibly fond of the Tinker Cole Valley teachers and staff. They demonstrated a great understanding of our daughter's needs, and made great effort to help her feel welcomed each day. The PTA is also very active and involved, which makes for a great young family community. Would recommend Tinker Cole Valley to anyone, no matter where in SF you live!

reviews.author: Jaclyn Loo
reviews.text:
I rarely write public reviews, but can't say enough positive things about Tinker Preschool in Cole Valley. From the caring teachers and administrators to the robust STEAM curriculum and fun activities, this school truly goes above and beyond to create a safe, dynamic environment for learning Mandarin and giving kids a great foundation in education.

Everything about Tinker- daily communications, the PTA and overall community - really set a high bar and we see ourselves staying in touch with many of the families we met there.

Perhaps most importantly, our kids loved going there every day. We were collectively so sad to leave when we moved out of state, and will always be thankful to Annie, Wendy and all of the wonderful teachers at Tinker!

reviews.author: Jeremy O
reviews.text: We are very happy with the school and the entire community that surrounds it. The staff and daily updates are wonderful. There's typically a long waitlist, we were happy we had signed up early!

reviews.author: Giff Brooks
reviews.text: Our daughter has attended NOPA Montessori for over a year, and we couldn't be happier. Every teacher and member of the staff cares deeply about the development and well-being of the children. I've enjoyed learning more about the Montessori approach to education. It's had a clearly positive impact on our daughter!

reviews.author: Lauren Ross
reviews.text: This is our second year at NOPA Montessori and we feel lucky to have found a school that feels like home. The staff are all so skilled, warm, and caring. Our daughter is thriving in the Montessori ecosystem, surprising us daily with new skills and discoveries. The kids really feel a sense of community together, and that extends to the parents as well. We couldn't be happier to be part of the NOPA family!

reviews.author: Haesun Brooks
reviews.text:
Our daughter has been at NOPA Montessori the past year and we've been thoroughly amazed by her transformation.

She moves and carries herself independently, from washing her hands, taking clothes on and off, and caring for her space (she's not even 3!). Her verbal skills have taken off (quote from today: "I cannot touch the sky yet because I'm still growing"). She loves her friends at school, many of whom also live close to school.

The teachers are attentive to each child and devoted to helping them thrive in every way. We're so excited to enroll our son as soon as he's old enough next year!

reviews.author: Ori Franco
reviews.text: Our daughter joined Nopa Montessori at 19 months and we could not be happier. The teachers are so caring and supportive, there is a great balance between play/academics/practical lessons, the day is structured and the facilities are clean and organized.

reviews.author: David Apple
reviews.text:
Both of our kids attend NOPA Montessori, and we couldn't be happier with the care, attention, and education they receive.  In fact, we decided to keep our son at NOPA Montessori through Kindergarden rather than transferring him to another school.

The school is very well run, and the teachers are outstanding.  I highly recommend NOPA Montessori.

reviews.author: Cathy DeCock
reviews.text:
My two children were lucky enough to have gone to Haight Ashbury Cooperative Nursery School and it was some of the best times in our family.

The community with the other parents, loving and helping each other‚Äôs children at such an important time in their development was so wonderful.  Snack time, story time with Cocoa (who gives nothing but kindness and live to each and every child (and parent) are things that are unlike any other school.

The freedom for our young kids to dress up, play, ready, play in the sand, ride bikes, do crafts and to choose what works for them is such a gift to our kids!

If you are considering HACNS, you and your family will be so happy to share that precious time in your child‚Äôs life at HACNS!!

reviews.author: Maureen Minn
reviews.text: We had two boys attend HACNS over 5 years and the art, stories, building, imagination, drama, digging, snacking, creation, reading, moving, making friends and growing was such a fantastic experience for them! The community of parent volunteers and a play-based approach is a great way to be involved with your child's development, and we've made amazing friends to boot. Haight Ashbury Cooperative Nursery School will welcome your child and your family with love and open arms.

reviews.author: Julia Finn
reviews.text: Haight Ashbury Cooperative Nursery is a Cole Valley neighborhood treasure. This play-based school has been amazing for our daughter. It's situated at the Grattan Playground which allows for a lot of outdoor play, which is so important at preschool ages. Teacher Cocoa is so very dedicated to the kids, their development, and ensuring an inclusive, collaborative environment. The kids are exposed to lots of age-appropriate activities that develop different skills sets in the most natural way, as well as lots of outdoor time. As a co-op, parents are expected to be active participants in the building of this amazing community. On that front, the communication channels are open and parents are very friendly and collaborative as well. My daughter has thrived at this school, hasn't yet had a day when she doesn't want to attend, and is always asking for more time at the school. Kid-approved as well!

reviews.author: Robert Snavely
reviews.text: What a wonderful place and nurturing community to be a part of! HACNS helped our three boys get the right start in life and brought us together as a family. Most of our best friends are coop families that we met along the way. If you can do it, and be a part of this wonderful coop preschool, it can be the best experience of your child‚Äôs life! What better gift can a parent give?

reviews.author: Katlin Zimmer
reviews.text: Our son is in 3rd grade and still talks about how much he loved his preschool days! He remembers the magic of it all, and so do we. We had an immediate community that felt like family, and being in a major city without family, the support and friendship from the community made San Francisco home. Cocoa writes a poem for every student when they graduate, and we still chuckle at how well she saw and loved our child for exactly who he is and how much of her poem about him is still true. I feel blessed that we landed at HACNS when we did and would recommend this magical place to anyone looking for a cooperative preschool.

reviews.author: 2o20march23 acct-COMPROMISEDbyhacker
reviews.text: fabulous teachers abd nice verbage astronauts, sharks for Hu-mans...plenty of activities, etc. The best diverse makeup and ratio of teachers to little ones.

reviews.author: Jennifer Brodsky
reviews.text: We have so many wonderful things to say about Alta Plaza Preschool (APP)! It can be difficult to find a preschool that is simultaneously well organized and structured - but also flexible and understanding that preschoolers don't always do things exactly as we might hope! This school achieves that rare and special balance! We needed a part-time schedule and they were very flexible and accommodating. They also offer full-time schedules. The teachers and administrators at APP are very kind, thoughtful, creative, fun and experienced working with children. They also plan so many fun activities in and outside of the classroom for the kids. We really liked the other families at the school and many would sometimes get together for weekend playdates and other informal fun. We liked that the children are divided into 3 different age-based groups but also get to spend time with all of the students during certain activities. HIGHLY recommend APP!

reviews.author: Laurane De Mot
reviews.text: Amazing preschool. Our then 2.5-yo son spent a few months there when we were travelling to SF for work, and despite the language barrier he immediately fell warmly welcome. He was always happy to go to preschool, and was coming back with beautiful memories of the activities he did there. The kids also go in the park every day, which I found amazing. I had the opportunity to spend several half-days in the preschool for specific activities, and I was amazed by the kindness and calm of the teachers in all situations. APP is one of the main reasons we miss SF so much...

reviews.author: Mathieu Poma
reviews.text:
Our child enterred APP at 3 and we immediatly felt welcome as part of a family. Erika's team was always super responsive and listening to us. The presence of Alta Plaza park next to the school is also a great add on as the kids go out (weather allowing) every day.
There are also numerous side activities organized (music,....)
Last but not least, the community of parent is quite active and organizes numerous event (eg camping trips) that are great both for adults and kids. We made many friends there!

reviews.author: rozana alam
reviews.text: As a grandmother of a preschooler who just graduated, I am advising any family looking for a nurturing preschool with a philosophy of learning and play in a supportive and loving environment, to seek out this wonderful preschool. Excellent and caring teachers who really ‚Äúknow‚Äù the kids! Well done, APP!

reviews.author: Zona Pan
reviews.text:
Both of our kids attended Tinker, and we couldn‚Äôt be happier with the experience. One of the things that really sets Tinker apart is its emphasis on outdoor play‚Äîour children thrived with so much time spent outside exploring, learning, and just being kids. We love that they enjoy ample outdoor time all year round.

The teachers and administrators are incredibly caring and dedicated. You can tell they genuinely love what they do, and it shows in how they engage with the children and support each family. We always felt heard, welcomed, and part of a thoughtful, intentional community.

Tinker is a truly special place and we feel so lucky to have been part of it.

reviews.author: Tim Fortescue
reviews.text: Tinker gave us everything we hoped for and more for our daughter.  Our daughter started as a toddler (2 and a half years old) and is leaving a confident, curious, adventurous, creative 5 year old.  We credit much of this to her experience at Tinker.  We loved that she could explore outdoors every day at Golden Gate Park and Mountain Lake Park.  Her teachers were fantastic, spending so much time with her and giving her role models to look up to.  She made wonderful friends in class and we met other parents that have become our close friends.  As she starts Kindergarten soon, we're grateful for these past nearly 3 years at Tinker and hope that the rest of her school experiences will be as positive as this was.

reviews.author: Scott Jablonski
reviews.text: We are now sending our second of two children to Tinker and love the teachers, admins and other families there. We were one of the first families at the Park Presidio location 4 years ago and, throughout, they have always been welcoming and caring with our little ones. There‚Äôs a lot of outdoor action which is terrific for kids learning about nature, etc. and it‚Äôs great to see the same teachers helping our second child grow years after our first was there. Highly recommended!

reviews.author: Trevor Ford
reviews.text:
Both of our children spent 4 years at Tinker and they loved every minute of it. All of the teachers over the years were special, our kids still talk about them.
Location is convenient for trips to the park or Presidio, both of which are part of the outdoor curriculum.

reviews.author: Jessica Allen
reviews.text:
My son loved this preschool!  He attended for two years and is more than ready for kindergarten.  The teachers are excellent and put a lot of thought into their lesson design.  Little things, like having each child trace their name every morning to "sign-in," are so brilliant.  My son rapidly developed the ability to write his name form this small activity.

You can tell they put a lot of thought into building social emotional well being among the student when you visit the school.  Students play together and happily help each other with outdoor building projects and games.

Can't recommend enough.  We stumbled upon this preschool because we were looking for a place after the pandemic that fit our needs and realized we were so lucky to have landed our son in a spectacular preschool.

reviews.author: Victoria Bogatsky
reviews.text: Great preschool with a wonderful teacher. My second one is going there and loves Tonia, he's learning so much. I plan to send my third one there soon! Highly recommend.

reviews.author: Peter Lidsky
reviews.text: Great place, great people.

reviews.author: Jynette Oji
reviews.text: Love it! Attentive. Inclusive. Caring. Creative. Collaborative. Organized.  Professional. Educational. Fun. Worth it.

reviews.author: Joey Michaels
reviews.text: These people are rude. Do not waste your time with this place.

name: Montessori Children's House of the West Coast

reviews.author: Karen Tso
reviews.text: I have two children at MCH and the experience has been wonderful.  My older son is now in kindergarten and was incredibly prepared by his time at MCH.  My younger son is in his second year and loves attending; he runs into the school at drop off without a backwards glance.  The teachers are amazing - gentle but firm and so knowledgeable (the two head teachers have over 25 years of experience each).  Every time I volunteer at the school, I am still impressed by the quiet and calm hum of activity in the classrooms that drew me in the first time I toured.  Every single child is engaged in their own work which is different from their peers.  The activities are changed out frequently so the children are consistently engaged.  The community of parents is friendly and easy going, and the school and social committee plan just enough activities for the families to get to know each other and not feel overwhelmed.  The school does its best to accommodate working parents with live drop offs in the morning and extended care in the afternoons.  The administrators and teachers are welcoming and approachable with easy to access office hours which can conducted over zoom.  MCH is truly a local gem and I feel grateful to be a part of this community.

reviews.author: Zainab Khan Allawala
reviews.text:
My daughter has truly blossomed at MCH. It‚Äôs an exceptional Montessori school where children are genuinely engaged and encouraged to grow with confidence. The school deeply follows the Montessori philosophy, and we‚Äôve seen so much independence, curiosity, and joy develop in our daughter since she joined.

All of the teachers are incredible, especially the head teachers who each bring over 25 years of experience to the classroom. I‚Äôd love to especially recognize Kathleen, the head teacher in my daughter‚Äôs class‚Äîshe is patient, kind, and simply a wonderful educator. We feel so grateful for the impact she has had on our daughter.

The administration is also incredibly organized and supportive, making the entire experience smooth and welcoming.

We feel very lucky to be part of the MCH community and couldn‚Äôt recommend it more.

reviews.author: Prerak Bathia
reviews.text:
We feel incredibly lucky to have found this school for our child ‚Äì it‚Äôs not just a Montessori, it‚Äôs the OG Montessori in San Francisco, with a long-standing reputation, deeply experienced faculty, and an incredibly thoughtful, well-run program.

What sets this school apart is the tenured teaching staff ‚Äì many of whom have been with the school for years, even decades. Their deep expertise and calm, nurturing approach help create a focused, purposeful environment where kids thrive. The low teacher-to-student ratio means every child is truly seen, known, and supported.

The classrooms are bright, clean, and inviting, filled with beautiful materials that inspire independent learning and curiosity. One of the things we‚Äôve loved most is how students are taught to focus ‚Äì really focus ‚Äì whether they‚Äôre working with practical life materials or exploring early math or language. There‚Äôs a quiet hum of concentration and joy that fills the space.

There‚Äôs also a thoughtful balance here ‚Äì a community of families who go on to attend top-tier independent schools in San Francisco, and others who pursue the SFUSD route. It never feels competitive; instead, it feels like a supportive, respectful village where everyone wants what‚Äôs best for the children.

Beyond the classroom, the extended day programs are a huge plus for working families. The Friday hot lunch tradition, catered in, is something the kids look forward to all week. And we love that they explore different parks around the neighborhood ‚Äì a beautiful way to connect with the broader community and embrace the outdoors.

Behind the scenes, the school is exceptionally well run. The communication from faculty and administration is consistent, clear, and transparent, and the social events for families are meaningful and fun. We've made some of our closest friends through this school ‚Äì real connections that extend beyond drop-off and pick-up.

If you're looking for a Montessori that‚Äôs rooted in tradition but responsive to the needs of modern families, with heart, integrity, and excellence in everything it does ‚Äì this is it. We couldn‚Äôt recommend it more highly.

reviews.author: Molly Siems Cavanaugh
reviews.text: I could not be happier with this school.  I have two children here and they are thriving.  The quality of teaching is exceptional, and the love and care they feel each day is palpable.  I call it the "MCH effect": after going here for a few months, my children became happier, more confident and kinder humans. And the community of parents is supportive and wonderful.

reviews.author: Dana Krastev
reviews.text:
My daughter is in her third year at MCH and we couldn't be happier with our experience. She entered as a toddler at not even 3 years of age, and is set to go to Kinder next year as a mature, confident, independent 5 year old.

The teaching team at MCH is truly outstanding, with incredible tenure (3 of the teachers have been there for 25+ years!) and even better ability to draw children out and help them develop a love of learning. My daughter's social emotional skills are quite advanced, and I credit MCH for this as well. The school emphasizes respect for your environment and your peers, and gives children the tools to practice it on a daily basis.

The administration and the parent community are wonderful. Brianne the director is so helpful with the kindergarten application process, and responsive all around. The other families are great - friendly, grounded, and diverse - and we've made friends that we'll have in our lives for a long time. MCH is truly a gem.

reviews.author: Christine Cantwell
reviews.text: Rocky mountain has been a great place for our family, we all are learning so much about child development and relationships and community.  It is ALOT of work but you get an amazing amount back in terms of quality experience. I think my son will be benefitting for years to come from the kindness and safety he is given here to explore his world and friendships and emotions. He loves it so much he wants to go there on the weekends and keep playing even when there is not school.

reviews.author: Katie Fehrenbacher
reviews.text: Rocky Mountain preschool is a hidden gem in the crazy and expensive world of San Francisco early education. If you have kids between the ages of 2.5 and 5 years old, and you're looking for a place where they can play, explore and be their best selves, do yourself a favor and check out the Rocky Mountain program.

reviews.author: saskia sofia
reviews.text: this was one of the best experiences of my life. I felt so welcomed and cared for with a loving community surrounding me. Everyone has special bonds and memories that can‚Äôt be replaced, especially with the DELICIOUS food that we make together. Overall- BEST SCHOOL EVER! (And i still visit it often to this day)

reviews.author: Eli Block
reviews.text: This preschool has been fantastic for us and our son.

reviews.author: Elliot Schwartz
reviews.text: Rickety old wooden playground with a sand base.

reviews.author: Grace Nicolas -Kim
reviews.text:
Our kid joined LFSF since she was pre-K in 2020 and we do not regret our decision to send her to this amazing school .

Their education styles is very close to French schools in France which was the way my husband wanted for our kid‚Äôs early stage schooling . Our girl loves going to school and loved every teachers throughout the years.
The teachers really make sure the need for individual students and help the kids to thrive every way possible.  Our daughter is fluent with French as well as English . She loves reading books in both languages and reading 2 levels higher than her grades thanks to the teacher‚Äôs effort to initiate interest of reading.

reviews.author: Sal Campos
reviews.text: Great school

reviews.author: Jamila Janakiram
reviews.text: Our family loves Buen Dia because the teachers are so caring, supportive, and creative. Our daughter is finishing her first year and has been excited to go to school every single day. We love the school's focus on creativity, problem-solving, and resourcefulness. We're excited to be returning next year.

reviews.author: Erin L Gardner
reviews.text: We love Buen Dia so so much!  It's a loving community of long-tenured teachers who are so committed to all the kiddos.  Tons of art, playtime, creativity, and tools for kids to exercise their ideas.  Buen Dia has also been such a wonderful place for my son who has special needs and was turned down by other schools (this definitely speaks to the quality of their program and care from the teachers).  Lastly Buen Dia is a stalwart of the community - it's been there for a long time (30 years plus) and has relationships with many community organizations.

reviews.author: RAIKA GRIGOR
reviews.text: Buen Dia Family school is a wonderful place for kids. The environment is a child-centered and has lots of warm spirits. They celebrate different cultures and families are diverse. The teachers and staff are super amazing! Also the community is lovely. Our kids learned through play and experience.

reviews.author: Stephanie Ciancio
reviews.text: Buen D√≠a is the best part of our lives here in San Francisco. This kind of learning environment is truly special, - led by listening to children and supporting their creative exploration. The school house is a dream, with distinct and magical areas. The incredible teachers‚Äô many years at the school speak to the uniqueness of this place.

reviews.author: Dominique Rodriguez
reviews.text: LOVE THIS SCHOOL. Both of my children have attended Buen Dia and I couldn't be happier with the quality of education that they received there. The environment encourages kids to take risks and really explore things that they love. It is an amazing place.

reviews.author: Matt McAviney
reviews.text: We had a phenomenal experience at Little Bee! Our daughter started when she was only 18 months old, and despite our parental anxieties of first child, first preschool, LB was a great success. The teachers are fantastic - even today, years later, our daughter asks whether she can go back and visit them. The curriculum, including bilingual immersion and exploration of the Presidio, makes me wish I went to preschool there. Thank you Sarra (the school director) for such a wonderful and memorable experience!

reviews.author: –ù–∞—Å—Ç—è –ß–µ—Å–Ω–æ–≤–∞
reviews.text: Our family had a wonderful experience with Little Bee Preschool. The staff is warm, attentive, and creative in their approach. Our daughter always looked forward to going, and we saw her grow in confidence and curiosity every day.

reviews.author: Ting Neo
reviews.text:
Little Bee is an incredible preschool, and I could not recommend it enough to prospective parents. Our son has attended the Funston (Presidio) location since he was 2 years old. Each class has 3 main teachers + floating teachers, who all care for the kids with kindness and empathy. The campus' location in the Presidio creates an idyllic and beautiful environment for the kids - they go outside to explore nature every morning and we get sent daily pictures and videos of their adventures. We love the Mandarin immersion aspect, and our son is fully bilingual thanks to the teachers' efforts.

Sarra, the director of Little Bee, runs a tight and efficient ship. The involved PTA organizes many community events, such as monthly playdates, Easter Egg Hunts, an annual Camp Out, Pumpkin Picking, Santa's Brunch, parents' nights out and more across the Funston and Lombard locations. Beyond just a preschool, this is also a supportive, caring, welcoming community of families and we have met many wonderful friends through Little Bee.

reviews.author: Daniel Kan
reviews.text: amazing preschool that helped my kid learn mandarin. can‚Äôt recommend enough. super friendly staff and teachers. very well run.

reviews.author: Ying Fu
reviews.text:
Best decision ever made! They are the cleanest and most organized daycare/preschool we have ever enrolled our son. We were worried about full day for him but little bee has a very thoughtful way of easing the little one into their school program. The teachers are very attentive and communicate with us daily. We get daily photos of the classes day.
We get lunch menus, snack menus, daily schedules and also weekly curriculum.
Our son absolutely loves little bee and look forward to going everyday!

reviews.author: Gabriella Merlonetti
reviews.text:
I absolutely loved our experience at Star of the Sea Preschool! Both of my boys attended for the past few years, and it has been such a wonderful journey. The team of teachers is truly special, they complement one another beautifully, each bringing their own expertise and knowledge, which creates such a well-rounded learning environment.

I really appreciate how the program includes so much: Spanish immersion, Montessori elements, and religion, all while keeping the atmosphere warm, kind, and welcoming for every little one. My kids were always so happy at drop-off and pick-up time, which to me says it all.

The classroom is filled with natural light, thoughtfully arranged, and stocked with excellent materials. Beyond that, the school fosters a genuine sense of community that we felt lucky to be part of. I‚Äôm so grateful for the love and care my children received here, it‚Äôs truly a wonderful place!

reviews.author: Lisa Berens
reviews.text:
Star of the Sea Preschool is truly special and we feel so blessed to have found it. Our son attended in 2022 and is now in 1st grade at Stella Maris Academy on the same campus, and now our daughter is there. There are so many things we love about this preschool, but what stands out most are the exceptional teachers. They are incredibly nurturing, warm, and genuinely devoted to each child‚Äôs growth ‚Äî not just academically, but emotionally and spiritually.

The curriculum is so rich and diverse and strikes the perfect balance of structure, learning, and play: Catholic catechism, arts and crafts, Spanish language from native speaking teachers, Montessori lessons from Montessori-certified teachers, music from classically trained music teacher, field trips to the public library, special visits from older students for reading time, interactive lessons on life skills to become more independent and confident, and much more.

The preschool environment itself is extremely clean, calm, and thoughtfully organized ‚Äî a peaceful little haven within the larger TK‚Äì8 school. We love that the children benefit from being part of the wider school community, yet still enjoy their own cozy, dedicated space designed just for them.

The teachers are highly accessible and communicative so you always know what they are learning as a class and how your child is doing. We couldn‚Äôt imagine a more joyful and faith-filled start to our child‚Äôs education!

reviews.author: Kathleen Quillian
reviews.text:
Our oldest had such an incredible year here. The teachers are truly called by God to teach young children‚Äîthey remind me of Miss Honey from Matilda, which in my book is the highest compliment! They are patient, kind, and nurturing, which is exactly what toddlers need.
The teachers prepared our son beautifully for his transition to transitional kindergarten, and we couldn‚Äôt be happier with his experience. We can‚Äôt wait to send our younger two boys to Star of the Sea Preschool!

reviews.author: Aurelia Justina
reviews.text:
Choosing Star of the Sea Preschool has been one of the best decisions we‚Äôve made as parents. My son isn‚Äôt the type who adjusts quickly to new places, but something about Star of the Sea made him feel safe right away, it felt like he belonged. From day one, he walked in with confidence and has never once cried at drop-off. That alone tells you how special this school is.

I can‚Äôt say enough about the amazing teachers ‚Äî Mrs. Janelli, Ms. Novoa, and Ms. Brooks. They aren‚Äôt just teachers; they are gentle guides who truly see, hear, and care for each child. My son loves them deeply, and we do too. He‚Äôs growing not just academically, but as a person; learning kindness, patience, social skills, independence, and responsibility. He taught me songs he learnt from the school too.

There was one moment I‚Äôll never forget. I saw him fall at the playground, and before a teacher even noticed, the older children ran to him, asking, ‚ÄúAre you okay?‚Äù and trying to help him up. It was such a pure moment of kindness. It showed me this school doesn‚Äôt just teach, it models love and compassion every day.

Star of the Sea preschool is more than a school. It‚Äôs a community built on love, values, and heart. We feel truly blessed to be part of it.
And honestly, I don‚Äôt know how we‚Äôre supposed to move on to kindergarten after this, we‚Äôre already emotionally attached! üòÇ

reviews.author: khanh nguyen
reviews.text: I brought my son from 2019 now he is in Stella Maris academy and in 4th grade wonderful teachers and great teaching

reviews.author: Erin Meyer
reviews.text: Both of my children attended preschool at 150 Parker, and it exceeded our wildest expectations.  Their creativity blossomed, they learned how to resolve conflict independently (with support from the teachers), and most importantly, they LOVED going to school every day.  The Little Red School Bus is a completely unique program; it's hard to describe how amazing it is.  My kids have gained so much confidence in trying new things and exploring their city.  When it was time for my daughter to move on to kindergarten, she was completely prepared to start school and it was such an easy transition.  As parents, the Parker community is deeply important to us.  We've made lifelong friends and built a village.  I am so grateful for Parker School!

reviews.author: Sara Yoo
reviews.text: Our family has been a part of the One Fifty Parker Avenue School community since 2015 when our eldest entered the 3-year-olds' program and were lucky enough to have a second child so that we could stick around for a few more years. The teachers are incredible in their level of experience, their intense commitment to supporting the children and their enthusiasm around continued professional development. We visibly could see our children's growth in self-confidence, resiliency, independence and empathy over their preschool years, a result of the teaching staff both being responsive to their needs as children and also providing the space to allow for the children to recognize their own capabilities and knowing when to give them a little push to challenge them. The families we met at Parker are still some of our best friends; though our daughter is now heading into middle school, when she sees her old Parker buddies, it's like no time was lost, and their time together is all smiles and giggles. Preschool seems like such a quick blip on the radar in a person's lifetime, but the experience truly can set them up for success down the road. We are so grateful to Parker School and all of the incredible teachers, families and children we have been so fortunate to know during our time there.

reviews.author: Nadeem Sheikh
reviews.text: We sent both of our two children to the Parker School, with one now moving on to kindergarten. The school and its teachers are kind, delightful, thoughtful, and supportive (of both parents and the kids) - kind of everything you'd want in a preschool.  It's worth noting that the outdoor aspect of the program (including the Little Red School Bus, which is a unique offer among the top-tier SF preschools) has been great for helping our kids build physical skills not just social-emotional ones.  Parker supported our family in navigating the kindergarten admissions process and we were thrilled with our outcomes in the K admissions process for our son.  The school is small enough that it can provide very personalized support and enables us to build meaningful relationships with the families as well.

reviews.author: Kristin Novotny
reviews.text: Our family has been part of the Parker community since 2018 and it‚Äôs been a wonderful experience. The teachers at this school are incredibly talented and in tune with each child‚Äôs individual needs. The parent community is fun and supportive as well! We will be sad when our time at Parker is over but forever grateful for the amazing start the school has gifted our children.

reviews.author: Carlie Leduc
reviews.text: Such a magical preschool! We are so lucky to have spent the past 3 years at 150 Parker. Not only is it a charming campus with amazing staff who are here to support you and your family as your little one grows, they also have their very own magic school bus. With the Little Red School Bus, children get to adventure. In their second year, kids can sign up for weekly to daily field trips and it is an experience that makes Parker truly magical.

reviews.author: Michi Pezeshki
reviews.text: Had the absolute pleasure of being a parent of this school for 4 years. My two kids both loved their daily adventures and had a real interest in learning Mandarin. The school director, Sarra, is amazing and is a seasoned school leader. The teachers have all been fantastic and completely loving. I felt so lucky to drop my kids off in the presidio for school each day knowing how much they loved being there. The PTA is also such a great community with lots of opportunities to meet other parents. Would recommend Little Bee to anyone, Chinese speaking or not, it‚Äôs just a fantastic school.

reviews.author: Nicholas Caster
reviews.text: I would argue there isn‚Äôt a better place in San Francisco for a daycare. Kids need to be outside, and they get to be at Little Bee. Every day they head out for a hike to explore everything the Presidio has to offer. It has been amazing for our two boys. Please don‚Äôt let the Mandarin immersion concern you. Perhaps it doesn‚Äôt. Maybe it does, but our primarily Caucasian/Hispanic kiddos have done great and thrived and it‚Äôs a blast to hear them sing mandarin songs at the dinner table. The teachers are fantastic and I can tell they truly care for the kiddos. Our 5 year old is transitioning to kindergarten and got into a great school. I highly, highly recommend Little Bee!

reviews.author: Tiffany Kosolcharoen
reviews.text:
We love Little Bee.  The kids are happy, well adventured on their daily outings & kept safe; the director Sarra is easy to work with, and the parent community is welcoming.

On top of a Mandarin curriculum with creative activities daily, the lucky kids take outings every morning to various beautiful Presidio locations, including the ocean & beach, forest, and the new Presidio Tunnel tops.

We also appreciate the weekly show & tells, daily photo updates, and music classes.  The kids enjoy singing Mandarin & English songs learned without speaking Mandarin at home.  Highly recommend.

reviews.author: Sarah Summerall
reviews.text: We really like Little Bee.   All of the parents I know there, including me and my husband, agree that Sarra, the director, is really easy to work with and very accommodating.  Of the schools we have attended, this is definitely the most supportive of busy working parents.   The kids are happy and make friends, lots of photo updates during the day, and a reasonable but not overwhelming number of group activities.  We had two boys go through here, starting our third soon.

reviews.author: Xue Xue
reviews.text: I would like to thank all the teachers here. They are very studious, patient and loving in cultivating our children, and they do their best to take good care of our children. I am very grateful to them. Their rich teaching experience and curriculum arrangements allow the children to obtain rich knowledge.  knowledge; in addition, 2 hours of outdoor activities every day allow children to exercise their senses, vision, touch, hearing, and smell, and they do their best to take care of the children's safety. I am extremely grateful to every teacher at Little Bee.

reviews.author: Tamar Sahaf
reviews.text: We absolutely love this preschool! The teachers are so warm, kind, and truly care about each child. reviews.author: Kathleen M. Mirrashidi
reviews.text:
We've been at SF Tikes for 9ish months now, and we couldn't be happier. Our son is now 3, and he's in his second classroom. Each classroom has at least 2 teachers and they've all been amazing. He is in the Spanish immersion classroom and can communicate with the teachers in Spanish (and our Spanish speaking friends) even though he only gets Spanish at school!

Sarah is the head of school and she is amazing!!! Very communicative, friendly, helpful, and responsive. She is also on top of the recommendations from SFDPH and health advisories for air quality. On smoky days, they close the doors and run air purifiers so our kids can stay in school! This is a BIG deal, as most preschools close during fire season.

The community is also very supporting. It's been harder w covid, but we are about to have a moms night out for our classroom. :)

reviews.text:
Angela started caring for our son Nolan since he was five months old. As a first time parent, you are nervous to drop off your child at a daycare; however, Angela made us feel welcomed, comfortable, and safe.

Angela is very knowledgeable about children‚Äôs development and her space is very clean. She put all my worries at ease and uses the Brightwheel app to send daily updates and photos. I completely trust her to take care of my son and to make sure he is happy and healthy.

You can tell Angela loves working with children and takes pride in her business. My son Nolan loves Angela and sometimes even wants to stay longer at daycare. If I had more kids, I would definitely bring them to Angela and I would highly recommend her to any parent needing childcare.

reviews.author: Alex Spoto
reviews.text: From age 5 to 20 months, Angela took impeccable care of our daughter and helped us parents transition with her through several key developmental stages and phases. Early Start was an ideal environment for our young one during that tender age--she made friends, learned to socialize, encouraged to play and explore, but also was afforded gentle structure that, I think, greatly helped us as parents to implement nap times, transition to bottles, transition to solids, etc. Angela is so warm and kind, she brings a very positive, fun, relaxed yet collected energy to the kids, and her expertise in early childhood education made hitting those developmental steps feel remarkably natural and easy. Plus, Angela is a master baby photographer, and her dispatches of the babies at play throughout the day were so reassuring to me as a parent in addition to being extremely cute to look at. Angela is a clear and responsive communicator, a keen observer of and listener to the kids, and just generally diligent and hard-working to create a great experience for both children and parents. My daughter received healthy home-cooked meals once she started eating solids, and the facility was safe, clean, and well-appointed with thoughtfully curated books, toys, and furniture to encourage the babies to explore, socialize, and learn. A+ recommend, so grateful to Angela and Early Start!

reviews.author: Charline Dhalluin
reviews.text:

We feel very lucky to have found her!

reviews.author: Claire Curran

The facility itself is absolutely beautiful and well thought out to be welcoming and comfortable for the children. I am so grateful to have found Early Start and am eager to see more families join. Thank you to Angela for all you have done! We are so lucky to have found you!
