reviews.author: Kat
reviews.text: Karine has created an incredibly enriching learning environment here. The various learning methods, the hands on experiences and exposures, and the beautiful and above and beyond and other learning environment art work crafted here is more than I could have dreamed of. My daughter attending here was a gift to her and I wish school curriculum for all grade levels would be more in this fashion. Children would learn better and actually enjoy school. I can‚Äôt recommend CMF enough, my daughter‚Äôs French also grew a lot, even though going in she knew practically nothing. We love you CMF!

reviews.author: Helene Rouse
reviews.text:
As a native French speaker, we were searching for a school where our daughter could learn and speak French with other children. We found that and so much more at CMF. For us, the experience can be summed up in what we call the 3 Cs of Color Me French:

Creativity
Karine is deeply passionate about nurturing curiosity and creative expression through music, art, science, food, and hands-on exploration, all while fostering a genuine respect for nature and the environment. From the weekly music lessons to the insect studies and art projects, our daughter was continually inspired. Even now, at almost six years old, she is so proud to share the artwork she created during her time at CMF.

Community
We formed lifelong friendships at CMF. Beyond the birthday parties and playdates, it was truly special to see parents coming together to support one another, both during school events and in day-to-day life. That sense of connection and kindness is something we will always cherish.

Culture
With monthly field trips to city parks, museums, and cultural institutions, the children were exposed to the richness of the world around them. These outings helped them learn, explore, and appreciate the diversity of their community‚Äîboth locally and globally.

Merci Karine et Fabienne pour votre d√©dication, compassion et votre amiti√©

reviews.author: Oana Alupoaie
reviews.text:
Our family was fortunate to be a part of the wonderful Color Me French community for six years, and it was a truly sad moment when our youngest finished preschool.¬†CMF is more than just a preschool, it is a community where children and parents alike create meaningful friendships, setting it apart from other schools.

When we first discovered CMF, the language immersion was an added bonus,¬†but now we see how much it has benefited our entire family. Karine genuinely cares about enriching the children to become curious, emotionally regulated, conscientious¬†human beings. She makes certain the kids engage in both fine and gross motor skill development. The¬†children create incredible art, explore themes of nature and environmental care, frequently visit the park or play in the outdoor space so they're not cooped up inside all day. They also regularly prepare¬†seasonal food, involving the kids throughout the process. My son even had two helpings of a veggie soup made from vegetables harvested from the CMF garden! The classroom is transformed into a new theme every few weeks,¬†keeping the children engaged in pretend play while learning.

Color Me French is one of the best experiences our children could have had, and our eldest (nearly 9 years old) still talks about her time at Color Me French.

A huge thank you to Karine, Fabienne, and all the other teachers at CMF!

reviews.author: MacKenzie Foreman
reviews.text:
Both of our children went to Color Me French, and we found it to be the most enriching and valuable experience for our children, and for us, as new parents! We don't speak French in our home, but they left school as fabulous French speakers. For us, the French was an added bonus to all of the other things they were taught/exposed to: art, outdoor exploration, writing, music, fine motor skills (cutting, writing, etc), math, science, personal autonomy, social/emotional development, the list goes on...

Along with the love and kindness they received as this school, they have grown into curious humans, with a great love for learning. I think this is due in large part to the uplifting and inspiring environment that Karine, Fabienne and the other instructors provided for our kids. We will forever be grateful to the school, and for how formative it was for our children.

reviews.text:

reviews.author: Emily Garvie
reviews.text: We are so grateful to have had the opportunity to send our two children to SOMACC YBG. Our family has been at the school for five years, and the experience has been truly wonderful. reviews.text:

In many ways its all about the kids, but at the same time, everyone's (Support staff, teachers', substitutes', custodians', community program staff, parents', etc) well being is taken care of because SOMACC cares about the child's relationship to their entire community. There's not room to name everyone, but thank you to Director Jennifer for always responding to parents concerns and leading Friday dance party; Joy, Roxy and Melinda for running administration so well; Simone for caring for our kids safety and individual development; Rod and family center staff for community building and outreach; SOMACC PAC for your dedication to enriching the kids' lives; and of course Teachers Saima, Winnie, Tina, Holly, Jasmine, Jenny, Tuba, and all the teachers for caring so much about all the kids development and well being. At school, when the older kids were graduating to kindergarten we talked to our son about graduating to other schools someday and how one day he might go to schools with names like Oxford and Cambridge. He responded that while he wants to go to kindergarten, he wished he could stay at Somacc forever.
In case it‚Äôs helpful for anyone on the fence about starting school at this time, we have been very confident in the schools safety protocols. As a reformed germaphobe, I would not have sent my child back if I did not feel he was safe and it is now coming up on a full year he has been back safely in class. The children are very resilient, adaptable, and able to wear their masks all day. The rooms have extremely high ceilings and full doors allowing plenty of ventilation in addition to the air filters and hvac. Much of the children‚Äôs time is spent outdoors since the play yard is enormous and the classrooms each have a large balcony play area. The space is truly amazing and we‚Äôd all be lucky to spend all day in such a wide open sky/green grass area in the midst of downtown. Meals are individually sealed and no child ever goes home hungry. While the pandemic has meant that many of the great families moved away, new wonderful families have joined and my child has enjoyed getting to know all the little babies to all the older kids. We miss that the pandemic means we‚Äòve had to put a hold on the regular multi-age play yard activities, spring and fall festivals, Friday merry go round rides, all students school bus field trips across the Golden Gate Bridge and nighttime pizza parties (a.k.a.: parents group, dads group and parents committee meetings), but new school activities like letter writing to other classrooms, movie night, sing- a-long Saturdays, and planting in the gardens within the enormous play yard and next door at Yerba Buena Gardens took their place over time.
Normal non-pandemic hours at YBG are just incredible for working parents (7:30am-6pm w/ extremely fewer holidays than most schools) though the hours are slightly reduced during the pandemic. I know former Somacc families that still talk about missing Somacc a year after leaving the country due to the pandemic.

reviews.author: Fanny Leon
reviews.text: We are very happy that our twins entered the worm classroom since they were 8 months old. It is a united family, the parents, teachers and educational and administrative staff, we are always happy and now we have another adventure that we will miss this second home üè° I recommend to a thousand this great child care.  our children learned a lot... thank you very much and blessings to the new families and generations üë®üë®

reviews.author: Jesse Lee
reviews.text: Nice little park with a merry go around ride for the kids.

reviews.author: Sally L
reviews.text: Yuanchen is truly a gem of a teacher! She is warm and gentle, the children absolutely love her. She has spent many years in childcare and understand the developmental needs of young children. As a teacher, she is a wonderful communicator, often working with parents to help with milestones such as potty training and managing sleep schedules. If a spot opens, RUN, and sign up!

reviews.author: Steph Ueng
reviews.text:
I am forever grateful to Yuanchen and the warm, loving teachers at Happy Garden for helping my daughter truly blossom under their care. If I had two words to describe her before she went at 18 months, it'd be: nonverbal, nonsocial. After just one month of being there, her vocabulary exploded (both Mandarin and English), and she has a best friend she runs out of the house (literally) to see everyday. We are six months in and this is one of the best parenting decisions we've ever made.

If you are looking for an in-home daycare that's Mandarin Immersion, led by the nicest humans alive who are constantly and proactively thinking about how to feed children's curiosity, happiness, and learning, look no further. We are so loathe to enroll her into school with her older brother at Presidio Knolls because we love the close proximity to our home, the caring environment, and how much the kids all get along and help each other grow (I really like the mixed ages). Logistically - the fact that they have homecooked food and I don't need to pack any meals is super helpful too - and Happy Garden has WAY less holidays / school closures than 99% of daycares I looked at.

Anyway, parenting is hard enough without being worried about your childcare situation. I have not worried one single bit since she's been here, and quite the opposite given her incredible growth in a short amount of time. She is so happy here and we are happy to be part of the Happy Garden community.

name: Mis Amigos Daycare Childcare Services in San Francisco

reviews.author: Nikki Rajnovich
reviews.text: Our son attended Mis Amigos from 6 months old to almost 2 years old (we only left due a move out of the area). We had the best experience during our time there. Our son thrived in the mixed age setting and small group size. Kai and Clara do a fantastic job of involving circle time learning, art, music, dancing, outdoor, and water play in the kiddies routine. They also love and care for the kiddies as their own it is apparent in how happy the children are every day. I highly recommend Mis Amigos for any family looking for childcare - it is truly a special, special place!

reviews.author: Keelin Linehan
reviews.text: We absolutely love Mis Amigos and feel so lucky to have such a great school in our neighborhood. Our 2-year-old daughter has been attending for a little over a year and comes home each day so happy and energized. She loves Kai as much as we do and I'd highly recommend Mis Amigos to anyone looking for a warm environment full of play-based learning.

reviews.author: Dylan DiBona
reviews.text: Our daughter has been going to Mis Amigos for over a year and we have nothing but great things to say about the experience. They provide an amazing level of care and engagement with the kids (that we get to see throughout each day via their mobile app). Our daughter loves going to Mis Amigos and talks about all of her friends and projects there non-stop.

reviews.author: Eaman Jahani
reviews.text: Mis Amigos a great local daycare. We loved the staff there and our daughter had great time there. We would not hesitate to recommend Mis Amigos to anybody who is moving to the area. The staff were very responsive, responsible and experienced. The place is managed very well and the kids have good activities.

reviews.author: Amanda Medrano-White
reviews.text: We absolutely loved our time at Mis Amigos.  Kai and Clara were very accommodating in how we transitioned into daycare, considering our child hadn't been around many people due to COVID.  We were nervous to put him into group care because of COVID, but they have a very strict policy and we felt comfortable knowing the other families had also signed an agreement to preserve the safety of the children.  Kai was super flexible and supportive when it came to starting, and we eased in in a way that set my child and us up for success.  My child loved it there!  It was reassuring to see him happy at drop off and sometimes didn't want to leave!  We also noticed his development just soared!  He really thrived in their care.  With the daycare being 6 kids, he got a lot of individual attention and it wasn't too overwhelming for him.  Kai and Clara engaged them in lots of outdoor play (they have a beautiful backyard area), and lots of activities and crafts.  We would have never left them if we didn't move out of the city.  I wish we could have taken them with us!  We miss them so much.

reviews.author: Blue W
reviews.text:
A heartfelt endorsement for Liu Ayi, Tommy, and Jiayu at Dolphin Stars.

Our connection to Dolphin Stars began with Liu Ayi, who was our daughter‚Äôs nanny starting at 8 months old. Though she was with us for just a year (she would have stayed longer if she hadn‚Äôt become a grandmother herself), we've remained close to her and her family for over five years‚Äîa testament to the deep bond and trust she built with us. Her warmth, dedication, and thoughtful approach to child-rearing left a lasting impact on our family. She now brings that same care and sensibility to Dolphin Stars.

Her daughter Jiayu and son-in-law Tommy run Dolphin Stars and have thoughtfully shaped it using their experience from respected institutions‚ÄîTommy, with a master‚Äôs in Early Childhood Education, draws from his time at Cypress School of San Francisco (formerly Cow Hollow Preschool), and Jiayu from her years at Little Footprints. They‚Äôve brought the best of what they‚Äôve learned into Dolphin Stars, creating a Mandarin immersion program rooted in play-based learning, social and emotional development, and genuine care

Our daughter, now five, does drop-ins at Dolphin Stars during school holidays and breaks (she‚Äôs currently at Presidio Knolls) and always comes home happy, engaged, and cared for. Even though the current cohort skews younger, Tommy and Jiayu are thoughtful in finding engaging activities and providing learning opportunities to ensure she's challenged.

When Liu Ayi transitioned out in 2021, we toured 13 childcare centers across the city. Most felt like businesses disguised by buzzwords and branding. Having gone through the search and from first hand experience, by contrast, Dolphin Stars feels grounded and personal. Tommy and Jiayu are not only skilled educators, they‚Äôre intuitive and open communicators. Their work reflects genuine care and a deep understanding of what children and families need. A true parenting partnership.

reviews.author: Alexandra LeFebvre
reviews.text: Our 6mo has been attending Dolphin Stars for a couple months and loves it! We get daily updates and photos on his activities and Tommy the director and the team are so knowledgeable about helping the littles grow and develop. They have been so patient and kind with my little guy and he is so happy to be there every day! Love the trips to the park and library during nice weather as well! Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Emily Campbell Snidal
reviews.text: We love dolphin stars! We love the focus on play based learning and the regular trips to the park and library are a plus. The teachers share frequent daily updates and photos and each day is full of fun and educational activities. Our son comes home from school every day happy and well fed. So happy we found dolphin stars!

reviews.author: Jonathan Cheung
reviews.text:
My son has been attending Dolphin Stars for a few weeks now. We get detailed daily reports with so many photos that help us feel connected even though we can‚Äôt be there.

The director, Tommy, has been incredibly communicative and attentive to our needs as parents.

I wish the location was less busy, but the quality of care is so good that im recommending them to my friends and family.

reviews.author: Bert Lin
reviews.text: Dolphin Stars is a new childcare on the block, and at first we were hesitant. However, after the tour, we learned the Director has over 5 years of experience at well reputable school and has a Master's degree in Early Education. The teachers in the center have decades of experience and they are patient with all the kids in the center. We will be enrolling our kiddos in the center and believe they will learn and grow together.

reviews.author: Miryam Garcia
reviews.text: My son attended this school for two years. Without a doubt, we couldn't have had a better experience. The teachers are very attentive and professional. I highly recommend it!

reviews.author: Esther Oh
reviews.text: Our experience at SOMACC is a bit more personal. About a year ago, my husband and I noticed that our son (now in the toddler class) was not meeting his communication milestones. A professional evaluation led to a diagnosis of Speech Delay. We sought help immediately through the resources that SOMACC connected us with, but to our dismay (due to the short supply of speech therapists in the city), we had to wait indefinitely (several months) to be paired with a speech therapist. Inevitably, we became very concerned that the developmental gap would widen between our son and his peers. In the meantime, my husband and I did our best at home to help encourage our son's language by being resourceful and accessing any materials that would teach us tools. However, it was the additional attention and support given to him by our son's teachers that motivated him to speak, even more. They would also send us video clips of his progress and keep track of each new word he spoke. We are happy to report that our son's speech development is now age-appropriate, and even excelling! Thank you to the teachers, who stood beside us throughout this journey. And thank you to the administration and staff for always making our family feel like a part of theirs.

reviews.author: Alex P
reviews.text: Amazing staff

reviews.author: Tiger Muda
reviews.text: Good place

reviews.author: Ula Popov
reviews.text: We love it!!

reviews.text: DONT LEAVE YOUR KIDS HERE!! They don‚Äôt care about your kids! This place is awful and definitely has to be investigated! Don‚Äôt believe in that 5 stars! The staff is terrible!! I definitely don‚Äôt recommend this place!

reviews.author: Lelia Glass
reviews.text:

reviews.author: Bonnie Nomunkhan
reviews.text:
One of THE best home daycares you could ask for.
Mrs. Nyamdorj is an excellent teacher who is absolutely wonderful with the children!

reviews.author: Olena Trush
reviews.text: Very happy with this place. Our daughter was well taken care of and would go there happily in the morning.

reviews.author: Shu Dar Yao
reviews.text:
Loving home daycare that my toddler son Gabriel enjoyed everyday - attentive and sensitive care from an experienced daycare provider, Mandarin immersion upon my request, homemade meals that were calibrated to dietary needs.

I can‚Äôt gush enough about how happy we were about Annie‚Äôs! She‚Äôs a small business owner that clearly adores infants and kids and take a lot of pride in her work.

reviews.author: Raymond a
reviews.text: The best daycare in the world

reviews.author: Elsy Reyes
reviews.text: The best place where I can leave my baby, I love the care, they are always attentive, I recommend it 100%, my baby has learned a lot, it's been months since he's been in daycare but I love the work that the person who takes care of him doesüëåüèª

reviews.author: Gorgeous C
reviews.text:
My daughter truly thrives here! MCC has been an incredible support system for our family. From the very beginning, their team has shown genuine care, professionalism, and a deep understanding of the challenges working families face when it comes to accessing quality child care. Their staff is responsive, compassionate, and always willing to go the extra mile to ensure families feel informed and supported. They do not treat families like numbers, they take the time to listen, advocate, and guide you through the process with patience and respect. It is clear that their mission is rooted in equity, community, and the well-being of children.

Because of Mission Child Care Consortium, our family has had greater stability, peace of mind, and confidence knowing our daughter is in a safe, nurturing, and enriching environment. Programs like this are essential for families who are balancing work, school, and caregiving, and MCC truly shows up for the community they serve.

I am extremely grateful for the work they do and highly recommend Mission Child Care Consortium to any family seeking reliable support, trustworthy guidance, and a team that genuinely cares.

reviews.author: Carmen Chen
reviews.text: My daughter went to preschool here at MCCC. I like the teachers and all the staff. They always have events like field trips and many things to do. I even refer my friends to enroll their children there! My specialist Amy is very nice and easygoing, she is always willing to help families and she goes above and beyond! 100% recommended!

reviews.author: Amy Liu
reviews.text: My daughter went here and she absolutely loved it! teachers and staffs are very nice and professional. I think the curriculum here is better than sfusd, they teach based on the child's level. my daughter learned how to write her name and all the ABC at the age of 4.

reviews.author: Yaneth Jovel
reviews.text: Great preschool. They do an amazing job with the kids.

reviews.author: Ms V
reviews.text:
PARENTS BEWARE!

I was appalled and scared for those tiny tots.  To hear adult staff from Mission Childcare CUSSING AT TODDLERS!

I would never refer this childcare since staff are so bold to speak to those poor babies this rudely in public!
