I had my own daycare and work for SFUSD and only want parents to know what I observed since the children can't always speak for themselves.

reviews.author: Nora Kurose
reviews.text: I cannot say enough good things about Tammy and the related Starry Family daycare. I have only one child who has been going to Tammy‚Äôs since she was five months old. As a first time mom, it was a big leap of faith to spend so much of the day away from my kid, but Tammy and her family quickly instilled a sense of confidence and trust that cannot be understated. When my daughter is in Tammy‚Äôs care, I feel as secure as though she were in my own - that is how much I trust and admire these women.  My daughter speaks so happily and with so much affection about Tammy and her family, but also all the other children at daycare. I am already sad knowing that someday she will age out to preschool instead of being with a team that so diligently teaches, engages, and loves her so much. Thank you, Tammy!

reviews.author: Stephanie Hua
reviews.text:
Our son has been going to Tammy since June 2023 and we love it! We started when my son was 1yr 9 mos and now he is almost
3.5yrs. Tammy is so patient and kind, and engaging with the kids. They go to playgrounds and take walks around North Beach, Chinatown, and Fisherman‚Äôs Wharf.

Before we started at Precious Babes I took care of my son full time and would see Tammy and her kids at our neighborhood playground all the time. I could see firsthand how good she was with them. Her sisters run another daycare in the unit below (same building) so they combine play lot when they go outside. I like that this allows for more social interactions amongst the children.

I speak Cantonese with her but we normally text in English. She mostly speaks Mandarin and Cantonese with my son during the day and I love that he is benefitting from the language exposure. There are a number of English only speaking families at the daycare and I believe they have no problems with communication.

I highly recommend Tammy!

name: Building Kidz of San Francisco on 20th Ave

reviews.author: Lindsay Meisel
reviews.text: My 4 year old has been at Building Kidz since it first opened, and we are SO happy there. We've built close relationships with all the teachers as well as other families. It's so clear that the owner, Sylvia, is driven to create a warm, caring, and connected community. My favorite part is that dance and music teachers come every week and lead a professional-level class for all the kids. Love seeing the videos of that!

reviews.author: Kelsey R
reviews.text: We've been happy with the care our son has received at BuildingKidz. The teachers are kind and seem to genuinely delight in the children and care about their growth. We love that the kids get to play outdoors nearly every day, and there are lots of fun toys and activities for them to engage with. The owner, Sylvia, is regularly onsite and involved with day-to-day operations.

name: UCSF at Kirkham Child Development Center
Tung Lok Early Childhood Learning Center

reviews.author: Jimmy & Ana Gubeladzes
reviews.text:
My daughter has been going to this center for almost 2.5 months(basically it opened up and she was one of the fist students there). She absolutely loves her school and we see how much she is loved there! She has become so advanced in this period, it‚Äôs unbelievable.

The team is very professional and this is reflected on our daughter. We have daily communication with them during drop off/pick up times and we are being updated about every important detail. We are very grateful to
Greg (site coordinator) and Cece (M‚Äô‚Äôs teacher) for being open and keeping us involved.

The place has just opened so everything is shiny and new there. The center has large sunny rooms and totally adorable furniture for kids to enjoy their day as well as a wonderful backyard where my daughter has so much fun every day. They provide kids with healthy food during the day,so the water bottle is the only thing you have to put in the backpack in the morning:)
The school has Reggio Emilia approach. They have classrooms from 3 months up to preschool period.
We started looking for a new center as M was not happy at the school where she was by that time. I was being told that kids don‚Äôt like daycares and that was normal, but that is not true! M loves the place from day 1, I can feel how happy she is there, she just loves her teacher Cece and the environment she is at.
Absolutely recommend this place to everyone!

reviews.author: Danielle Sandre
reviews.text: Best daycare in sunset!

reviews.author: Carol Rojas
reviews.text: Our son attended Oyunaa's Daycare for 1.5 years and he absolutely loved it there. Oyunaa and her team are so gentle with the kids and look after them with so much love and care. As parents, we felt very comfortable leaving our son in their care. We highly recommend Oyunaa's Daycare!

reviews.author: Anna Binnewies
reviews.text: Oyunaa's Daycare has truly been a loving and caring environment for our son for the past year and a half, starting when he was just 6 months old. It's heartwarming to see how eagerly he looks forward to each day, often running in without even a second glance back ‚Äì a testament to how happy he feels here. This small daycare's intimate setting has allowed our child to make great connections with the other kids and us with the other families. The playground right down the street is great too. Oyunaa has a flexible schedule and ample hours, with minimal holiday or vacation closures. They provide all meals and snacks which has been a huge convenience, and the festive holiday and birthday celebrations are really cute and special. We're incredibly grateful for Oyunaa's Daycare and highly recommend it to parents in search of a nurturing, safe and loving daycare.

reviews.author: Eug√©nie Le Moulec
reviews.text: My son attended Oyunaa‚Äôs daycare for 2.5 years starting at 3 months old. I cannot emphasize enough how great a care he got from Oyunaa and her team. They truly care about the children and their wellbeing. My son loved spending time there, he had a lot of fun and was cherished. It was heartbreaking for me when it was time for him to start preschool. My youngest son attended as well but only for a couple of weeks because we moved away, I wish we could have taken Oyunaa with us. If you need a daycare where you can leave your child with great peace of mind, this is the place!

reviews.author: Molly Stein
reviews.text: My son attended Oyunaa‚Äôs for 1.5 years starting at 16 months old when we moved to SF and I am so thankful I found Oyunaa‚Äôs Daycare! Oyunaa provides such a loving, nurturing environment. My son was so happy to go to ‚Äúschool‚Äù each day and all smiles at pick-up. He would come home and tell me about all the fun activities he did with his friends and he was constantly learning something new (letters, counting, songs, days of the week)! Oyunaa and the teachers really created a bond with him that helped him thrive too. My son would even run up and give Oyunaa a hug when he saw her! I was sad when my son started attending preschool after his little sister was born, because of how wonderful this place is. There‚Äôs no better care for your little one than Oyunaa‚Äôs!

reviews.author: Geri Hartkamp
reviews.text: Oyunaa‚Äôs Daycare is great! It is a wonderful place for your little ones. Oyunaa is thoughtful, kind, and very attentive to the children in her care. She and her staff are genuinely interested in each child doing well and learning new things. The home is very clean and safe. Breakfast and lunch are provided for toddlers (always smelled delicious, making me hungry at drop!) and a backyard for play. Oyunaa takes care to celebrate birthdays and holidays too. Location and schedule are also a huge plus for working parents.

name: Chinatown Community Children's Center North Beach

reviews.author: Toby Dixon
reviews.text: I cannot express my love for CHINATOWN COMMUNITY CHILDREN'S CENTER (CCCC) in North Beach. They are amazing people from top to bottom and run a fantastic organization. They hire the kindest and most caring staff. I have visited hundreds of times, dropped in, and peeped in the window, and they are so engaged and present with the kids. The staff speak both English and Mandarin and have little to no turnover. Both my native English-speaking daughters went there and can both talk and sing in Chinese. They have plenty of outdoor activities and learn so much about other cultures, the community, and each other. I highly recommend this school for ages 2-5 years old. We have all benefited socially and culturally from our girls attending CCCC.

reviews.author: Noelle C
reviews.text:
This preschool is amazing. I was looking at a few places and trying to figure out how to swing tuition for some of the well known schools in the area and so glad I didn‚Äôt. I‚Äôm really glad I found this for my daughter. She loves it here and the teachers are wonderful. The student to teacher ratio is so ideal being in the city that I wish all schools were like this. They also have an in-house cook that prepares all their meals. Mind you these meals are not just PB&J‚Äôs and some carrots. They provide a good mix of nutritious lunches that open up a child‚Äôs palette instead of the ‚Äúnormal‚Äù easy kid foods. My daughter tells me every night ‚ÄúI hope I can go to school tomorrow‚Äù and it literally warms my heart to know that she enjoys school that much. I was nervous when she first started. Will she make friends, are the teachers good, will they be able to help her adjust, will she hate it and not want to go back. But all those questions and worries disappeared after her first day.

The building itself looks like a normal apartment building and I was nervous at first but the minute she walked in and I heard all the kids saying hi I wasn‚Äôt worried about exterior looks at all. Come pick up time, she tells me she didn‚Äôt want to leave and at drop off....well she‚Äôs run off inside and I have to always tell her to come back and say goodbye to me. The COVID precautions are also most ideal. I 100% am fully appreciative of how well they take precaution here given that children don‚Äôt get the vaccine yet and are still at risk of contracting the virus. One pair of outdoor shoes and one indoor. This was key. Living in the city you should always want to have separate outdoor and indoor shoes. You don‚Äôt know what you‚Äôre stepping in and to ensure a clean space for the kids is great. Wash hands prior to entry and sharing is limited, this was a bit sad but of course it‚Äôs temporary and my daughter has adjusted to it. They also have a very diverse class which is ALWAYS a plus.

reviews.author: Abby Sukarto
reviews.text: Smily Daycare has been a great place for my son since he  was 4 months old.  There is flexibility in pick up time that reduces lots of stress as a working mother, overnight nannying provided even with such short notice, and structure that allow my son to stick to routine as well as be independent.  Both my son and I greatly appreciate Grace and her whole family that we get to know for the last 2 years.

reviews.author: Jeff Leopando
reviews.text: We're very pleased with this daycare for our 10-month-old son. The flexible drop-off and pickup times are incredibly helpful for our work schedules. The carers, whom we've known for years, are trustworthy, knowledgeable, and nurturing. Their excellent communication keeps us well-informed about our son's day, meals, naps, and milestones. What we value most is how much our son enjoys being there - his excitement when we arrive each morning speaks volumes about the positive environment. The daycare provides a good balance of care and fun activities, contributing to our son's development. We've noticed improvements in his social skills and motor development since he started. Overall, we feel confident in the quality of care and would recommend this daycare to parents looking for a reliable, caring, and stimulating option for their little ones!

reviews.author: Jennifer Hellawell
reviews.text: Grace has created such a loving and supportive environment in her home. She maintains a clean space with age appropriate and enriching activities for the kids. My daughter absolutely thrived there and Grace has truly become a member of our own family. In addition to be being so nurturing, she is very flexible with drop off and pickup times which is so hard to find and so important for working parents. I simply can‚Äôt recommend her highly enough and am happy to serve as a reference for other prospective parents. May we all have people like Grace in our village to raise our children! üíó

reviews.author: Dylan Tang
reviews.text: Our family has known Mrs. Samantha for 6 years and we were so lucky to have her as my kid‚Äôs first teacher. My son has grown and learned a lot during the year with Mrs. Samantha. Mrs. Samantha is very nurturing and patient. I love Mrs. Samantha‚Äôs teaching style. With her guidance and encouragement, my son was less shy and more eager to talk to others. He blossomed and was an explorer who always wanted to try new things. We hope Mrs. Samantha continue teaching other students to guide them to success!

reviews.author: Natalie Marquardt
reviews.text: My daughter has attended Bernal Infant and Child Care with Erica and Marc since she was just 6mo old and she is 3 now. Nobody prepares you for how difficult it is to drop your baby off at a daycare and return to work. Erica and Marc truly the most incredible caretakers  - they are professional, empathetic and amazing teachers. My daughter absolutely LOVES going to school. She comes back happy, loving and confident every single day she spends with Erica and Marc. They have gone above and beyond to accommodate my requests to help my daughter feel as comfortable and safe as possible... they truly go above and beyond. Look no further if you want your child to be loved, safe and enriched with learning activities.

reviews.author: Elizabeth Ubaldo
reviews.text:
My husband and I love having our son under the care of Erica and Marc. We started our journey with them during the pandemic with our oldest son who just turned 2. He blossomed in the environment and they even motivated him to get potty trained. Erica and Marc really take the time to think of engaging activities for the kids of all ages.

We had no doubt that our youngest would follow suit. He's just a little over 1 year old and he already is much more social and talkative.

We are so greatful for the care and piece of mind they provide for us especially as two working parents. Thank you so much!

reviews.author: Muamer Cisija
reviews.text:
Our son was at Bernal Infant and Child Care for around 18 months.

He had the best experience possible with Erica and Marc. They are wonderful humans, really are passionate about what they do but also very professional at the same time.

They basically helped raise our kid, from how to engage with other kids, to potty training but also fun things like painting and engaging with animals.

Love that place. We have a second child and plan to enroll him as well.

Cannot recommend enough!

reviews.author: Brian Conlin
reviews.text: I can't say enough about Bernal Infant and Child Care. They provided a great environment of fun and education for my daughter over the past two years. It's readily apparent how much Erica and Marc love the kids and do an amazing job of making a strong group while tailoring activities and lessons to individual ages and developmental phases.

reviews.author: Kathryn Zyskowski
reviews.text: We had the BEST time here. My daughter would ask to go to ‚ÄúMs Erica‚Äôs‚Äù house on the weekends and when I would say she could go in Monday would erupt in a big ‚ÄúHooray!‚Äù They covered healthy snacks and food and brought the kids to do all sorts of fun activities in the neighborhood. Would highly, highly recommend.

reviews.author: Gia Punjabi
reviews.text: Can't say enough wonderful things about Leah and this very special daycare facility. We feel so lucky to have enrolled our little one here from the age of 12-months onwards. She's thriving, happy and safe. Don't think twice - if you're able to secure a spot here for your little one, I would highly recommend you take it.

reviews.author: Wesley Zheng
reviews.text: Leah is super nice and caring! Sent our boy there when he was 1 yo and Leah took good care of him.

name: Little LYNC Preschool and Family Center

reviews.author: pelin arslan
reviews.text:
We love Little LYNC!! It is a lovely school with lovely teachers and friends.

My son has attended the school since he was 2 years old. All of his teachers from caterpillar to butterfly were amazing ‚Äì highly dedicated, engaged and caring. The administration has been responsive and flexible with our requests.

My son is always excited to go to school in the mornings. He loves his friends and engages with them in plays, crafts, outdoors, circle times, science experiments and many more different activities. I am impressed with the creative environment and curriculum they provide to teach kids in a fun way. I learn a lot as a parent, too :)

Little LYNC has been an inclusive and diverse community for us and getting to know the other parents in occasional events has also been a great experience.

My son is very happy there. So we are. I highly recommend Little LYNC who is looking for a smaller scale, nurturing and play-based education.

reviews.author: Elizabeth Durham
reviews.text: The teachers at Little Lync made school the most positive experience for our son and our family. This was his first experience with school and they were welcoming, warm, caring and have really helped our son grow. He is excited about going and we can see he is learning new things, both educational, and personal with his peers. The smaller atmosphere Little Lync can offer has been a great fit for us. We are very happy with our choice!

reviews.author: EJ Amanda Diamante
reviews.text: We have been a part of the Little Lync family since my son was 2 years old. From the beginning, the teachers were so understanding, caring and helped him transition into daycare. It's a lovely community and my son has met great friends. Overall we have had a great experience and would recommend Little Lync for anyone looking for a caring and nurturing environment.

reviews.author: Khristine Atienza Walker
reviews.text:
We absolutely love Little LYNC!  My daughter has been attending this school since August 2020. She loves her teachers and her friends, and she seriously comes home happy (and full of stories) everyday!

I was really nervous to put my daughter back in school at a time when Covid was raging.  The teachers really put me at ease when I toured the school, and the owner (Timberly) was so gracious in allowing me to decide when to put her in. She wanted to make sure I was comfortable, and I really appreciated that.

One of the great things about this school is the community of parents who band together to help teachers when they need it. For example, during the big fires of 2020 (when the skies turned orange), the parents pitched in to buy the school a bigger air filter.

By far, the very best thing about Little LYNC is the teachers. They are all AMAZING! I am so grateful for them for teaching our kids, keeping them safe, and loving them like they‚Äôre own.

To Amy, Melody, Carina, Marlene, and Rose ‚Äî Thank you for everything you all do!

We‚Äôve been very happy here and would highly recommend it!

reviews.author: Matt & Anne
reviews.text: We have been really happy with our experience at Little LYNC over the last year. The kids are always happy and excited at pick up time and in the photos that get posted to the daily class dojo website. They do lots of fun arts and crafts and activities - the teachers are so creative including making a ballot box to understand voting, and the school celebrated Lunar New Year and St Patrick‚Äôs Day in addition to the usual Halloween, Thanksgiving, and Christmas events. More importantly, the teachers are wonderful and learned how to care for our child with insulin pump dependent diabetes so well that we trust them completely. Thank you Miss Amy, Melody, Carina, Marlene and Rose!

name: Hands and Hearts Daycare and Preschool

reviews.author: Victoria Z
reviews.text: My daughter had Kate as her nanny when she was one to two years old, and I can wholeheartedly recommend Kate as a daycare or preschool teacher! Kate is a warm and caring person who loves kids and cares for them. My daughter would crawl and later run to her every time she came over. Kate was able to start playing with the little one quickly, so mom (me) could leave with zero tears or worries, which is so important at this early age. She played with her, read books to her, fed her, and walked with her outside. I also credit Kate with being able to teach my daughter to fall asleep in her own bed for the daytime nap, since previously, she was only able to take a nap outside in a stroller, and would cry if she were put in bed during the day instead. Kate created a warm and friendly atmosphere, and my daughter felt loved and cared for, and we always looked forward to Kate's visits. I am confident that Kate's daycare will be a great success and kids will be very happy there!

reviews.author: Kim
reviews.text: Our child really likes Kate ‚Äî she‚Äôs very warm and approachable.

reviews.author: huyen nguyen
reviews.text:
My son has been lucky to spend almost 2 years learning and growing at Panda garden family child care. Michelle and her staff provided such a great experience for our son. They truly love all kids. My son loves going to school and stays there like his second home. We‚Äôre very grateful to Michelle and her staff for all help.
I highly recommend this childcare for all parents. This is the place they are most likely to feel at home

reviews.author: Claire Torkington
reviews.text: As a first-time parent, I truly couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better daycare experience. Michelle was incredibly supportive throughout key milestones‚Äîfrom teething to potty training‚Äîand always made me feel confident and informed. My daughter absolutely adored her teachers, running in every morning with hugs and excitement. It was such a comfort knowing she was safe, well cared for, and engaged in fun, enriching activities every day. The consistent routine at daycare also made a big difference at home, helping us establish good habits. While we‚Äôre sad to be moving on, we feel so grateful to Michelle and the team for preparing our daughter so well for the next chapter. We‚Äôll miss them!

reviews.author: Emily Hui
reviews.text: I can't say enough good things about this daycare. Michelle and her teachers are kind, supportive, and attentive. Everyday my son is excited to go to school and when he comes home, he tells me about his day and friends. I truly appreciate the photos that Michelle sends over throughout the day and love the activities that encourage learning, gross motor skills and play. Thank you so much Michelle & team!

reviews.author: Annie Liou
reviews.text: My son just graduated from Panda Garden (3yo) and we were so sad to leave! He is currently at a new preschool and keeps telling us how much he misses his "old school". He started at 14 months old and as first time parents, my husband and I were more nervous than he was. He was a little hesitant the first few days of drop off but after that he kept saying "school" and was so excited to go! The owner, Michelle, and her staff took such good care of our son and treated him like their own family. They provide home cooked meals (breakfast, lunch, and afternoon snack), help with potty training, and keep us updated on everything he did at school. Our son also can now speak Mandarin fluently! I speak Mandarin as well but he comes home saying phrases that I don't even know which is so impressive to us! Sending him to Panda Garden was honestly the best decision we've made and cannot recommend them enough! If we do have a second child, he/she will also definitely be attending Panda Garden as soon as he/she can start! Thank you so much again Michelle and staff for the best daycare experience for our son and us as parents!!

reviews.author: Kokoro X
reviews.text:
We are so happy to find Panda Garden online, and our son has been here since the pandemic when he was a little older than a year.  We were skeptical and concerned about how our child would do in a daycare environment during that very special period.  From the moment we did a tour, Panda Garden banished all our worries and concerns, and I cannot brag enough about how great Michelle and her team are.
*Michelle and her team are very loving, caring, and attentive. We love that we receive daily photos of our son and consistent updates throughout the day via the Brigthwheel app.  We are always aware how our son is doing every day.
*Strong curriculum with good balance of education, intellectual stimulation, creativities, motor skills, and social skills. Weekly curriculum is shared with all parents through the app and we know exactly what our son is learning at school so that we can also enhance his learning at home.
*Culture learning through hands on projects, such as homemade mooncake for moon festival, cookie baking for Christmas. Michelle and her team also package the goodies for kids to bring home. Imagine the joy of tasting the food our little one makes at such young age!
*A safe environment that is always clean and organized with good hygiene. Michelle and her team always try their best to protect the health of our community.
*Monthly menu is shared via the app. Nutritious organic homemade hot foods and healthy snacks are provided from morning to afternoon, which make our life much easier. The only meal we need to prepare for our son is dinner.
*The one-on-one milestone conference meetings with Michelle always greatly help us understand the development progress of our son from multiple aspects, so that we are able to work on different areas to help our son grow.  It also shows Michelle and her team really pay close attention and note down the details of each kid.
Everyday we drop off our son, we know he is in great hands. We will conclude with much praise and gratitude for Michelle and her team that love our son as much as we do and for everything they do for him. We highly recommend Panda Garden!

reviews.author: Nora Garnier
reviews.text:
We've been sending our daughter to Amy's Family Child Care since she was 7 months old. Amy is a truly gifted care provider, and we have loved watching our daughter blossom into a happy, confident toddler under her care. The first thing you notice about Amy is her warmth, which instantly puts our daughter at ease. Amy has a genuine passion for early childhood education and it is obvious that this is her calling. She sends numerous photos throughout the day, and I love seeing all the fun activities my daughter and the other kids do, such as playing with blocks, finger painting, kicking soccer balls around, playing with musical instruments, and reading books. Amy takes the kids outside every day (weather permitting) to run and play in a protected, fenced-in field, which we love. Also, Amy has a team of equally stellar classroom aides who we feel very comfortable with. Finally, the hours are very convenient: 8 am to 5:30 pm Monday through Friday.

I can't say enough good things about Amy and her daycare; she feels like family at this point.

reviews.author: Weiwei Rao
reviews.text:
We discovered Amy's daycare through online research when our daughter was one year old. We were looking for a facility that was close to home, bilingual, and run by people who viewed childcare as more than just a business.

Amy and her team provided exactly the kind of care and attention we hoped for. Over the past year and a half, our daughter has transformed from a fairly reserved and cautious child into one who is curious, bubbly, and eager to connect with her friends and teachers. While much of this growth is natural development, we know that environment matters tremendously, and Amy's facility has provided the nurturing atmosphere our daughter needed outside of home.

Amy's dedication extends well beyond daily care activities. She celebrates each child's birthday, organizes special holiday meals (like their Thanksgiving turkey lunch!), and holds graduation ceremonies. Watching videos of these events always brought us joy and reassurance that our daughter was building meaningful connections and a sense of community.

This supportive environment has benefited our family in unexpected ways too‚Äîwe've formed friendships with other parents and regularly attend each other's birthday parties and social gatherings.

Amy truly serves as a second mother to all the children in her care. We are grateful for the significant role she has played in our daughter's growth and development. We hope she continues to provide this invaluable service to our community and to the many families who will have the opportunity to receive her support.

reviews.author: Rongze Olivia Lu
reviews.text: Sandra and Amy are really caring. My son is very sensitive and not easy to adjust to new environment. I am so glad and relieved he was so happy at Amy‚Äôs place. He made close friends he misses them very much after leaving. They offered breakfast , lunch and afternoon snacks, which makes our life so easy. They are so attentive to kids‚Äô individual needs. My son has so many wonderful memories there! Amy‚Äôs place is always a special place in our heart!

reviews.author: Yue
reviews.text:
We absolutely love Amy's Family Childcare and feel so fortunate to have found her. Our older child started when she was almost 1 and stayed for more than two years.

From day one, Amy made sure we were always in the loop about our daughter's daily schedule, mood, and activities. She would send pictures and updates throughout the day, so it felt like our daughter was never far away. Over the two years, Amy consistently shared photos and videos, helping us stay connected. At pickup, she would always give us thoughtful details about how the day went, as well as share sweet and funny stories.

Our daughter sometimes has a strong "opinion" of her own, but Amy was incredibly patient and guided her with so much care. Amy also helped her learn to share with others and manage her emotions when she got frustrated, which has been such a big help to us as parents. When I was pregnant with our second child, our daughter would always ask me to carry her down the stairs, but after Amy talked to her, she started saying, "Mommy can't hold me, but we can hold hands." It was a small thing, but this was how much Amy's words resonated with her.

Amy always went above and beyond. During my pregnancy, Amy went out of her way to accommodate our schedule when my husband was out of town. She sent photos and videos to the grandparents and grandaunts who were staying with us to help, knowing how much they missed the kids. It's those personal touches that make Amy's care so special.

On top of everything else, Amy provides nutritious breakfast, lunch, and dinner for the kids. It's such a rare offering and makes our mornings and evenings so much easier. Knowing our daughter is well-fed during the day has been a huge relief--we only need to give her milk in the morning, and we don't have to scramble to make dinner after a long day.

Amy strikes the perfect balance between nurturing and learning. The teacher-to-child ratio means that every child gets individual attention. Not only does Amy and her team take care of the essentials like feeding and napping, but they also engage the kids in story time, music, and free play. Our daughter learned so much Chinese (and English!) while she was there, and she loved singing songs in both languages.

Amy has built such a warm and welcoming community at her daycare. She celebrates each child's birthday and throws fun holiday parties for events like Chinese New Year, Easter, and Halloween. Our daughter made wonderful friends at Amy's, and we've even become close with other families there.

Our daughter has since graduated from Amy's to start preschool, but for the first month, she would cry every morning, saying she wanted to go back to Amy's. Whenever she gets the chance to reunite with Amy and her friends, she's beyond excited.

reviews.author: Esther
reviews.text:
Our son attended Amy's daycare 4 days a week between 10 months and 2.5 years old -- almost 2 years! We highly recommend Amy's, and would give more than 5 stars if we could. After moving to a preschool that is underwhelming, I've realized how blessed we were to be at Amy's and how high she's set the bar for our future school expectations. Here's why:

1. Social & emotional skills: As an only child, our son has had fewer opportunities to interact with other kids. At Amy's, he learned how to take turns, share, wait, and be "gentle" with kids instead of hitting etc through adult-facilitated activities and free play. He always looked happy when we picked him up, running around and climbing the indoor gym toys. We are so glad he's build some foundational social skills for life while at Amy's.

2. Health & sanitation: Our son didn't get sick the entire first year of his life, and had only minor colds + one stomach bug at Amy's. We caught covid outside of Amy's and needed to stay out for a few weeks, and take several tests to show we were no longer contagious. The adult staff always wore masks indoors and outdoors, and they covid tested themselves frequently. As mentioned in the other reviews, I always saw the staff vigorously cleaning the daycare at the end of the day.

3. Kids well-fed w/ nutritious meals: Unlike many daycares and preschools, Amy provides breakfast, lunch, dinner, and 2 snacks for all the kids. The cuisine is mostly Chinese w/ some other kid-friendly foods mixed in. We would always get reports about how our son ate multiple portions of lunch and dinner because he's a hungry boy!

4. Long, deep naps: Our son slept 2-3 hours a day at Amy's, which meant he was healthier and happier in the afternoons and evenings with us. They keep the daycare dark with music playing, and help kids who wake up early move to a different location so they don't disturb the ones who are still napping.

5. Academic & language learning: Our son was diagnosed with a speech delay early in his life. By the time he graduated from Amy's he was no longer speech delayed and could speak both English and Chinese. He learned shapes, colors, ABCs, and numbers at Amy's and probably a lot more that I'm unaware of!

6. Going above and beyond: Through diaper rashes, potty training, and more, Amy helped us troubleshoot things inside and outside of daycare. Our son was potty trained in a week and a half, thanks to Amy's consistency with our methods at school. Diaper rashes disappeared more quickly at Amy's than they did at home! Communication was detailed and daily with photos, texts as needed, and an end of day summary. Our questions were always answered in detail, because Amy or the other caregivers were present and engaged the whole day with the kids. Every morning, Amy or another caregiver greeted our son with a huge hug and smile, making him feel comfortable and loved. They cared for our son like he was family.

Through our partnership with Amy's daycare, our son has built a strong foundation of good health, attached relationships, and rapidly developing language & cognition. It is everything we could have wanted and more. You will not regret visiting, applying, and joining Amy's.

reviews.author: Erica Reyes
reviews.text:
Angelica is so sweet and caring. We started bringing our daughter when she was 5 months old and she made us feel so comfortable. Her daycare is very clean, with age appropriate toys. She‚Äôs extremely communicative, which I love. My Spanish is just ok, but she takes the time to text me using google translate - which works great for us. I can‚Äôt wait until our daughter starts eating more solids, because Angelica cooks everything for them! My favorite part about her is how she loves my child
Like her own. That‚Äôs the most important thing to me in finding the right childcare. Would highly recommend!

reviews.author: Kristy F
reviews.text: Angelica (owner) is the kindest, sweetest, most loving caregiver I could imagine. From my first time meeting Angelica I could just tell she has such a love for children. When I think of who I trust in my village, Angelica is one of those people. My daughter loved Angelica so much and I was so sad when she ‚Äúgraduated‚Äù to preschool because she wouldn‚Äôt see Angelica every day. But we hope to keep seeing Angelica because our family loves her so much! She will take amazing care of your children.

reviews.author: Connor Skelly
reviews.text: If you are looking for a daycare for your child, I‚Äôd highly recommend Angelica! Our daughters absolutely loved their time with her. She‚Äôs so friendly and energetic and supportive. She clearly loves with she does. She also has tons of experience. Thank you for everything, Angelica!!!

reviews.author: My-Thuan Tran
reviews.text: Angelica took wonderful care of our son at her previous daycare. She was incredibly thoughtful and loving to him and the other children. We never worried about the care he was getting. Thank you, Angelica!

reviews.author: Ana Huante (AnaDIY)
reviews.text: The daycare is gorgeous! And Angie is just wonderful! I will soon hace my baby and uf I was ro choose and trust someone with my beloved child would be her! Her soul is a blessing to the children!

reviews.author: Astkhik Levantian
reviews.text: Liliana's family daycare has been amazing. My daughter Sona started going October 2021 and it's been a wonderful experience. She enjoys her time there and loves Liliana, Nino, and Ira. They are caring and attentive and do a fabulous job. Some of the activities they do are arts and crafts, music time, outside play in their big backyard/play area, reading books, and yoga! Sona has grown and learned so much at the daycare and I'm forever grateful for their phenomenal care and skills they teach. They recently celebrated Sona's 2nd birthday and even got her a gift. Super thoughtful and loving team! Highly recommend.

reviews.author: Neli Ermamatov
reviews.text: Honestly by far the best daycare. Liliana takes care of all of the kids as if they were her own. The food is always freshly made. I leave my child with her knowing he is in great hands! My son has a blast during music time and also loves the arts and crafts that Lilana does with the kids. 100% recommend this daycare to all the mommies out there that are looking for a safe place for their child.

reviews.author: Galya Sf
reviews.text: Liliana has cared for our daughter since she was a year old - she was great with her and learned a lot from the daycare. I would recommend the daycare to anyone

reviews.author: Jen Morgan
reviews.text: Diana and her family provided amazing care for our two children over 3 years. We are so grateful for the love, affection, and security they gave to us; it made it so much easier to drop our kids off. Our babies still love giving big hugs to Diana and her family when we see them around. Thank you!

reviews.author: Nikki San Miguel
reviews.text: Diana‚Äôs daycare has been a godsend for our family! We‚Äôve been with them for over 3 years now and the amount of love and attention they give to our two babies is so wonderful‚Äîboth of our kids didn‚Äôt cry on their first days which is a testament to how amazing they are with children. They also take them on adventures all around North Beach everyday so they get to experience so much than just a play room. Our kids come home content with big smiles every day. They are also wizards and effortlessly get our little ones to take long naps and eat their vegetables üòÜ (whereas we struggle with both so much at home!!!). Would highly recommend them to anyone looking for a loving environment for their babies and toddlers.

reviews.author: James Lu
reviews.text: Highly recommend Stella's home daycare! We started at Stella's daycare full time when our son was 6 months old, and she takes very good care of him. Stella sends us updates and photos throughout the day that really help put us at ease. I also really appreciate the flexible times for drop-off and pickup.

reviews.author: J.Y. Lim
reviews.text:
We are beyond grateful to have found Blooming Stars as our son‚Äôs daycare. Transitioning to daycare after 19 months of being cared for by family was a big step for him, but thanks to Stella‚Äôs  (daycare owner) warmth and attentiveness, he only cried on the first day.

She keeps us updated throughout the day with pictures and even helps him nap‚Äîno small feat since he‚Äôs a challenging sleeper! Stella takes him outside everyday every day, giving him opportunities to socialize with other children. Every Wed/Thu they attend story time and music classes at Salesforce park, which my son loves.

These days, my son runs to Stella with excitement every morning‚Äîsomething that brings me so much peace as a working parent. Knowing that he is in such caring hands makes all the difference. I cannot recommend Stella highly enough for any parent looking for a nurturing and engaging caregiver!

name: Modern Education Family Childcare - Mission Bay

location.street: will be provided upon tour request, 1180 4th St Unit number

reviews.author: Joyce Zhang
reviews.text:
We chose Auntie Siu's Modern Family Education in Mission Bay because of amazing reviews from friends, and she exceeded our already high expectations. We started sending my son to Auntie Siu's when he was around 8 months old and his younger sister at around the same age. Whenever I drop my kids off, they run excitedly inside and I know they are being loved and cared for as if they were at home. It makes me happy to see all their milestones and developments and how safe and secure they feel with Auntie Siu, who is now like family to us.

The daycare is in a safe and convenient location in Mission Bay, on the 2nd floor inside a doorman guarded building. There is a spacious outdoor turf area and a private outdoor patio connected to it. The inside is large and spacious, with everything childproof and many different toys, puzzles, books, and arts and crafts for the children.

My kids love spending time there, and receive so much love and care from all three of the adult caretakers. I get daily text messages with pictures and updates, which is a good way for me to practice my Chinese as well.

The daycare prepares healthy, home-cooked Chinese food without salt or sugars and makes sure the children have an assortment of different activities and games, from art and drawing, to daily song and dance. I really appreciate the Chinese immersion (Auntie Siu speaks both Cantonese and Mandarin) and especially the true love and care that she and all the other caretakers exhibit. She knows each child for his or her individual personality and attributes, and gives good parenting and healthcare advice given her decades of experience.

Modern Education Family Childcare truly goes above and beyond. Auntie Siu throws birthday parties for each child on his/her birthday and other themed parties for various holidays, always managing to cook a delicious Chinese feast. She dresses them up for Chinese New Year and has parents bring Halloween costumes so the children can dress up for Halloween and other holidays as well.

Even now that my son is in preschool and has graduated, he always looks forward to returning during school holidays. We are still friends with many of the families whose kids attended daycare at the same time.  Auntie Siu is like family, and we are very grateful to her.

reviews.author: Bianca Chen Hsiao
reviews.text: My daughter has been with Auntie Siu for the past year, starting from 6 months of age. It has been a truly amazing experience. She makes daycare feel like family. So many home-cooked treats, joyful birthday and holiday celebrations, but most importantly, she provides a loving and gentle environment for all of the kids. She speaks Chinese (Cantonese) to the children (an immersive experience that we value highly), and communicates regularly via text message with pictures from the day. I honestly would want to have another baby so Auntie Siu could look after them, and I cannot recommend her enough!

reviews.author: Veronica Antonova
reviews.text: Siu is a caring provider who feels more like a family member. She‚Äôs warm and instantly connects with little ones. Home cooked meals, outdoor time throughout the day, family festival celebrations, lots of play and reading, and learning Chinese. Love Siu and her family. Our kid still asks for her by name 2 years after we stopped daycare, now that she‚Äôs school age, and refuses to let anyone else watch her if we need to leave her for a few hours in care at odd hours. Siu is our go to for childcare!

reviews.author: James Harvey
reviews.text:
After two kids and five years, this past Friday was our last day at Modern Education Family Childcare, as our younger child is moving on to preschool. Auntie Siu has become a beloved part of our family, and we'll miss her dearly. She's gone above and beyond anything I've ever heard of at any other childcare, and her love for her kids is obvious. From working with us to manage our son's allergies to thoughtfully sending home-cooked food home to my wife when she was pregnant, she's been a gift to our family.

In the covid-era reopening, they've been particularly careful, and it's clear that they're following all precautions, from consistent mask use and disinfecting hands and surfaces to avoiding social contact outside of childcare hours. If you're lucky enough to join MEFC, I can't recommend them highly enough.

reviews.author: Mikaela Burns
reviews.text:
Our daughter was in Yandan's care from 6 months to almost 2 1/2 years, and she is truly one of our daughter's favorite people. As a nervous first time mom, Yandan provided a gentle and safe environment for my infant, and had our daughter taking a bottle no problem, which had been a previous challenge. Yandan provided a nurturing and explorative environment for our daughter to continue to grow and learn into toddlerhood. She went from being the youngest of the groups to the oldest child with a new group, and the transition was seamless. Yandan kept her stimulated and learning at each stage with daily park outings, art projects and other activities. Yandan has a great way of helping the kids interact and build connections, there were always lots of smiles and hugs at pickup.

Yandan is a great communicator, she sends daily photos and has a tracker sheet with sleep, diaper changes and meals/snacks that she shares at the ends of each day. She cooks fabulous and balanced lunches with a variety of fresh fruits and vegetables.

It was so hard to say goodbye, we will miss her dearly and cannot recommend her enough.

reviews.author: Jordan Hod
reviews.text:
Yandan's Family Day Care holds a special place in our hearts. From the moment our daughter walked through that door at 5 months, the care, attention, and love she received at Yandan's daycare were exceptional. With Yandan we found more than just a safe place for our daughter ‚Äì we discovered a nurturing and enriching environment that truly felt like an extension of our family.

Yandan forms an excellent bond with children and encourages their individual curiosity and development. Our daughter flourished with Yandan. The warm and loving care she received every day made it feel like a home away from home.

Moreover, the open communication, regular updates, and photos kept us connected to our daughter‚Äôs daily experiences and needs, and we were able to construct a good routine for her together. Yandan is highly flexible and communicative. She understands the different needs and habits of the little ones, assisting them in transitioning from home to daycare and facilitating their growth through fun experiences.

I highly recommend Yandan‚Äôs family daycare!

reviews.author: Angie
reviews.text:
my family and i absolutely loved sending our daughter to Yandan's Daycare. we feel so grateful for the care, love, and attention she received every single day! Yandan is incredibly caring, attentive, and experienced with early childhood care and development. our daughter thrived there.

the food was another standout: fresh, healthy, and home-cooked meals that made us feel confident she was well nourished. we also loved how Yandan encouraged independence in age-appropriate ways, helping our daughter build confidence, language skills, and an outgoing personality.

the overall environment was safe, positive, and full of laughters and genuine joy. our daughter thriving socially and emotionally, and we couldn‚Äôt be happier with her growth.

if you‚Äôre looking for a daycare that feels like a second home, and an incredible super-mommy caretaker, Yandan is best choice.

reviews.author: alessandra mosenifar
reviews.text: My family and I absolutely loved sending our son to YanDan's family childcare. We feel so lucky and grateful for the care our son received there! We honestly wish we could send him there forever and never go to preschool! Everyday Henri would get home cooked meal, go to the park and form deep friendships with the other 2 children who attended. We saw him grow and develop so much over the course of his time there (he started at around 15 months). YanDan was also such a great communicator and texted us photos daily! We can't wait to send our second baby there in a couple months! If anyone is ready to get their child out of the home, but not quite ready for big daycare setting, YanDan's family child care is the perfect fit.

reviews.author: Laura Martinez
reviews.text: I couldn‚Äôt be happier with Yandan‚Äôs daycare. She is incredibly kind and caring, and my son, who is typically very attached to me, immediately warmed up to her. He has a fantastic time with Yandan and the other children. Yandan consistently sends us updates and photos, keeping us informed about his day and making us feel reassured and comfortable. It was difficult for us to part ways, and we still miss her greatly.

reviews.author: Earl Dos Santos
reviews.text:
We had the most wonderful experience at Ella's Second Home. Both our daughters transitioned seamlessly to going to daycare there. They learned how to nap and play with others, and always were happy at the end of the day. Our kids were even eating soup with a spoon at just over a year old -- all because Ella's home empowers the kids to do things like that.

Rimma and Ella are so loving to the kids, and really prepare them for preschool. Those transitions have been smooth after leaving Ella's - in fact, each kid's new school mentioned how well-prepared they were in terms of cleaning up after themselves, playing with others, etc.

My partner and I highly recommend Ella's for families close to the Sunset. You won't regret it!

reviews.author: Christoffer Klemming
reviews.text:
Ella's Second Home has truly been like a home for our son. The staff Ella, Rima and Emily really care for and love every toddler like it's their own.

There hasn't been a day in the almost 1.5 years our son has been there that he's been sad or upset to go there in the morning. It anything, he doesn't want to leave when we come pick him up!

They have a great backyard for outdoor play with a bunch of great toys, slides, castles and cars. They make good food every day that the kids love and they make a huge occasion for every birthday.

Two times a week there a soccer coach that comes and teaches the kid soccer, and they have a great music teacher that gets everyone roaring. Plus, they make special events throughout the year!

All in all, we have really loved having our son here and our daughter will start in a few months! üëç

reviews.author: Michel D
reviews.text:
My family has had the privilege of entrusting our children to this daycare, and we couldn't be happier with the experience. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted by Silvia warm and friendly staff who made me and our child feel right at home. Silvia has been running daycare facilities in San Francisco for the past 20 years.

My oldest child, in particular, spent a remarkable three joyful years at this daycare and has a bond with the staff, it's always a special moment to stop and say Hello. My youngest has been enrolled for a few months and has benefited from the social interactions and the nurturing environment. The staff members are not only professional and well-trained but also genuinely caring and attentive to each child's needs. They offer Spanish immersion for the kids. I appreciated the daily reports and photos I receive, which assures me that my child was having a blast and thriving.

One of the standout features of this daycare is the nutritious and diverse (included in the price!!) meals they provide. They also have a garden with small structures onsite. They love to celebrate holidays and birthdays! You will be overwhelmed with art projects! It's evident that they prioritize the health and well-being of the children in their care.

Overall, this daycare exceeded my expectations in every way, and I highly recommend it to any parent looking for a caring, safe, and enriching environment for their child.

reviews.author: Steph Beadman
reviews.text:
Our 10 month old daughter attended Silvia‚Äôs daycare earlier this year and we absolutely loved it. Silvia is a caring, warm, and flexible caregiver and she has two helpers who are just as wonderful. Beyond her character, there are three other reasons we love Silvia:

1. She works on ‚Äúprojects‚Äù with the kids, which are Montessori-style activities that combine play and education. Our daughter came home with the cutest Father‚Äôs Day card as an outcome of one of the projects ü•π

2. She provides timely and informative updates to the parents. When she suspected our daughter might have a slight sensitivity to a strawberry, she called right away to keep us informed of how she was monitoring it. She provides a daily physical report of how well the kids ate/slept/pottied that day as well as photos of them playing.

3. The ‚Äúextras‚Äù ‚Äî she hosts little parties for their birthdays and other occasions. She provides healthy and nutritious meals and snacks (bonus: we don‚Äôt have to prepare food for them!!). She has a huge backyard that they can get some fresh air safely in. She speaks to them in both English and Spanish, helping to develop those early neurological connections. I can go on!

Silvia is an absolute gem and any child attending Silvia‚Äôs is extremely lucky. She is nurturing, loving, and patient. Silvia and her team exceeded our expectations for what a daycare could be like and we would 100% enroll any of our future children in her care.

reviews.author: Lucia Ramos Perez
reviews.text: Our son attended Silvia's day care for almost a year. I cannot recommend it enough. They are very caring, thoughtful and trustworthy. I wish we could have stayed longer but we are moving out of the city, if we come back we would without a doubt enroll our daughter. We will miss them!

reviews.author: tacobar
reviews.text:
The best you can do for your family.
Great day care.
Both of my daughters love it
Highly recommend the professionalism of   The staff members

reviews.author: Greg Cibuzar
reviews.text: Love Sylvia and her team

reviews.author: Cassie Xie
reviews.text:
We are so immensely grateful for Dong Dong's Family Childcare and can't recommend Teacher Kelly enough! Our son started attending at three months old. As first-time parents without any local family support, we were very cautious when it came time to look into childcare options. We interviewed several daycare facilities and immediately, Teacher Kelly's prompt and detailed communication stood out to us. In particular, I was so impressed by Teacher Kelly's references. Her former supervisor was extremely effusive and full of accolades for Kelly's hard work and compassion.

In the few months since starting daycare, we've only had the best experience. We receive daily reports of our son's activities and mealtimes, as well as adorable photos of him playing both indoors and outdoors in the beautiful backyard space. Even with our changing schedules, Teacher Kelly has gone above and beyond to accommodate our needs and take the best possible care of our son. The bilingual nature of her Mandarin Chinese childcare is an amazing bonus! Overall, we truly feel like she loves our baby - what more can a parent ask for? We love and wholeheartedly recommend Dong Dong's Family Childcare.

reviews.author: Jinglin Sogbesan
reviews.text: My baby girl has been at Dong Dong‚Äôs child care since she‚Äôs three months old. Teacher Kelly is the most loving and caring care provider I have ever met. Had visited several day cares and spoke with many care providers, but none of them are good enough to earn my trust. Then I noticed this one in the bayview area and decided to go take a look. Kelly‚Äôs space is literally spotless when we visited, everything is so organized. The little backyard with a play structure is a bonus. Kelly also grows a lot of fruits in her backyard and the kiddos get to harvest them, a little gardening class there right? All of the above is what made me decide to entrust my baby with Kelly. My baby girl is almost 11 months old now and has been enjoying the time there during the day, and even makes some new friends. Kelly will send out daily activities sheet and many cute pictures of the babies every day and communicate with us if there‚Äôs anything that we need to be aware of. Really thankful that we found this day care for our baby girl.

reviews.author: Laura Wakani
reviews.text: We had a great experience with Kelly and her daycare. My son had been home with me until he was 20 months old and we were nervous about how he would adapt. Kelly was great! So attentive and flexible and kind! It was a much smoother transition than we expected. And she kept us updated on how he was doing. We highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Stephen Chow
reviews.text: This is a bilingual Mandarin and English daycare. The teachers are responsible, friendly, and take excellent care of the children. They provide meals and organize outdoor activities, such as trips to the library and playgrounds. They give your children their full attention, and the kids are always happy to go to daycare. I highly recommend this place to parents.

reviews.author: Gloria LaBerge
reviews.text:
We recently left HappyChild because our family relocated out of state and one of the saddest moments was when we had to say goodbye to Gloria and Lisa. The two of them are amazing caregivers and teachers for the little "friends" and they truly love all the children.

Gloria puts so much thought and effort into partnering with you as a parent to help your child grow. They have plenty of time to play and also learn through play. They provide healthy and delicious meals for all the children.  It is clear when I see my daughter in new situations how much she benefited from her time at HappyChild. My daughter loved her time there from when she was just 5 months old until we left a year later. We wish we could have taken them with us.

reviews.author: Ben Miller
reviews.text: This is a great group of teachers.  Kind, loving, with good attention to detail.  They keep a well cleaned home, and take the kids to the park a ton.  Very happy having our 19 month old here.

reviews.author: Valentina Castillo-Rice
reviews.text: I'm so happy I stumbled upon Pikaboo. My daughter was in Teacher Elo's care from ages 2 to 4. My husband and I were both very anxious and concerned about finding a daycare and Elo was our absolute favorite among several options. She truly is wonderful with the children. What made us feel comfortable is that Elo offered us taking our daughter a few times before her start date so she could get familiar with her and acclimate. These "transition" visits were extremely helpful. Elo is great at working on each of the kid's individual needs and developmental milestones. She also does a fantastic job at keeping you posted about your child's day by sending pictures and notifying about meals, nap time, diaper changes, etc. My daughter absolutely loves her Teacher Elo!

reviews.author: Andrea Roselman
reviews.text:
Moving to a new city and leaving our firstborn with a stranger was a truly intimidating thought, and we initially had serious reservations about choosing to send him to a daycare. We scheduled in-person meetings with several nannies and centers, but¬†Elo at Pikaboo immediately stood out. She effortlessly formed a connection with our toddler aright away and impressed us with her interactive, engaging play style.

Since then, our decision has been consistently reaffirmed. The¬†communication has been excellent, with daily picture updates and thorough end-of-day summaries. We always felt informed, even receiving proactive check-ins regarding any behavioral concerns. Most importantly, our son¬†consistently came home happy and well-cared for!

Though we've since moved to a new area, our son still lovingly refers to Elo as his "teacher" and frequently asks to go back to visit her as well as all his friends from Pikaboo all the time.

Elo truly treats every child like they are her own and it shows. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Nichlesh Patel
reviews.text:
Pikaboo Daycare has been an incredible experience for our family! The center is safe, welcoming, and filled with fun, engaging activities that help the children learn and grow every day.

We are especially grateful for Elo, who is an outstanding caregiver. Elo is kind, patient, and attentive, making every child feel loved and cared for. Our little one absolutely adores Elo and comes home each day happy, excited, and full of new things to share. It gives us such peace of mind knowing our child is in such capable and compassionate hands.

reviews.author: Joel Enquist
reviews.text: Elo, the teacher who runs the daycare, is amazing. When we couldn't get a spot for our youngest at Bright Horizons UCSF, another family, whose oldest was in the same class as our oldest, recommended that we reach out to Pikaboo, where they had their youngest. They had nothing but good things to say about Elo, so we went to meet her. From the first meeting, we felt very comfortable with her. Our youngest has been there since January, and we could not be happier.

reviews.author: Ally Huang
reviews.text: Everyone in my family loves the daycare! Staffs are very friendly and patient. My son was very introverted at the beginning. And thanks to the curriculum and Selina‚Äôs encouragement, he becomes more outgoing and always willing to share his feelings and thoughts! I love that they have a community circle every day in which they sing and talk to each other. Selina pays high attention to SEL as well, which is very beneficial to kids. I will highly recommend this place to you!

reviews.author: kristy Liu
reviews.text: I highly recommend this daycare. The teachers here are very patient and professional with the children. I trust my daughter to take care of them. Parents can communicate with teachers at any time.

reviews.author: dannis zhou
reviews.text: Selina is a wonderful caregiver!! I have two sons and they both grew up here. Selina offers a different theme each day to do a lot of activity to children. Very patient, patience to teach children. Every time there is a festival will provide different activities to take children to know different festivals. My son likes going to school very much.

reviews.author: M. Tan
reviews.text: I like smiley baby family child care. The provider offers healthy and delicious breakfast, lunch and snacks for kids. The caregivers supervise lunch, nap, and indoor & outdoor activities all the time! The kids celebrate holidays and birthdays; the provider communicates daily with parents, share important milestones of the kid. And the provider will have the parent conference with you about kid‚Äôs development in daycare! It‚Äôs a sweet daycare!

reviews.author: Lin
reviews.text: Our family really love Smiley Child Care, my daughter had learned a lot here in the past two years.  All teachers are very friendly and take good care of the children.  Strongly recommend this place  .

location.street: hidden for privacy, 821 Folsom St Unit number

reviews.author: Joseph Flannery
reviews.text: Ryan and Qing have been terrific teachers for my daughter. She is happy playing games, finger painting, and climbing at nearby playgrounds. Highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Patrick Ruiz
reviews.text:
Modern Education Family Childcare was the the second daycare provider we used. We left  our first provider because the owner was causing significant grief for our daughter. After one week with Ryan and Qing our daughter was much happier and smiled when we picked her up.

Ryan and Qing have a clean, warm, and welcoming environment for childcare. They both have a pleasant and calm demeanor that all the children in their care seemed to respond well to. I never felt worried entrusting my little one to them. My only regret is that we didn‚Äôt find them sooner!

As a bonus, we received tons of daily pictures showing us what our girl was doing that day. As the pics showed, there were plenty of activities/educational toys for the kids to be occupied with. Qing was constantly engaged with the kids in the pictures.

Thank you so much, Ryan and Qing.

reviews.author: Rachel Lim
reviews.text: Our 1 year old son went to Ryan's dayhome last year. Great experience! Clean bright space with good meals. They really take good care of your children.

reviews.author: Eran Kaufman
reviews.text: We were lucky to have Pyrena taking care of our first daughter, this daycare if full of love and caring.

reviews.author: Laura Hemphill
reviews.text:
I‚Äôm so happy to recommend Margaret, who cared for our two-and-a-half-year-old son for several months. She quickly became someone we trusted completely. She‚Äôs patient, warm, and incredibly attentive - our son absolutely adored her, and we could see how much he grew and learned during their time together.

She always kept him engaged with fun activities, both indoors and outside. She was reliable, easy to communicate with, and clearly cared about him. He became extremely attached to her, talked about her all the time, and always looked forward to seeing her. Their bond was so sweet.

We ended up moving out of the area, and honestly, we wished we could have brought her with us. She made such a positive impact on our family. I also know Margaret is very close with her own family, so it was really exciting to hear that they‚Äôre opening a daycare together. While I can only speak from our experience with her, based on that alone, I know any daycare she‚Äôs part of will be lucky to have her.

reviews.author: Sara Torlic
reviews.text: Margareth and her family have cared for my 3 children (infant/3 year old/5 year old) over the past 5 years. They're extremely trustworthy, kind, genuine and put 100% of their focus on the kids! She always has fun activities to do to entertain the kids and can often be found singing to them in Spanish. Margareth has taken our children to the city parks, taken care of them at home (during the day and overnight) and she became family to us as we did not have family nearby to help with our kids. We are so happy to see her daycare open up and thrilled to recommend her!

reviews.author: Doralba Ibarra Marulanda
reviews.text: ‚ÄúThis family daycare recently moved to a new address, but the same loving and dedicated caregivers are still there, providing warm and high-quality care. My child continues to grow, learn, and feel truly supported every day. I am so grateful for everything they do, and I truly recommend this family daycare to any parent looking for a safe and nurturing home like environment.‚Äù

reviews.author: Lizeth Romero
reviews.text: Jos√© has taken care of my son; he is a responsible and patient person, and I now recommend him for his family project with the new daycare.

reviews.author: Erika Cruz
reviews.text: A very safe place where my daughter learns and is happy. Very spacious for playing. Don't miss out on coming; it's very beautiful and your children will be very happy here.

reviews.author: teddy phuong
reviews.text:
After looking at many different daycares, we were so relieved to find Lucy. We knew within 5 minutes we‚Äôd found what we had been looking for. She brings such positive energy and has created a warm, inviting, stimulating environment for the kids. Our little guy (around 1 year old when he started) was always excited to go in the morning and happy when we picked him up. The recently renovated backyard is such a wonderful place for the kids to play, explore, and enjoy different activities.

Highly recommend Bright Star, especially if you‚Äôre looking for exposure to Chinese language.

reviews.author: Vicky Wu
reviews.text:
Our family has had the absolute pleasure to have Bright Star Family Child care for our little one since she was just a few months old, and we couldn‚Äôt be more grateful for the care, love, and attention they‚Äôve given. From the very beginning, they made us feel like family. Lucy is always patient, kind, and genuinely invested in our child‚Äôs growth and happiness.

It‚Äôs been amazing to watch our child thrive, learn, and develop such a joyful curiosity for the world under their guidance. they‚Äôve introduced her to so much Chinese through songs, stories, and daily activities ‚Äî something we deeply value. We truly feel blessed to have found such a wonderful provider, and we can‚Äôt thank them enough for the beautiful start they‚Äôve given our little one‚Äôs life. We highly recommend them to anyone who is looking for a nurturing environment for their child.

reviews.author: Yvonne Won
reviews.text: Our son had a great experience here under the care of Ms Lucy. This child care is very intimate (also Chinese immersion) and allows children to grow in their individual ways. They have a great backyard area where the kids get many outdoor activities in. I am so grateful to have came upon Bright Star and would send my kids here any day. Ms Lucy is so compassionate with the kids and cares for them like her own.

reviews.author: WITTY H (wittys_world)
reviews.text: I truly appreciate Miss Lucy and the Bright Star Family Childcare for the wonderful experience they‚Äôve provided for my daughter. The love, care, and attention from the staff are evident every single day, creating such a warm and nurturing environment. My daughter is constantly engaged, challenged, and given opportunities to learn and grow. The diverse arts, crafts, and culturally inspired curriculum enrich her experience, fostering creativity and curiosity. This daycare has been an absolute blessing to our family, and I wholeheartedly recommend it to anyone looking for a caring and enriching environment for their child.

reviews.author: Alvin Wen
reviews.text:
Bright Star Family Childcare genuinely cares!

It took us months and many on site interviews, finally we found Bright Star, it's by far the best one we had visited. I remember the first day we met Lucy, we brought our 4M son with us and he fell in sleep during the interview, Lucy noticed that and lowered her tone of voice, she's attentive and caring, also very patient.

The place is very clean and organized, Lucy speaks Cantonese and Mandarin besides English, our son surprised us with new vocabularies and new skills constantly, we ask our son everyday if he's happy in daycare of the day, at least 95% of times he said happy. Lucy constantly improve the environment of the place, creative toys and quality equipments too. Both indoor and outdoor are very neat, lots of creative activities. On special days and holidays, our son brought back thoughtful craft works for us, it's really lovely.

Bright Star Family Childcare is highly recommended, definitely 5 BIG STAR!

reviews.author: Amy Horton
reviews.text: We've had a wonderful experience with Tater Tots. Amiee and her team are caring, knowledgeable, patient, and fun. Our daughter enjoyed going every single day, and we really valued the great communication and reliability as well.

reviews.author: Brian Conlin
reviews.text: We loved our time at Tater Tots Family Daycare. We brought our daughter at 4 months old, and this crew provided the utmost care. They shared pictures and updates daily, provided meals (when she was old enough), and engaged her with books and activities. Tater Tots can't be beat.

reviews.author: Chris Moen
reviews.text:
Aimee and Jenny are the best!!

We have absolutely enjoyed their services, it's so nice to get photos of our little man throughout the day!!

We know he is in the best of hands when we drop him off at Tater Tots. Everything is top notch professional here from beginning of the experience and throughout. They make things easy for us parents and we appreciate that!!

Just dropped our son off for another day of learning, playing, and tasty foods!!

Chris

reviews.author: Sharon Kubo
reviews.text:
This was our first and only daycare. We called it 'Teacher Jen's House' :)

Our toddler went here from 17m til nearly 2yo and our family loved it! We discovered Sunny Side Tots by word of mouth, and have sent other families there too. Teacher Jen is reliable and sweet, with a great sense for what learning and energetic balance the kids need throughout the day.

This place provides a great routine, enriching activities and art projects, comfort around the clock, and plenty of age-and-stage appropriate ways for a range of little kids to each get the play and exercise that's right for them.
She keeps things very fun and super consistent for the kids - while being able to flex with each family's evolving needs. Great staffing ratio of adults to children in a clean, cozy, bright home environment. Teacher chooses toys and activities well. Good at meeting each child for who they are.

Nowadays my kid is a preschooler, but during the summer break we brought her back to Teacher Jen's for a much-needed week of bonus childcare and fun. Another former student also dropped in for that week - they had a kiddie reunion! Teacher Jen's flexibility was wonderful - we were impressed at how easy she made it to bring our child back, low fuss, with our past records at the ready.

reviews.author: Heidi Vaughan
reviews.text: Our son attended Jen's Crayon Box full time from ~18 months to 2 years old, and Jennifer is the best daycare provider we've ever worked with! Our son loved every minute! He really enjoyed the curriculum at school with lots of enriching activities and games like arts & crafts, learning songs, and counting in different languages. They also have a huge secluded outdoor play yard for the kids, and it was so nice knowing our son would be getting enough physical activity and time outside during the day. And we certainly enjoyed how Jennifer would send pictures throughout the day so we could see all the fun he was up to! Jennifer is always very communicative and reliable, and she is very caring and patient with the kids. We also really loved that they would serve 3 meals/day + snacks--it made the day so much easier to have our kid get delicious, home cooked meals at school without having to worry about packing food each day. We were very sad to have to leave Jen's Crayon Box when we moved out of state.

reviews.author: Judy Holmes
reviews.text: My son has been here since he been a year in a half and we love it Jen the teacher is amazing my son really enjoys going to daycare.

reviews.author: H Zhen
reviews.text: Nice job
