reviews.author: Thibault de Waziers
reviews.text: Our kid loves this place and I would strongly recommend it!

reviews.author: Karl Naegle
reviews.text:
Mei and Tracy took care of our son for two years, since he was 4 months old. I always felt that he was cared for well, and they were really flexible with pick up and drop off times. They were really dependable with giving breast milk throughout the day, and he was fed well, with the snack and lunch time meal included in the monthly cost. We would have had a very difficult time without Little Cookies.

Overall, I can't recommend this daycare enough.

reviews.author: K Lam
reviews.text: I was referred by my friend and teacher Tracy explained all in details. She‚Äôs patience and organized during the tour. This place is clean and safe which it‚Äôs so important. I would recommend this daycare to all families looking for trustworthy and reliable daycare for their loved ones.

reviews.author: Yael Cohen
reviews.text: My son started at Little Dinos when he was 18 months old. Nguyet made us feel very comfortable, answered all of our questions and invited us in to visit the place a couple of times. Our son had a great transition and now loves going to daycare. He talks about friends, activities, and songs. He learned so much there, like colors, how to put his socks on, songs and how to share. The place is always organized, clean and calm. Nguyet is always presenting new and creative activities to the kids in all different learning areas - mat, science, arts, language, movement. It was the perfect first school experience for him!

reviews.author: Victoria Ku
reviews.text:
Jenny‚Äôs Daycare is the best for my daughter! Jenny and her team of teachers are kind, genuine, playful, and trustworthy. They send a lot of photos throughout the day and you get to experience your little one‚Äôs day with them. My girl always comes back smiley and has learned new skills such as holding her own bottle. Most
importantly, Jenny‚Äôs scheduling hours are fair and very working woman friendly. I am absolutely able to entrust in her and the team!

reviews.author: Cindy P
reviews.text: Jenny‚Äôs place is perfect for the kids. She is very friendly and takes good care of the kids. My nephew likes her place so much. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Kyle Zhang
reviews.text: Teacher Jenny is a very patient and love person. The environment there is new and clean.

reviews.author: Emy Kelty
reviews.text:
Our baby started going to Claudette at just 4.5 months old, and I couldn‚Äôt have asked for a better experience as a new mom. From day one, Claudette made me feel completely at ease ‚Äî her warmth, attentiveness, and experience truly stood out. It was clear early on that our baby felt safe and happy in her care, and now it‚Äôs even more obvious how much our little one adores her.

Thank you, Claudette, for the amazing care and for creating such a nurturing environment. We‚Äôre so grateful to have found you!

reviews.author: Kevin C
reviews.text: This review is long overdue. Our daughter graduated from Winnie‚Äôs over a year ago and her experience there could not have been more amazing. The tears we shed when dropping off our daughter for the first time when she was six months old were only rivaled by those when it came time to move her to preschool. Over those two years Winnie and Popo became more than a daycare, they were a second family to our daughter. It was wonderful to see how they helped our baby develop into a perfect little toddler. Our daughter still asks to stop in and say hello every time we walk past and Winnie gladly obliges with open arms. We‚Äôre so thankful we found Winnie and hope this helps others find her too.

reviews.author: Angela Chen
reviews.text:
My husband and I thank our lucky stars that we found Winnie Cuties Family Daycare and their caretakers. First time parenting is tough and nothing is harder than leaving your little one in the early months of his or her life. Here‚Äôs a few highlights:

Happy Kids ‚Äì Our little guy started at four months old and is now happy 20 month old who asks to go to Winnie‚Äôs in the mornings.  During drop offs, all the kids are smiling and I always see a room full of happy babies and toddlers

Videos and Communication ‚Äì We get photos and videos so we can see what they are up to at school.  We have even created a shared album with grandparents who love watching our son dancing and singing. In the first year, we got a daily report of milk feeds, food and diaper changes.  Winnie is great at giving a quick update at pickup and will follow-up at night if needed

Engaging Caretakers ‚Äì Winnie‚Äôs mom was extremely nurturing when my son needed to be rocked to sleep and even spoon fed him when he would not take a bottle. As he grew older, he would come home learning new things at school including physical milestones and new words

Healthy Food ‚Äì I did not think to ask about food when initially touring but once our son started solids, they provide delicious and healthy food that my son loves.  Not having to food prep has made my life so much easier and a benefit of the daycare versus nanny share

Music and Field trips ‚Äì The kids go out to the playground on nice days and they will take field trips to further parks and gardens before nap time. It‚Äôs nice for our kid to have art time, excursions and outdoor time.  Winnie will celebrate holidays with the kids including Easter, Halloween and Chinese New Years which is wonderful. Lastly, while most of the songs are in english, my son is picking up some Mandarin Chinese and according to the pediatrician, exposure to multiple languages is great for brain development.

Now that my secret is out, I hope the waitlist for potential future siblings doesn‚Äôt get too long üòâ

reviews.author: Tyler Bosmeny
reviews.text:
Our son has been enrolled at Tilly's Tots for four months, and so far our experience has been spectacular.

This facility is a rare find ‚Äì a unique blend of a professional childcare center and a heartwarming home environment. Our son is especially fond of the outdoor play space.

Most importantly, Tilly and the staff's affection and dedication to the kiddos is clear. They've helped our son adjust to daycare life, make new friends, and progress through milestones. We‚Äôve noticed dizzying progress in his time at Tilly‚Äôs with walking, language, and eating solids (we only wish he ate as happily at home as he seems to at Tilly‚Äôs!). We also appreciate how so many moments are lovingly documented and shared with us throughout the day.

The thoughtfulness and effort that goes into daily activities has also impressed us. From creative crafts to park visits, every day seems like a new adventure for the kids. Our son has grown so fond of the daily circle time that he likes to recreate it at home by handing out books and telling everyone to ‚Äúsit!‚Äù just like at Tilly‚Äôs.

Choosing Tilly's Tots has been one of our best decisions, and we can't thank Tilly and her team enough for making our son‚Äôs (and our) weekdays so wonderful.

reviews.author: Amit Bedi
reviews.text:
If you are lucky enough to be selected by Tilly to have your tot be a member of Tilly's tots, you are in for an amazing childcare experience. Tilly is truly a wonderful human - she is warm, communicative, thoughtful, social and loving. Her love for the kids is palpable in every pick-up and drop-off. Our son, Oliver, started attending full-time daycare at ~4 months and attended until he was almost 14 months, and we have had an incredible experience.

The only reason we are leaving Tilly is because we are relocating back to the East Coast. There are definitely days where we think about staying, entirely due to the wonderful care at Tilly's.

Things we especially like:

(1) Tilly posts daily pictures of the kids doing all sorts of things from playing dress up to play with toys - and it is truly the best homescreen notification to get. We have an amazing catalogue of Oliver growing up living in the Brightwheel app.

(2) Tilly posts info of Oliver's meals and activities, and highlights if he seems unlike himself and maybe is coming down with something

(3) Tilly is highly, highly communicative and always there to help when you have a question about babies.

(4) Tilly has monthly social events for the babies and their parents through which we have made many friends in the neighborhood

We're first time parents and we are so thrilled that we were lucky enough to find TIlly. We are going to miss her dearly!

reviews.author: Laura Walters
reviews.text: So happy to have found Fernandes Family Daycare!! They are so kind and accommodating, and we feel very comfortable leaving our daughter in their care. She smiles every time they open up the door each morning to welcome her in. The space is safe and clean, the ratios of adult to child are fantastic, and they provide full healthy meals so I don't even have to worry about packing anything in the mornings. I also have a wonky work schedule and they are so great about coordinating timing and needs with me. So grateful to be a part of their little community!!

reviews.author: Cristina Pinotti
reviews.text:
This review is long overdue.

My son started at Fernandes Family Childcare when he was just 5 months old. I had called many daycares and visited several in person, but the moment we met Eliza and Jessica, I knew Fernandes Family Childcare was the right place for us. Both of them were incredibly warm and welcoming, and they took the time to walk us through their routine and the specific care required for infants. I immediately felt a sense of relief and peace of mind ‚Äî which, as any parent knows, is hard to come by when trusting someone else with your baby.

Leaving my 5-month-old to return to work was one of the hardest things I‚Äôve had to do, but knowing he was in such caring and capable hands made all the difference.

Fast forward to today: my son is now almost 2 years old and still attends Fernandes Child Care. He loves going every day ‚Äî playing with the other kids and spending time with Eliza, Jessica, and Emily, who now feel like family to us. I never have to worry about him because I know he is safe, happy, and well cared for.

I highly recommend this daycare to anyone looking for quality childcare. Having an in-home daycare for your child‚Äôs first experience is a huge comfort. They provide breakfast, lunch, and snacks, engage the kids in music, games, books, coloring, and even create the cutest crafts for every holiday.

We are so grateful for everything they do!

reviews.author: Julia Noack
reviews.text:
We've had our 2-year-old daughter at this amazing home daycare for a year now, and we couldn't be happier. From day one, we felt welcomed, supported, and completely confident in the care she receives.

The environment is warm, safe, and thoughtfully structured for learning and play. Our daughter has grown so much‚Äîsocially, emotionally, and developmentally‚Äîand she absolutely adores her caregivers.

Daily updates, fun activities, fresh meals and a loving, family-like atmosphere make this daycare truly exceptional. We're so grateful for the care our daughter has received and highly recommend it to any parent looking for a nurturing, home-based option.

reviews.author: Chris Lara
reviews.text:
We sent our son to Kris since he was 7 months old, from a recommendation from another friend who sent their daughter to Sunflower.  Kris and the staff at Sunflower are amazing! We know our kid is taken care of, and they truly care and show affection for the children.  They provide attention and help the kids develop.

We plan on sending our next kid to Sunflower again!

reviews.author: Sara Zhang
reviews.text: We have been sending our daughter to Sunflower since she was 11 months old and we have absolutely loved it. As first time parents we were nervous to send our daughter to daycare but when we met Kris during the tour could sense her enthusiasm and care for children. We have been so pleased with her care and she really cares for every child as her own. Our daughter loves daycare and I can tell she has so much fun and she learns so much! It is amazing to have someone like Kris to help our daughter and us through her milestones. It truly feels like she is apart of our village.

reviews.author: Wesley H
reviews.text:
As a parent who knows very little about daycares, I had to do plenty of research. When I came across The Little Dreamers daycare it caught my attention right away! Cherie was welcoming, positive, and very excited to learn more about my son. Cherie reassured me that she follows a consistent schedule that keeps students engaged and disciplined.

Quickly after enrolling my son, he interacted very well with the other children and enjoyed all the toys and books at the daycare. It was clear the children were well behaved and excited to play with their new playmate. Cherie has a weekly curriculum that includes plenty of activities, and I love that she incorporates the holiday season and birthdays into her activities.

I value that Cherie took the time to answer all my questions about my son and his participation with the other children. I‚Äôve always felt confident leaving my little one with Cherie. I give her my highest recommendation!

reviews.author: sean storms
reviews.text:
Love this daycare! Little Dreamers holds a dear place in my heart and by far the best one I‚Äôve seen. Cherie truly has a passion for what she does and you see it through her engagement with the children. The kids are safe, clean and well taken care of. The daycare is well organized and nicely decorated with age appropriate materials. There‚Äôs plenty of open space for the children to play and interact with different games/puzzles.

Cherie does an amazing job to identify what the children already know and what types of activities will help stimulate and grow their minds. Her top priority is the children!!! The students enjoy to participate in several activities planned throughout the day. I enjoy to watch the children work on art projects, playing games, singing songs and language development (Chinese/English). I highly recommend the open house on Saturday‚Äôs to explore with your child and meet Cherie (make an appt. first).

Thank you Cherie and Little Dreamers for being attentive, caring and always going out of the way for the students and families. She is by far one of the most genuine, loving and experienced Directors I have ever encountered.  I‚Äôm beyond satisfied with the care provided and highly recommend this daycare!

reviews.author: Yan Yang
reviews.text: Little Dreamers is an organized and warm place which has various toys/ materials for younger kiddos to explore. When I arrived, I was surprisingly impressive by how quiet and beautiful this neighborhood is. I saw a playground is walking distance and there is a small grassy area right in front of this daycare. Love it, love it!!! My baby boy is about 6 months old and he enjoyed playing here. The toys are appropriate for his age. Miss Cherie spent one hour playing with him for our first visit. She is very patient and friendly. Her daycare is simply neat and calm. I highly recommended!!!

reviews.author: lauren cook
reviews.text: First I want to say that I have toured and experienced many daycares in SF and it was only with my second child that I finally found Little Dreamers. Cherrie is truly the most loving and attentive teacher I have met and her care for the children shows in every way. Her classroom is sparkling clean, she has amazing toys, and she feeds them healthy food. She takes as much time as parents need to communicate special needs or updates and she takes amazing photos to share. The hours are unmatched esp for working parents, and they provide great activities and experiences for the children. We especially loved how much effort she makes to get them outside every day and they all nap so well there. And learn mandarin! It‚Äôs really the best ever. If we hadn‚Äôt left SF our daughter would have stayed as long as possible and I absolutely recommend Little Dreamers to family and friends.

reviews.author: Levin Li
reviews.text: Cherie is an experienced, knowledgeable and patient educator. She released me from concern about my baby‚Äôs developmental achievement through her observation and evaluation. Also,  this newly remodeled daycare is so cheerful for toddlers and kids to learn and play.  If you are looking for a quality daycare facility, she definitely one of the best option.

reviews.author: Laura Cunniff
reviews.text: The Vicky's Too team is so professional and grew to be like family over the two years our daughter was in their care. Elizabeth and team have such an innate ability to care for infants and toddlers alike. The loving and educational environment they provided ever single day set a high bar for our preschool search!

reviews.author: Jessie Ross
reviews.text:
They're  absolutely  a great place full of love and  compassion.
My daughter  enjoys going there and the teachers take care of  her wth lot's of  respect and care

reviews.author: Maria
reviews.text:
This was a great place for my son to go, until I no longer qualified for childcare!

My son Emmanuel has wonderful memories, and with everything we pass by on the street, he proudly declares, "This is my school." In his heart, it will always be his school!
All the teachers were incredibly kind and loving. He loves Mariela, Rosita, Rosa, Zaida, Sandra, and of course, my dear grandmother, Sandy!

The memories my son created, regardless of how long he spent there, will last a lifetime. I have no words to express my heartfelt gratitude to all of you teachers.

My son studied at this preschool for a few months. All the teachers loved him dearly and showed their devotion to the children. He misses this school a lot and has excellent memories of his teachers!

He always talks about Rosita, Mariela, Zaida, Rosa, and Sandra. But to be honest, Mariela was his favorite! He loved his grandmother, Sandy, very much too.

reviews.author: Aliz Csaki
reviews.text:
My daughter attended NVNS for two years, from the time she was 3 until she started Kindergarten, and it was such a positive experience for our whole family. She started off as a rather shy and slow to warm kid and I can truly credit the school with building her confidence and bringing her out of her shell. She developed trusting and loving relationships with a whole group of adults - from the staff teachers to the parent teachers. The incredible ratios in the classroom, where there was never a shortage of caring adults to support her, really helped in this. Seeing her get close to some of the parent teachers, who also became very close friends of mine over the years, was honestly one of the most rewarding things about being part of this community. She was born during COVID and we all felt pretty isolated, and I truly think NVNS helped turn that around for us.

Beyond this, I loved the enrichment activities the school offered. Gardening, swimming, Canyon hikes, music. I loved that free, self directed play was balanced with some fantastic organized opportunities for her to get a little taste of different hobbies and things she might like.

Being a coop is definitely a commitment but one that we were happy as a family to make and I can say, it has paid off with long term friendships for both our daughter and our family. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Ryan LeBlanc
reviews.text: Noe Valley Nursery School (NVNS) is an incredible co-op preschool at the top of Glen Canyon in Diamond Heights.  My three daughters have attended NVNS over the past 6 years, and our family has become part of the warm and welcoming NVNS community.  The school is play-based and led by our experienced and nurturing teachers.  Our school front doors open to the new Christopher Playground where our children play each morning, and Glen Canyon is a short walk away providing opportunity for nature walks and exploring.  As part of NVNS, we've had the ability to work in the classroom and watch our children grow and form friendships, and we (as the parents) have formed close friendships with other parents.  We highly recommend NVNS if you are looking for a co-op preschool for your child.

reviews.author: Jessica Doe
reviews.text: Every co-op will tell you, the community is what makes their school special. What makes NVNS stand out from others is how the whole family benefits - from siblings to grandparents. My 1 year old (future NVNSer) is growing up in the classroom, attending as a sibling on my workday, she is respected and encouraged by the older students. My 3 year old (current student) is more interested in music after watching parent-teachers perform in the classroom and at concerts on the weekend. My 5 year old (an alum!) made lasting friendships and gets to reconnect with other alums during community events and camping trips. My husband and I are continuously learning from the parents and grandparents who bring their own unique teaching style to the classroom and the playground after school. This community changes with the addition of new families, so we hope you'll join us!

reviews.author: Jessica Driscoll
reviews.text:
NVNS is a gem of a co-op preschool. My two children attended for five years combined and memories of that time are some of our most treasured as a family. The location can‚Äôt be beat, the director and teacher are experienced, wise, enthusiastic, nurturing, incredibly kind and create a magical environment for kids to learn through play. My husband and I grew as parents by observing how the teachers and parent-teachers interacted with our children and by learning how to engage with children different than our own. The community is warm and inviting and our entire family made wonderful friends there. My older child is currently in 4th grade and some of her best friends are still those she made at NVNS. My younger child qualified for TK and we opted to forgo TK and keep him at NVNS to benefit from another year of play. For those with questions about how a play-based program translates to kindergarten readiness - both my kids easily acclimated to the structure of kindergarten. Their K teacher also shared that the focus on social emotional learning in a play-based environment is essential for success in kindergarten and had a direct correlation to their ability to thrive in elementary school.

I can‚Äôt recommend this school enough!

reviews.author: jason standiford
reviews.text:
I wish I could give it 10 stars, 5 isn't enough.

The most amazing place to send your child. But I caution you, only go here if you want:  to build an amazing community with other families that will become lifelong friends, you want an entire staff who genuinely love and nurture your children to be amazing little humans, you want an environment for your child that I can only describe as magical, you want to cry at the graduation ceremony when your child finally ages out, not just because your emotional about your child growing up, but because you realize just how special of a place Peters Place actually is, and your upset at yourself for not having more kids you can send here because you aren't really to let it all go.

If those sound like things you're into, you might love Peter's place.

reviews.author: Courtney Tawadrous
reviews.text: Incredible, nurturing play-based school that just celebrated 50 years! We loved our years at Peter‚Äôs Place so very much

reviews.author: Amy Barr Mlinar
reviews.text: I‚Äôm an alum from the 80s.  What a lovely school, so many happy memories ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.author: Charles Thornton
reviews.text: Peter‚Äôs Place is the best preschool! The staff is so nice and caring and create such a great environment for the kids.

reviews.author: Kim Larson
reviews.text:
Both of my children attended Telhi Cooperative Nursery School. I couldn't have asked for a better introduction to school for them. Telhi is more than just a preschool. It is a welcoming, diverse, and deeply supportive community that nurtures not only the child but the whole family.

From the very beginning, we felt embraced by the teachers, staff, and fellow parents. The cooperative model gave us the unique opportunity to be involved in the classroom, which created lasting friendships and a strong sense of belonging. The diversity of families and backgrounds made for a rich environment where my kids felt seen, included, and valued.

Teacher Margaret and Andi at Telhi are exceptional. They truly understand early childhood development and create a space where curiosity, creativity, and empathy are encouraged every day. My children thrived under their gentle and thoughtful guidance. They built confidence, developed social skills, and discovered a love for learning that they will carry with them.

Telhi holds a very special place in our family‚Äôs story. It is a school that not only prepares children academically and socially but does so with heart, intention, and a strong sense of community. I feel so grateful to have found it for both of my kids.

reviews.author: Charlotte Rollins
reviews.text:
My 3 year old started at Tel-Hi Coop this Spring. From day one she has enjoyed every moment. This is the same kid that cried every day going to summer camp and told me the teachers were mean there. She has never complained about an adult at Tel-Hi. Any issues with other kids have been worked out with love and respect for both students.

As a parent raising black children in this city, diversity is very important to me. At Tel-Hi, my daughter is surrounded by children of different backgrounds, from different countries. She is learning from adults that all look differently and are of different genders. I love how many father's (my daughter's included) are the working parent at the school. There is definitely a lack of male teachers in the 0-5 age range. There are also grandparents.

It is a lot of work and a lot of time on our end, but it is worth it for my daughter to be in an environment that she feels comfortable enough to be herself and learn so much.

Thank you Tel-Hi for being a part of her life during this developmentally crucial time in her life.

reviews.author: Jordan Brantley
reviews.text:
We love TelHi!!
Our oldest attended preschool at TelHi a few years ago and we were so excited to come back this year with our younger kiddo. It is so great to know that when they are at school they are safe, loved and learning.
As a co-op, parents help in the classroom one day each week which allows us to get to know everyone well and see what our kid's days are like at school. One of the things I appreciate most has been learning from our awesome teachers and other parents as we all help our young kids navigate their big feelings and teach them how to express them safely - in a loving and non-shaming way.
We're so grateful to be part of the TelHi community and can't wait to be back next year!

reviews.author: erin lampe
reviews.text:
My son graduated last year from Telhi Coop (not to be confused with Telhi Community Center which is also a great place.) It was a wonderful first school experience for him as well as us parents. The time he spend there helped prepare him for Elementary school as well as allow him to be just a kid.

The Telhi Coop community felt like you were on a cul-de-sac not urban SF, allowing for life long friends and a village of other families to help support you and your little ones. My daughter just started there in February. And we‚Äôre happy to be back daily at the school. In just last few months, she‚Äôs learned tons more words,  lots of songs, and she‚Äôs become a crazy gymnast, and just loves her friends and teachers at Telhi. I would highly recommend this preschool, even though it‚Äôs half day, it‚Äôs the perfect place for our family. Our daughter is  thriving there, just like our son did. Happy 70th anniversary Telhi.

reviews.author: Kirsty McKay
reviews.text:
We have just completed our first year with Telhi for our 2 year old, and I just love the community we have built up. As the parents participate in the classroom we really get to know the kids. I looked around at our end of year party yesterday and saw parents engaging with different children in a way that you see at family functions: one dad was showing a group how to do handstands, someone was pushing a gang on the tyre swing, someone was helping a child search for a hair clip and another making up a plate of food for a pupil.

The teachers both bring enthusiasm and creativity to the classroom and my daughter could not love them more. For a long time she would not stop telling her grandparents about ‚ÄúTeacher Andi‚Äù every time they phoned. The play-based model means there is plenty of time for open play but also the kids have music time, story time, art, yoga classes, introductions to other languages (if there‚Äôs anything cuter than a two year old singing twinkle twinkle in Japanese, I haven‚Äôt seen it yet), age appropriate science experiments and fine motor development activities. The gross motor activity area is a favourite with all the kids and they can really get their wiggles out there.

Personally I have also made great friends with my fellow work day parent, and it‚Äôs so nice to now have a group of moms in the neighbourhood that I can happily socialise with at the playground or without our kids in our downtime.

reviews.author: Ana Harris-Padley
reviews.text: Highly recommend. Our daughter has attended for two years (ages 2.5 to 4.5). Fabulous staff from teachers to those that run the school. Great student/teacher ratio, attentive and caring, and good mix of social and educational learning. They use Brightwheel for communication and photos which is great to get updates on your little one(s). We'll be sad to leave the school as our daughter heads to public school/TK but PE has definitely prepared her well!

reviews.author: Lisa Mendelman
reviews.text: Echoing everyone's rave reviews! I have had two children at PE Nopa over the past two years -- my son started in the Petite Room at age 2.5 last August and is now in the Discover Room at age 4.5, my daughter started in the Petite Room at age 2 this August. We have been thrilled with everything about the school. The teachers are phenomenal--nurturing, engaged, and well-educated. The husband and wife owners/admins Vickie and Andy equally thoughtful, experienced, and caring (they are very involved and often sub in when teachers are out, so they really know my kids, which I love). Communication is seamless. The site is also great--up to date facilities, indoor-outdoor space, and (most important to my children) endless activities. The project-based learning is perfect: my kids have learned so much about bees (my son) and airplanes (my daughter). I really can't say enough good things about our experience and recommend it without reservation.

reviews.author: Amanda Webb
reviews.text: My son is nearing the end of his second year at Petite Explorer NOPA. He started at just over two years old and only spoke a handful of words at that time. He has blossomed in so many areas thanks to the staff and friends at Petite Explorer. Love the classroom, outdoor space, variety of activities and seeing his interests grow! Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Julia Tanase
reviews.text: Our son Wesley has been going to Petite Explorers for a year and he absolutely adores it.  The teachers are wonderful and the program director Vicky is very organized, responsive and attentive.  It‚Äôs a wonderful preschool that we highly recommend.

reviews.author: Shelley Estelle
reviews.text: Glenridge Cooperative Nursery School is a very special place for young children to attend preschool.  Tucked into Glen Canyon, the act of hiking to school brings wonder and joy to kids and their families.  My son and daughter have both had fun attending this school, and I have learned so much as a parent working in the classroom and at the parent education meetings.  We have made a wonderful network of friends and people we can rely on!

reviews.author: Andrew Casteel
reviews.text:
Not only does Glenridge have the most amazing setting of any school in San Francisco, nestled in the middle of Glen canyon park along side a creek surrounded by so many trees you forget you're in the city, but¬†Glenridge is so much more than a school, more than community.¬† It's family.

I knew I wanted a co-op preschool so that I could share these magical years with my son while he still wants to play with me.¬† I didn't know how much meeting all these families would change our lives as parents.¬† We've made so many new friends and gone on so many adventures together outside of school with other parents.¬† For the first time in my life as a new parent, I have a peer group that shares all the same struggles and joys.

If all that wasn't enough, our administrator and head teacher, Mame, is incredible.¬† I taught highschool for 6 years, so I was very critical of the administrators I met as I toured preschools for my son.¬† Mame impressed me from the start and continues to impress me with her approach to early childhood development.¬† She's not only a great teacher, but makes great teachers out of all the parents in the classroom.¬† I'm a better parent because of Mame and Francis is blooming under her care.

I've met former Glenridge parents whose children are now in college who still remember their time there.¬† Now I know why it left such a lasting impression.¬† There's no place like it.

reviews.author: Nikki Virgo
reviews.text:
It is truly beautiful here. It is a tranquil place where you can easily enjoy the different plants, flowers, and foliage. It is a good place to take pics if you like photography and a good place to enjoy a nice walk and you can easily recover and gain a peace of mind. I love to meditate in the quiet no to busy environment and you should visit ots a site to see!

reviews.author: yangjz00 YANG
reviews.text:
Silver Tree Summer Camp.
Great!

reviews.author: Maureen Lindmeier
reviews.text: We have a been a part of the Miraloma Community for over two years and both of my children attend preschool there. Not only is a warm, nurturing environment for the kids, but it's also a supportive community for the parents. The school embodies its mission fully (which is so powerful for the kids to witness!) and you can feel the sense of cooperation when you walk through the door. We got lucky in finding this place when looking at preschools because it's really shaped our lives in the best way possible!

reviews.author: Alex Teng
reviews.text: Have absolutely loved our family's time at Miraloma! Couldn't ask for a better preschool experience!!!

reviews.author: Cassie Yip
reviews.text: A wonderful community with lovely families and teachers that help my child to thrive!

reviews.author: Megan Gulbahce
reviews.text: Wonderful little school- great teachers, caring and involved community.

reviews.author: Paul Jasper
reviews.text: Great community!

reviews.author: Xing Ye
reviews.text: Our experience at PHMS has been wonderful. The impact on our son has been profound; he has developed both academically and socially, showing remarkable growth in his confidence and enthusiasm for learning. All of the teachers and staff are exceptional‚Äîpassionate, dedicated, and always approachable. Their genuine care for the children is evident in everything they do. We can‚Äôt thank PHMS enough for all that they have done for our family- and would recommend to anyone looking for a safe and nurturing community for their little one.

reviews.author: Jessie
reviews.text: As a working parent, I value academics & communications and PHMS delivers both. The academics are great, your child will learn read, write and do math. Our daughter is developing confidence, independence & a love for learning. She made some good friends and also enjoys the enrichment classes including music, art, soccer etc. the school offered. The daily updates and parent communication is a huge plus for us while we are both working parents.

reviews.author: Alice B√©rard
reviews.text:
Our 2 year-old son has been going to this school since he was 5 months old and he absolutely loves going there every morning. He‚Äôs very attached to each of his teachers, who have been able to create a strong bond with him.

In the infants classroom, he had dedicated support and teachers were very respectful of his routine and skills, always supporting and encouraging him for the next milestone.

In the toddlers classroom, he‚Äôs learning everyday with different Montessori material, going to the playground every morning, taking soccer and music classes each week.

We‚Äôre very grateful for this school and deeply appreciate every teacher who made this a great experience for our son!

reviews.author: Kailey
reviews.text:
An exceptional experience for my kid!
We couldn‚Äôt be happier with our experience at this wonderful school. From day one, it has been a nurturing, joyful, and inspiring place for my kid to learn and grow. The teachers are some of the most dedicated and caring to kid‚Äôs development.

The beautifully curated classrooms create an engaging and stimulating environment, fostering both creativity and learning. The school‚Äôs location is also fantastic‚Äîsituated next to Jackson Park and near the police station, it offers both convenience and a sense of security.

Beyond the academics, the school truly fosters a strong sense of community among parents, making it a welcoming and supportive place for families. The enrichment activities, including music, art, and soccer, add an extra layer of excitement and fun to the curriculum.

We are incredibly grateful for this school and highly recommend it to any family looking for a warm, enriching, and inspiring early education experience!

reviews.author: Erin Coull
reviews.text:
PHMS was our son's first home away from home. From day one he was welcomed with warm and caring arms from teachers devoted to learning each child's unique needs and personality while exuding fun, love and patience.

The well appointed Montessori classroom was peaceful while open to inspiration.  As a busy toddler with lots of developmental changes seemingly happening weekly (!) we loved how engaged he was in his daily adventures with friends, the love he had for his teachers and the pride about new skills learned (squeezing oranges, slicing cucumbers and helping in the kitchen were favorites!).

The ease with which we potty-trained we completely credit to PHMS and their approach to independence for the kids, along with the additional enrichment activities (soccer, kinetics, live music, art, foreign languages) were added bonuses where we felt like we hit the jackpot.

Our family is extremely grateful for PHMS and the sweet community of kiddos, teachers and parents who make it so special.

reviews.author: Sacha Proano
reviews.text: Our son has thrived under the care of David at Little Earthlings. As parents sending our first child to their first group care setting, we craved an environment that would allow our son to develop in his own time with little interference. What we found at Little Earthlings was exactly that - and much more. From the wonderful and compassionate teachers to the community of parents to the early childhood development guidance from David, we could not be happier with our experience at Little Earthlings! Our son has learned valuable lessons & skills in a nurturing outdoor environment that will last a lifetime.

reviews.author: Natalie Gantz
reviews.text: Little Earthlings is AMAZING! David and the other instructors create such a loving, safe, and magical world for kids. Our two kids both went to Little Earthlings and have such a connection to nature and the outdoors, but also self-confidence and social skills, too. David is a true master of early childhood development, and gives kids the room to grow and explore their own abilities without having to be on an adult's agenda. Not only does he guide and inspire our kids, but makes us better parents, too. Highly recommend üëç

reviews.author: KATIE KIM
reviews.text:
Little Earthlings Forest School has been a truly special experience for our son. David and Beeta create a safe, warm, supportive, and nurturing environment in the forest, and it‚Äôs clear how much they care about the children‚Äôs development and fostering strong connections. I love that my son spends so much time outdoors, learning from nature, and discovering more about himself and his friends. He‚Äôs grown more confident in tackling new challenges and has developed into a stronger and happier child. His independent play has flourished, thanks to the freedom and space he gets to explore in nature.

Thanks to David, who always offers thoughtful solutions and answers for handling different parenting situations. His guidance has been so helpful, and we really appreciate how he navigates challenges with such care and expertise. It honestly feels like we‚Äôve been on a meaningful journey together.

reviews.author: Catharine Burhenne
reviews.text: We‚Äôve had both our children attend Little Earthlings, and Teacher David's impact has been incredible. Both our children thrived in this environment which focuses on emotional awareness, confidence, and resilience‚Äîall while learning through nature and play. We see the benefits of this approach even now as our eldest excels in elementary school. If you value gentle/respectful parenting, this is the place to be. As my husband and I look back on our parenthood journey, Teacher David Calabrese stands out as one of our top 3 influences, and we are forever grateful for him and the Little Earthlings program.

reviews.author: David Sanderson
reviews.text: We‚Äôve sent both of our kids to Little Earthlings, and it‚Äôs been an incredibly formative experience for them. The name of the school perfectly captures David‚Äôs magical approach‚Äîhe understands that kids are new creatures on this earth, trying to figure things out, and he gives them the space and support to do so in a unique and special way. The open and safe environment creates a magical space where kids are able to build confidence, develop essential skills, and let their minds flourish. Even though our kids have grown out of the program, we still send them back every summer, and our eldest is excited about becoming a junior counselor.

reviews.author: Emily Williams
reviews.text:
We absolutely love Acorn! Tarusha and Maria are truly wonderful. Every day, they guide the children through open play, songs, stories, or art projects with gentle, positive care.

Here‚Äôs part of what makes Acorn so special:

Thoughtful toys: Only wooden and cloth‚Äîno plastic or battery-operated toys. Everything encourages creativity, skill-building, and big imaginations. This was a big one for us!

Organic vegetarian meals: Delicious, adventurous dishes lovingly prepared every day. Our toddler‚Äôs palate has grown thanks to their thoughtful choices (and we‚Äôve even learned new recipes from them!).

Magical outdoor space: The children spend most of their days outside in the beautiful backyard, digging in sand, exploring nature, and playing freely, yet somehow always come home clean!

Gentle conflict resolution: We‚Äôve watched them guide children through social challenges calmly and respectfully, which has helped us approach similar moments at home with more patience.

Supportive potty training: They followed our preferred approach, and our toddler caught on quickly thanks to their guidance.

Natural remedies: For minor scrapes or sniffles, Tarusha draws on her deep knowledge of herbal care, always starting with gentle, natural solutions.

We were VERY picky about where to send our toddler for her first school experience, and Acorn has exceeded every hope we had. We‚Äôre endlessly grateful for the love, care, and wisdom they pour into each day.

reviews.author: Jillian Monaghan
reviews.text:
Acorn Nursery is a very special place. Both my children attended from 2 until they entered TK/K, and loved it. Tarusha and Maria are such a loving, calm and patient teachers. My favorite things as a parent:

1. The kids spend a ton of time outside in all weather except heavy rain. They learn about plants, grow food and spend hours in the large, beautiful sand box in the backyard.

2. The food. They eat all organic, really healthy meals. Tarusha gets my kids to eat much more interesting foods at school than I was originally able to get them to try at home. The kids are able to help with the cooking some days. Also there is no stress on me to pack snacks or lunch.

3. Multi-age group. Both of my children have really benefited from the having a broader age range. They had kids to look up to when they were the youngest and have grown into the role of helper and "big kid" as the oldest.

We love Acorn and would highly recommend it.

reviews.author: Marie Chaufour
reviews.text: Our daughter is currently attending Treehouse Preschool, and we absolutely love it. We have 2 older kids, so we have experience with other care and school structures around the city, and Treehouse is one of the best places we have seen. The care team is so nice and welcoming and the educational program is well structured. Kids learn a lot while being in a nurturing and loving environment. I can't recommend this place enough!

reviews.author: Mancasola Cheryl & Allen
reviews.text: What a delightful school.  I have worked with special education kids for 30 years and every time I visit treehouse pre-K I am so impressed with the child focused learning that takes place at Treehouse. What a wonderful foundation for these lucky kiddos

name: L‚ÄôAcademy Language Immersion Preschool and Infant Daycare Center

reviews.author: Arnaud D.
reviews.text: Our little one loves it here. We feel lucky to have found a spot at this daycare!

name: Spire School by Parks Plus Creation

reviews.author: Daniel Robinson
reviews.text: An amazing school with in an amazing setting run by gifted and dedicated teachers. I‚Äôve had my 5 year old in their programs since she was 2, and she is happy, curious and resilient thanks to Parks Plus Creations

reviews.author: Max Elman
reviews.text: We love Spire! So happy we found this forest school.

reviews.author: LITTLE SUNSHINE (MOURINHO)
reviews.text: Nice place

reviews.author: Lehua Sparrow
reviews.text: I have become a better parent, better partner, and better community member because our family joined the Coop. We've made life long connections with the teachers and the families from Sunset Coop. It truly is one of the gems in the Outer Sunset and I can't recommend this place enough.

reviews.author: Helena Madsox
reviews.text: This is a wonderful place for a child to learn about the world. I loved this school.

reviews.author: Lina Garcia
reviews.text: Our son loves going to daycare at Baby Prodigy. The staff is very sweet and friendly. They have great communication with parents, keeping you updated on your child every day. Highly recommend it.

reviews.author: Jennifer Kwan
reviews.text: Amazing daycare with the best teachers! My daughter loves going everyday and has learned so much!

reviews.author: Mandukhai Enkhbat
reviews.text:
My son has been attending Alphabet Kids for the past year, and we couldn't be more thrilled with our experience. Buya, the owner, is a truly exceptional educator with a natural talent for connecting with children. Her warmth, patience, and enthusiasm create a nurturing and inviting atmosphere in her home.

Not only is Buya a skilled caregiver, but she also prioritizes safety and structure. Alphabet Kids adheres to all safety regulations, ensuring a secure environment for the children. The daily routine is well-planned, providing a sense of stability and consistency while allowing for creative exploration.

The variety of age-appropriate activities offered at Alphabet Kids stimulates children's minds and fosters a love of learning. From engaging storytelling sessions to hands-on art projects, there's always something new and exciting for the kids to discover.

One of the highlights of our experience has been watching my son's growth and development at Alphabet Kids. He has made significant strides in his language skills, problem-solving abilities, and social interactions. His artistic creations are always a testament to the creative and imaginative environment Buya has cultivated.

We particularly appreciate the weekly yoga sessions at Alphabet Kids. These sessions not only promote physical fitness but also teach children valuable skills like mindfulness and relaxation. It's heartwarming to see my son come home, eager to share the yoga poses he's learned.

If you're seeking a home-based daycare that offers a safe, nurturing, and educational environment, we wholeheartedly recommend Alphabet Kids. Buya and her team have exceeded our expectations and have become an integral part of our family.

reviews.author: Crystal Zhou
reviews.text: I was really hesitant to send my son to daycare but given our childcare circumstances, we had to. When I toured Alphabet Kids, I noticed it was extremely clean and there were toys and play areas appropriate for kids of all ages. My son was 12 months when he started and has been going here for a month now and I was originally really worried about how he would lose weight and not eat, but they feed him almost every two hours and I know he is eating because he has a lot of dirty diapers the next day! Buya, the program director, is very good at arts and crafts and my little guy frequently brings us home something he made at daycare. I also really appreciate that they play with something different all the time and send daily pictures. Buya is also masked and they keep things very clean. I looked at over 10 daycare places and this one was the most flexible in terms of hours (7-5:30 pm) and days, so if you are looking for full time or part time, Alphabet Kids is ready to make it work! I am very happy with the care that my son has received so far!

reviews.author: Molly Phillips
reviews.text: We feel so blessed to have found such a wonderful daycare for our daughter, Avi. Our daughter has been going to Alphabet Kids 5 days a week since she was 5 months old and it truly feels like our second home for her. Buya and her daughter welcome Avi each morning with lovingly open arms. They are so creative with planning a variety of activities each week, that are both age appropriate and engaging. Buya and her daughter have created such a special place and I would recommend them to anyone looking for a daycare.

reviews.author: Ketti Wilkes
reviews.text:
My son has been attending Alphabet Kids Daycare full-time for a month now (he is currently 23 months old). My husband and I toured several different daycares in Sunset and Richmond Districts. We decided to enroll our son here because Buya, the Program Director, was so attentive and quick to respond to our son's behavior during our first meeting! It usually takes some time for this toddler to warm up to unfamiliar faces and environments, and he is constantly distracted. Within minutes of our tour, Buya was able to get him to sit down calmly on a kid-sized chair and play with a toy. She was even able to get him to pick up and bring back the toy, too! At that moment, we knew that our son was getting good vibes here.

We also adored the set up of this daycare because they have a really cute outdoor area that's not directly under the sun. The ground is padded with artificial grass, and there's a slide, toddler vehicles, and seating area outside too. The area inside is also carpeted and padded. It is very clean and tidy even in the middle of the day, it looks like the photos she posted (I have personally been inside in the afternoon). We could also see that every little area was so well thought out to keep kids safe.

We are also amazed by Buya's creativity and love for arts & crafts. They always have fun new activities like finger painting, sensory play with seashells and water and much more. In the past month, I've kept all of the artwork that we were able to take home. We received pictures of our son's activities everyday and a "report card" that details everything from when his diaper was changed to what he ate and how long he slept. We are happy to find a daycare that gives us a peace of mind knowing that our son is being cared for by someone as kind as Buya and her sweet daughters.

reviews.author: Chelsea Rosenbloom
reviews.text: This daycare is pure magic! Buyan and her daughter are so gentle and kind. My son Gabriel loves them both (and they love him) and he loves going to daycare here every day! They celebrate the small things in life and make each day bright and fun. They send home crafts and little bundles based on holidays and themed events throughout the year. This is a small family daycare, with a quiet napping room, a big bright play room and a really nice outside space for all of the kids to play together. Definitely don't hesitate to check Alphabet Kids out, I wish we could stay with them forever!

reviews.author: Margarita Aulet-Leon
reviews.text: My husband and I were both in medical residency when we sent our son to Little Ducklings starting at age 4 months, until he was a year and a half old when we moved away. I trusted the care he received there wholeheartedly. Zagdsodnom showed our son so much love and care, and he truly loved her! The best feeling a parent could have is to see their kid be totally happy and comfortable in their daycare. We also witnessed him thrive in his development- Zag made a dedicated effort to keep the kids cognitively stimulated throughout the day according to their appropriate needs. I saw evidence of this when my son ran into one of the other kids at the playground after daycare. They were playing a game they had learned together at Little Ducklings (yelling ‚Äúup and down‚Äù while jumping and giggling). She also was incredibly patient and adaptive to each child‚Äôs unique needs, and spent time chatting with each of the parents nearly daily to ensure all caretakers were on the same page. Lastly, she was very accommodating when my husband and I had more demands on our work schedule. We were so sad to leave! I recommend little ducklings very highly!

reviews.author: Nick Kings
reviews.text: Sodoo is amazing, our daughter feels so safe and happy at Little Ducklings and is always excited to see her friends.

reviews.author: Bre Lawrence
reviews.text:
We had the most wonderful experience with Sodoo and her teachers at Little Duckling. Our daughter, Juliana, started daycare at 8 months and we were nervous about the transition. We could not have asked for a better, more loving environment for Juliana. They were attentive to her needs, flexible with her schedule as she adjusted and grew, and very communicative with us. They made celebrations special and fun for the kids and provided many enrichment opportunities - arts and crafts, imaginative play, and a great backyard play space.

Juliana was so excited and happy to see Sodoo every morning at drop off.

I highly recommend Little Ducklings to any families looking for childcare along with peace of mind!

reviews.author: Kira G
reviews.text:
We had the absolute best experience at Little Ducklins. Our daughter was six months old when we first brought her, and I was so nervous and stressed over leaving her for the first time. But Sodoo was obviously incredibly experienced and immediately made me feel at ease. When I would bring my daughter to daycare in the morning, her face would light up when she‚Äôd see Sodoo which was such a great sign. Sodoo has the calmest maternal feeling about her, and I think the kids really respond to it. My daughter obviously really loved Sodoo, and that made me feel so much better and more relaxed about leaving her during the day.

We unfortunately had a few medical emergencies at daycare when our daughter suddenly spiked a fever, and I was extremely impressed at how Sodoo handled scary situations: she was calm and in control and contacted us in real time so we could be there as soon as possible. Our daughter‚Äôs health scares were alarming but I‚Äôm really glad Sodoo was there when they happened and that she handled the way she did. Our doctors even praised our daycare and were really impressed at the way Sodoo handled the events.

Net: I can‚Äôt recommend Sodoo and Little Duckling Daycare enough. The kids are happy, Sodoo is fabulous, and I felt safe and comfortable leaving my baby there while I worked. We would bring all our future kiddos here if we could.

reviews.author: Laura Maxwell
reviews.text:
Our daughter spent two years at Sodoo‚Äôs and we couldn‚Äôt have asked for a more warm, loving, nurturing environment for her. Sodoo truly cares for the children in her care, and our daughter grew to love her so much. She would even ask to go to daycare on the weekends. For our daughter‚Äôs first birthday, we were so surprised by a sweet present for her and pictures of a birthday celebration they had with the kids! Birthday and holiday gifts given to the children are such a sweet and personal touch. Sodoo makes warm meals for the children each day and our daughter learned to be a great, independent eater.

It was such a blessing to be able to drop our daughter off each day at a place where we knew she was loved and cared for. We cried on our last day - Thank you to Sodoo and her team for making our daughter‚Äôs first daycare experience such a great one.

reviews.author: J L
reviews.text: Little Dolphin has been great for our baby. They are very thoughtful and caring, and I love that my daughter will be exposed to Mandarin instead of English because she'll pick up English easily once she goes to primary school. Our daughter has learned a lot while there, especially in how to play with other children and is always happy. They will also take the kids to the local playground, and you can tell they love it! Each day, they send pictures and videos of your child so you can see them in action. Very happy with Little Dolphin.

reviews.author: Touma Kunjo
reviews.text: I highly recommend Little Dolphin Daycare for your family. We enrolled our son  at the age of 1 and Xiao and Jason and the teachers are incredible and amazing!! They truly care for this kids, pamper them with holiday parties and nice toys and frequent playground trips. My son is a happy kid and loves all of buddies from Little Dolphin as well as all the staff and teachers. I cannot thank Xiao and Jason enough for the love and care they shower unto these kids,

reviews.author: M Y
reviews.text: My child has been attending Little Dolphin since December and I've got nothing but praise for them. They are very accommodating with any special requests the child needs. Jiao is extremely thoughtful and genuinely cares about her kids. My child looks forward to school every morning, which is more than I can ask for. I'd highly recommend touring the facility and talking to past and current parents about their experiences. There's no doubt we made the right decision in choosing Jiao and Jason to care for our baby.

reviews.author: Sara Sagui Henson
reviews.text: We enrolled our daughter at Little Sun daycare from 6 months to 2 years old. We loved Marine and her intimate daycare! There were 3 other kids under 2 so our daughter got a lot of attention and love and she made a best friend. Marine was like another grandmother and treated our daughter so well. She provides healthy breakfast, lunch, and snacks each day. She has the cutest little parties for the kids on holidays and birthdays. Marine is kind, responsible, and caring. We will miss her!

reviews.author: Ashley Ferris
reviews.text: My daughter has been at Little Sun since summer 2017 when she was about 13 months old. We have been so happy with Victoria at Little Sun. She provides a loving, safe, nurturing environment. We love the small size (5-6 kids) and that she provides healthy breakfast, lunch and snacks. We just could not be happier with the level of care our daughter is getting at Little Sun.

reviews.author: Elisabet Perez Bautista
reviews.text: We could not be happier with St Nicholas care takers. They are really attentive, caring, methodical, and responsible. Especially Gabrielle, she is exceptional and super really detailed oriented. I know my daughter is in the best hands

reviews.author: A FAMILY of TWIN sisters In USA

name: Mi Cunita de Noe Valley Nursery

reviews.author: Sarah Mahmoud-Bseiso
reviews.text:
Genesis and Eric are truly the absolute best! We were blessed to spend 4 years straight at Little Banana's as our daughters were two years apart. Moving on to preschool was bitter sweet moment for our family.

One of our favorite things was the sense of community they fostered amongst the families. Even in a small environment it's easy for people to drop off and pickup without really knowing each other, but Genesis and Eric insure that's not the case and I am forever grateful for that.

You will get everything you could hope for and more by sending your little hear: love, development, community and just a fun place to be daily. You'll also get daily updates and photos of your little which is so helpful.

We hope to always stay in touch with this dynamic duo as our girls love them and still ask about them often.

reviews.author: Jon & Larissa
reviews.text:
There are so many daycares in San Francisco, but my wife and I knew right away when we toured Little Bananas that this was where we wanted to send our daughter.  Genesis, Eric, and Gel are fantastic!  They kept us at ease (especially since this was our daughter's first time being away from us) with regular updates and pictures through the Brightwheel app.  They also kept our daughter engaged with various activities, crafts, field trips (e.g., the beach, the zoo), and music lessons.  They also arranged for several events so all the parents could get to know each other.

Additionally, my wife and I appreciated how they were willing to help with what we were trying to teach our daughter at home.  They helped her as she was potty training and also while she was having a hard time with napping.  Furthermore, they met with us several times a year to review our daughter's developmental progress.

Genesis and Eric went above and beyond during the first few weeks of the coronavirus pandemic.  While they were not required to close, they closed the daycare for a few days in order to make sure it was thoroughly cleaned.  They also made sure parents and kids washed their hands prior to drop off and pick up.  In the meantime, they arranged for circle time for the kids via Zoom and even dropped off projects for our daughter to complete when she was not at daycare.

We are so sad that our daughter is leaving Little Bananas--time goes by so fast, and she's now starting preschool!  We knew she was so well prepared, though, because of her time at Little Bananas.  We can't thank Genesis, Eric, and Gel enough for their love, care, time, energy, enthusiasm, and patience with our daughter.  We HIGHLY recommend Little Bananas Daycare; your child will be in good hands!

reviews.author: Elsa Chan
reviews.text:
We are forever grateful to have found this rare gem of a daycare/preschool. We were very particular about choosing a daycare for our youngest son due to developmental delays, and sending him to a large daycare where he would be easily lost in the crowd was not an option. We toured SO MANY daycares and Little Bananas definitely stood out from the rest. The moment we stepped into Little Bananas, they genuinely wanted to get to know my son and welcomed him with open arms. My husband and I immediately agreed that this was the best place by far. Little did we know that they would go on to go above and beyond to exceed our expectations! My little one was a little over a year old when he started there, and he is now 6 years old! So many milestones were achieved as a direct result of the quality care they provided to help him thrive and reach his full potential. They are still the only people outside our family we trust to care for our son.

Genesis and her husband are amazing caregivers and teachers! They do circle time in English and Spanish, teach not only the basics - but also social and emotional learning, diversity & inclusion, and have special music teachers come in for live music. They have taken the kids on fun field trips to the zoo, the Bay Area Discovery Museum, and quality indoor play places like PlayHaven. They also use a secure app only parents have access to, letting us know what fun and educational activities the kids partake in every day, record diaper changes, what they eat for breakfast, lunch, and snacks, not to mention they take awesome pictures of the kids enjoying their day!

Little Bananas not only provides exceptional care but also strives to build a community among families. They host potlucks and fun seasonal parties for families to get to know each other. Because we have stayed with them for such a long time, we have seen many happy children graduate and are well-prepared for the next phase of their education. Every family we have met in our close-knit community feels the same way as us - that we all lucked out in finding them! They were a lifesaver during the pandemic. They stayed open to ensure children of frontline workers could continue to work, ensuring that they deep-cleaned even more than usual, and followed guidelines to provide a safe environment for the kiddos when many other places were shut down. They even hosted virtual Zoom classes and created activity kits for the children whose families chose to stay at home so that they would continue to have access to educational activities even if they were not on site. That just shows how much they care about the well-being of all their students.

There are no words that I could write to truly express how much we love Little Bananas and how appreciative we are for the personalized and extraordinary care they have provided to us. We could not have asked for anything better. We highly recommend Little Bananas if you are lucky enough to get an open spot here!

reviews.author: Lorelle Strange
reviews.text: We love Little Bananas and cannot sing their praises enough!  It is a very loving environment and great attention is paid to each child.  They are nurtured and taught at their level and each child thrives.  We miss our Bananas family and would suggest them to anyone looking for a place where their child will be accepted with open arms, open play, circle time, wonderful art projects, and delicious/nutritious food.

reviews.author: Moira Marr
reviews.text:
Genesis, Eric, and Gelica are a dream team! We have been with them for almost a year and they have become like family to us. Their deep love for the children shows in everything they do, from the circle-time adventures, to the home-cooked meals and snacks. I had a bad experience at a previous day care so was very anxious when we came to Little Bananas. They understood our fears and made sure we were 100% comfortable, answering all our questions. They are all highly certified with many years experience working with children and babies.
The children all love them and you can see by their smiles and laughs that they feel safe and happy there. We are constantly updated on their daily activities through an app and get near-daily pictures and videos of the kids enjoying their day. Field trips to the zoo and nearby playground happen every week and the kids get plenty of outside time in the backyard.
I highly recommend Little Bananas to anyone looking for care for their babies or toddlers!

reviews.author: Rory Davis
reviews.text: Our son has been at Little Universe for the last 9 months and has loved it since day one. Melanie's home daycare is warm, comforting, clean, and a perfect place for our two-year-old to grow and develop. Melanie takes great pride in her work, is a fantastic communicator, and we are so lucky to have her support. Every day we pick up our son he has a smile on his face and it's clear that he has been well cared for. He's developed friendships with other kids and we really appreciate the close knit feel and convenience of Little Universe. I would highly recommend this daycare to anyone considering it. Thank you Melanie!

reviews.author: Dan Asadorian
reviews.text:
Little Universe Daycare is a shining example of what an in-home daycare center can be. Melanie has a passion for early childhood development and is absolutely wonderful with young children.

Our daughter was the first child admitted to her program and it was evident from the interview and onboarding process that this was not like the other day cares we were considering. Melanie takes great care to understand your child‚Äôs current development and will come up with a plan on how best to integrate them into her program.

Melanie has cuddled our daughter to sleep when she‚Äôs had a difficult day and is having trouble settling in for her nap. She is attentive to the many complex transitions children make during their infant and toddler phases and will guide them with poise and compassion.

Throughout all of this, Melanie is steady in instilling a sense of routine and order, which the children seem to gain confidence from and thrive in. She will work with parents to form a developmental plan and then follow up with regular thorough assessments showing a clear understanding and commitment to each child‚Äôs growth.

I have seen tremendous progress from each child admitted to her program and look forward to seeing them grow.

reviews.author: Shannon East
reviews.text:
This is a long overdue review for City Kids and the director, Lisa.

Our son attended City Kids from age 2 until 4 1/2 (when we moved out of state) and we couldn't be happier with the care he was given. Lisa and the teachers are absolutely amazing and nurturing. They all worked with him and were extremely hands-on with any issues or concerns that we had about his learning and development. At 2 we were nervous about how our son's energy level would translate in a learning environment but Lisa and Astrid worked with him to help him adapt. They were very reassuring of his progress.

We are now enrolling him in a new pre-K program where I've noticed that he is easily at or above the curriculum level that is planned for the upcoming school year. I believe that his time at City Kids has well prepared him for this transition.

I highly recommend City Kids. We were treated like family and we always trusted that our son was in great care. Our son tells us everyday how much he misses his City Kids friends and Mrs. Lisa.

reviews.author: Itai Zukerman
reviews.text: My 3.5yo son attends City Kids 3 days a week.  He's not always thrilled about going there in the morning, but once he's there he immediately jumps into whatever activity is his current favorite.  Teacher Lisa does a great job of keeping the kids focused and teaching them new skills, and she's given us some good advice on how to fix behavior problems and nudge along the potty training.  There are only 3 or 4 other kids there, so I know my son is getting individual attention.

reviews.author: Cristian Grajales
reviews.text: Best daycare ever with me Lisa being a rockstar I wish I could‚Äôve ended on a better experience but really was special

reviews.author: Leonard Jung
reviews.text:
We were so lucky to have had Christie as our nanny for our daughter. She took care of her as if she were her own‚Äîpatient, loving, and endlessly attentive. Christie worked for our family for 2.5 years and never once came late. Her reliability, along with her warmth and care, gave us complete peace of mind.

Christie didn‚Äôt just ‚Äúwatch‚Äù our daughter; she truly engaged her‚Äîreading, playing, singing, and encouraging her to explore the world. She had a beautiful balance of kindness and structure, and we always felt completely at ease leaving our daughter in her care.

Now that Christie is a caregiver at Rainbow Kidz Daycare, we feel extra confident about the wonderful care children receive there. The whole team is dedicated, and knowing that Christie is part of it makes us especially happy. Any child who gets to spend time with her is in wonderful hands.

If you‚Äôre looking for a place where your child will be cared for with genuine love and professionalism, Rainbow Kidz is a place you can trust.

reviews.author: Anne Elise Fortes da Silva
reviews.text: The teachers are warm, attentive, and clearly passionate about working with children. They create a nurturing environment where each child feels safe and supported. The daycare follows a well-structured daily routine that includes a thoughtful balance of playtime, educational activities, and quiet time. Rainbow Kidz is the best place for children develop socially, emotionally, and intellectually.

reviews.author: Meredith Downing
reviews.text:
We enrolled our daughter at Rainbow Kidz when she was 6 months old and are incredibly grateful to May and her team for the care they provide each and every day. My daughter is now 18 months old and thriving. She loves her days spent with May and team.

Finding childcare is such a personal decision. Some of our priorities included: daily outdoor time, loving and responsive teachers, use of an app or other digital communication tool, convenient drop off/pick up protocol, a bright/light-filled classroom space, a small class size, and a commitment to play-based learning. Rainbow Kidz provides all of these things and so much more.

May has been a true partner to our family through the various big developmental changes this year (starting solids, sleep training, nap transitions, teething, etc.). It has all gone so much smoother as a result of May‚Äôs support and collaboration.

Highly recommend taking a look at Rainbow Kidz if you are searching for childcare!

reviews.author: Aaron Franklin
reviews.text: We love having May and her team care for our little one.  They are truly part of our village now because they have a genuine love for our son and take an active and interested role in his upbringing.  We adore Rainbow Kidz and can‚Äôt imagine being without them!

reviews.author: Christie Aur√©lio
reviews.text: The best teacher ever!! Get ready to have your child talking about teacher May all the time and sharing with you all the cool and fun time they had together

reviews.text:

It is daunting for parents to figure out what‚Äôs best for kids especially in a city like SF - public vs private, nanny vs daycare, immersion vs focus on English‚Ä¶we have looked into all. After all the research and discoveries, one thing told us LT is the best for our kid and family is that our son comes back home every day, happy!

Happy as in singing new songs, learning new words, making new friends and telling us all about his time at school.

Love the entire staff team, and adore every teacher our son has had from infant room to toddler room. They are truly with you through the journey and have your back.

Even though her time there was short-term, you made her feel like a true part of the Little Trailblazers community. She came home every day with stories, smiles, and a sense of belonging that made all the difference. Your attention to detail, patience, and the genuine care you show for each child is something truly special.

reviews.text: We love the school and the parent community. Our daughter has really thrived in here 1+ yrs here. The school does a great job teaching topics like art and math and small life skills too. The hours are also great and provide more coverage than most preschool options (8-6pm).

reviews.text: My daughter goes here and it has been amazing.  The curriculum and most importantly the teachers are world class.  We were in a Montessori prior and I can say this one is a step above - math, language, culture, botany, you name it.  Could not recommend more!

reviews.text: Our daughter joined BCMS just before she turned three and will be continuing on. The teachers and staff are truly exceptional. She loves the school, her teachers, and her friends.
