reviews.author: Justin Martin
reviews.text: We have been extremely happy with the quality of care and education that we‚Äôve gotten at Big City. We particularly love the mixed age classes and the wonderful teachers and special programs (Spanish, music, yoga). The family community has been wonderful and our child has thrived here and is well prepared heading into Kindergarten this year. We‚Äôre looking forward to sending our second child here this fall.

reviews.author: Angela Chang
reviews.text: We loved our 2 years at Big City when our daughter was 3-5 years old. Wonderful teachers, great enrichment classes (yoga, music, and art every week) with outside teachers, on site field trips--what a dream! School is supportive and the other families are great as well. Highly recommend.

reviews.author: gilbert cabral
reviews.text: Best and safest place to have your children in.  3 of my kids attended Big City. One in the late 90‚Äôs, early 2000‚Äôs and late 2000‚Äôs.  Rest assure your kids will be well cared for and educated appropriately individually.  Ms Amanda and staff are wonderful.  The building is kept up very well.

reviews.author: Sohum Misra
reviews.text:
Our daughter is about to complete her second year at BCMS and we plan to send her there for another year before enrolling her in a K program. We have enjoyed our experience at BCMS so much that we are going to be sending our son there next year as well.

Both our kids are/will be in Miss Amanda's class and we have nothing but positive things to say about my daughter's experience so far. We have seen her grow and learn and develop a real curiosity and interest in learning more. She truly enjoys going there every day, sometimes even wanting to go on weekends. She doesn't like leaving early in the day either.

Some things we love:
1. Communication: We get a constant stream of updates every day of the activities the kids have been up to through Brightwheel. This is amazing as we can follow along with what they are learning and talk about it with her after school. We can also message the staff on the app and get responses usually within minutes.
2. Variety of activities: The Montessori method likes the children to be at the forefront of what they want to learn. Instead of having a rigid schedule or just play time, there is a combination of structured learning and then unstructured learning where kids can choose to do a lesson or work on a particular type of activity they find interesting.
3. Support for parents: Miss Amanda is happy to set up time to talk with any struggles we have when parenting our kids, especially at home, and is an excellent partner in making sure our kids learn how to make the right decisions by themselves.
4. Availability: There are no long school closure periods. The largest closures are 2 weeks in the winter and 1 week in the summer. Additionally the school operates from 8am-5:30pm offering great flexibility to working parents and no need to think about significantly long camps during vacations.
5. Parent community: There are so many great parents and the school makes a real effort to keep parents committed. There is no pressure for parents to fundraise and many/most parents come mainly for the social opportunity.

Really the biggest measure of how happy we are is how happy the kids are. My daughter comes back every day with a smile on her face and she is never unhappy to be dropped off (after a few days of adjusting up front, of course). She adores her teachers and her friends.

Also, reading some of the negative reviews, I do have to set the record straight with respect to the allegations of "borderline racism", which in my opinion are objectively false. In our daughter's class there is a broad mix of ethnicities and we (as an Asian family) have not faced any racism whatsoever. And the argument that "Hispanic staff members... are relegated to roles such as doormen and kitchen staff" is just... blatantly incorrect. All the teachers in Miss Amanda's class are of Hispanic descent and the school's co-director and Spanish teacher (Miss Hilma) is of Hispanic descent. Besides that, all staff are treated with the utmost respect (that they deserve) and it is demeaning to define their roles as "relegations" as if they are not critical to the functioning of the school.

reviews.text:

Our daughter is doing early reading, math, and science activities daily. We get photo updates on the school‚Äôs app so we can actually see what she‚Äôs learning. And the best part is you can message the teachers on the school‚Äôs app, and the teachers respond quickly. They‚Äôre always available, kind, and truly invested in the kids. We felt immediate peace of mind dropping her off, and that‚Äôs priceless. She‚Äôs gaining real skills, confidence, and independence, and we know she‚Äôll be far ahead by the time she enters kindergarten. The Montessori approach makes it purposeful and child-centered. It‚Äôs not just childcare. It‚Äôs worth every penny. Oh, and they also have enrichment programs. When you go there, they will show you. My daughter loves it, and this makes me happy and definitely gives me peace of mind.

The teachers don‚Äôt just care, they work hard to make sure your child is academically way ahead by kindergarten. If you want results and a place where your child is truly seen, this is it. They also offer free Spanish or Mandarin immersion, you choose what‚Äôs best for your child. We picked Spanish, and now our child speaks and understands so much. Amazingly, it‚Äôs included.

reviews.text: Every day I see a happy group of children running down the street leaving this Montessori school (( I‚Äôve not been inside and I do not know the facts of the situation, )) but I do know the girl has a very very sweet, large, very soft loving golden retriever , which apparently really adds to the good vibes! reviews.author: Angelica Garibay
reviews.text:
Growing Minds Montessori

We are so happy with our choice of Growing Minds Montessori. As this was out first child, coupled with the pandemic (born in Feb 2020) we were headed in to this process pretty much blind. After the intro tour, we almost immediately knee this would be the perfect fit. Our daughter was transitioning from a daycare where she was the oldest by a year, and understandably was a tad but behind socially. Donna‚Äôs set up, coupled with the Montesorri ideology provided us with comfort, and an almost immediate/noticeable improvement in her energy, spirit, and curiosity. The Brightwheel app that Donna/Montessori uses has us in awe of how much they find to do in the house, backyard, and the local neighborhood. An added bonus has been the relationships our daughter, as well as the parents have made thru the school. Parent zen achieved!

reviews.author: Rose Seng
reviews.text: Our daughter just started at GMMP and I have to say, we are already blown away. The space and environment is unlike any other daycare/preschool we've been to or toured. It's peaceful, clean (surprising for a school), calming, and the yard is great! Ms Donna is very kind, warm, sweet, understanding, and wonderful to work with.  Our daughter was going through a potty regression due to a new sibling, and Ms Donna worked so patiently and positively with her. The adventures to the library, parks, and neighborhood walks are great additions to the daily outdoor time our daughter already gets. The art projects and curriculum she's learning in just the few short weeks far surpasses what she was creating and learning at her previous school for the last year!! Oh and not to mention, the level of communication and daily updates we've received is unparalleled! Our daughter is a very strong willed and spirited child, so I was very anxious about her transition and just a new school in general, but I am beyond relieved and grateful she is now at GMMP. We can see the positive difference in her energy and mood already!! I only wish we had found Ms Donna and GMMP sooner!!

reviews.author: Sara Sivesson
reviews.text: Montessori Story is amazing. My kid has so much fun during her days there. She comes home happy and calm. The food provided is excellent, and Elmira makes sure every kid get attention and love.

reviews.author: Dave Kim
reviews.text: My son has been attending for a few weeks now and he is loving it! He is a learning a ton, getting tons of sun, and now wants to spend more time outdoors even outside of school. He also loves teacher Laura, Alex and Frank!

reviews.author: Valerie Navarro
reviews.text: Little Robles is a special place. My son attended this school for almost a year (until we moved out of the city) and we couldn‚Äôt recommend it more! The teachers and administrators are so warm and welcoming and the space is beautiful! We loved that our kiddo was able to explore Golden Gate Park daily under supervised care. My son learned to express his emotions, speak some Spanish, and socialize with kids his age. While we moved out of the city, my son still talks about all of his friends and teachers often. They really made an impact on him and he misses it so much! Thank you Kristina and staff for creating such a wonderful space for all kids to thrive and grow.

reviews.author: Lien Nguyen
reviews.text:
Our daughter started attending Little Robles in the Sunset full-time when she was 2.5 years old at the beginning of 2024 and we stayed with them until we recently moved away. We were very sad to leave the school because of how much they supported her and our family.

They helped us with her transition to starting school (which took 3 weeks for there to finally be no tears) and supported us with different challenges that are typical for 2-3 years (big emotions, meal time battles, hitting/biting, nap issues, toileting).

I loved that their space is bright, open, and contemporary. They are a short walk to GGP. My daughter thrived within this school program and under their care. I loved that they incorporated a lot of outdoor play and neighborhood adventures. I noticed her behavior and mood was so much better because of it.  She LOVED her teachers and school friends. The classroom size was small enough that she created really meaningful and genuine bonds with several of her classmates and teachers. We have since been away from the school for 3 months and she still talks about her former teachers how much she misses them.

My daughter really enjoyed the daily activities. Their curriculum and activities were very engaging for her.  She did a lot of hands-on  learning about science, art, reading, counting, food, as well as doing things within the neighborhood and community (like going to post office, visiting library, walking by the produce/fish market, taking the train to a new park, etc). I really liked that they exposed the kids to their community.

If we hadn't moved, we would definitely still be at this school until Kinder.

reviews.author: Andrea Bramchtein
reviews.text: My daughter has attended Little Robles since she was 1.5 years old and has had the best experience. The teachers are so loving, you know they‚Äôre in the best care. They take them to Golden Gate Park everyday which is such a bonus! I would highly recommend anyone looking for a Spanish bilingual free play day care.

reviews.author: Abe Dieckman
reviews.text:
Little Robles is great. They have taken care of my insanely energy-prone son for about 2.5 years now, and I've been grateful and happy  with his care throughout this time.

Kristina, who runs Little Robles, has always been warm and friendly and kind... and most importantly, communicative. She allows us to bother her with more texts than are reasonable and has never turned us away when we wanted to chat about something on our minds. Moreover, her staff has always been friendly and loving and my son is fond of all his teachers.

Their sunset location is brand new, and I'm really happy to see how bright and airy and spacious it is. They also take the kids to the very nearby park often, including Mother's Meadow playground.

Hard to go wrong.

reviews.text:

We will miss CMS but plan on sending our younger child there when it‚Äôs time.

reviews.text:
My daughter has attended CMS for the last two years and I couldn't be happier with her time there. The teachers at CMS are all so caring, attentive and kind. My daughter felt safe and heard there, which is a huge testament to amazing teachers at this school. They are great at communication, sharing updates, and customizing to the needs of the children. They are level-headed and reasonable with requests, engage parents and help children where they are needed. Also, it's great they heat up the kids lunch so they can have yummy food! They bring in enriching activities that make the kids day (animals, visits from fire fighters, magicians).

My daughter grew up in so many ways at CMS, beyond academically they fostered her self confidences and self-worth. She left CMS to go to Kindergarten, prepared both academically and emotionally. To prepare your kid to be ready for Kinder is no small feat, and I'm so happy we chose CMS. I would highly recommend it to anyone.

reviews.author: A.K. Kapoor
reviews.text: Our son attends CMS since he was 2.5 and loves to go to school each day. The teachers are attentive, caring, and compassionate with all the children. There's a learning theme each week, plenty of outdoor activities, and a concerted effort to learn through play which was very important for us. We'll be sad to leave once he goes to TK but good thing his sister will go in a year-ish.

reviews.author: Nosheen Mirza
reviews.text:
I have never written any reviews but this place deserves one! So when I got the job I was worried for my youngest son, 4 year old, as to which preschool he should attend. I searched a few preschools online and came across with CMS. I instantly knew this was the place for him. I went to see the director, she showed me around and I really liked the place, their set up and how they were dealing with the kids.
My son went to CMS for one year and that one year has left me and my family some wonderful memories that I will always cherish!
Harjit, the director is very experienced with the kids and has been running this place successfully for more than 40 years! She is super good with the kids but when the need comes to be firm she is firm! And thats what I wanted for my son. Friendly environment but also he should learn to respect everyone.
Reenu who is taking over the school now is super friendly with kids, she cares for them and genuinely likes children. As a mother it was important to me that the place my son goes to has a friendly environment and that the staff deals with my son as one of their own. Thankfully the staff was always upto my expectations!
My son didn't know any of his alphabets and numbers, within a month of attending CMS he knew all his alphabets and numbers. I was so impressed by the progress he made. He instantly liked every single thing about the school and really never complained about anything. I still remember the first day when I was leaving him the director hugged me and told me not to cry :D and that he's in safe hands. He indeed was! My son liked going to CMS so much that he even asked me to take him to school on weekends :)
My son always talked about teacher Harjit, teacher Reenu, teacher Linda. They really put a  lot of effort in their work, all of them! They are also adding a lot of value in the children's life. The children do a lot of fun stuff and you will love to see what children are doing in school actually because every child takes his all day work back to home with him when the school is over. So parents know exactly what the child has been doing during his day.
They have a really nice routine for the kids, their study time, snack time, lunch time, nap time, play time is all very well organized. They staff gives 2 snacks everyday and I must say that everyday the snack is different and something that the kids really enjoy. They also celebrate the children's birthday and its a lot of fun! Every child in treated as an individual and the staff works with the child's pace. They do not rush in things.
As a parent if you want your kids to thrive and learn and play as a team this is the place for you and your child! you will have a peace of mind and you won't be worrying about the well being of your children. I would HIGHLY recommend this place!
CMS me and my son miss you a lot! :(

reviews.author: YiMu Li
reviews.text:
It was an amazing positive experience for my two kids at California Montessori School. Teachers are thoughtful, attentive and caring. Kids are really learning and growing. I still remember the first day my boy joined CMS, he knew no single english words at all. But not for long, my boy spoke english like a native and made friends at school thanks to the help of all the teachers, espeically teacher Reenu. She built the curriculum that sets kids up for success as they enter into Kindergarten and beyond. I also trust CMS to maintain a safe, clean environment that teaches kids self-responsibility. Therefore, when my younger girl turned three, i didnot hesitate a single minute to send her to California Montessori School.
For those who are looking for a preschool, I cannot recommend this one enough -- thank you CMS for everything you did to care for our two kids and set them up for success!

I know that my review might sound ‚Äútoo good to be true‚Äù but it is true, and was very good for us!

reviews.author: Bryce Word
reviews.text: Our son attended Holistic Seedlings Wonderschool before, during, and after-COVID. We were so lucky to have found Massiva. She takes great care of the children giving them a variety of activities to help them develop and socialize. The food she prepares is amazing and healthy too!

reviews.author: Laura Ayala
reviews.text:
Massiva, Younes and their family are such warm and supportive caregivers and I am so grateful that they founded Holistic Seedlings and I feel so blessed that we were fortunate enough to find them online and for our son Camden to be accepted into their program.

What Massiva offers at Holistic Seedlings is truly unique. It is clear that running her daycare, in the way in which she does, is both her passion and purpose in life. She an exceptional cook and with her holistic nutrition knowledge she makes the most delicious and nourishing food from scratch for all the children every day. (Breakfast, lunch and snacks). She often shares homemade snacks, dates or freshly baked sourdough loaves with the parents as well! She takes the children to their community garden every week to teach them about where their food comes from, how to tend to the plants and how to harvest and enjoy whatever is in season.

Her eldest sons host and teach soccer every Friday afternoon. Their support and influence has had a remarkable impact on my son, who loves soccer and basketball and clearly looks up to the older boys and enjoys playing with them. It warms my heart to see Camden so well taken care of.

Massiva and her husband Younes, provide such a warm and loving environment at their home. I trust them wholeheartedly and I honestly could not imagine what I would do without their holistic support. My husband and I felt instantly at ease with them, in contrast to other daycares we visited that just cannot compare.

An added bonus is that Massiva an excellent and creative photographer! The regular photos she sends parents through the daycare app are an absolute gift and treasure for us to have. We can see all the wonderful activities she has created for the children and get to witness all of the joy that radiates from their smiling and excited faces. I also keep each of these high quality photos as a document of my son's growth and development.

I also so appreciate the bi-monthly mother meetings that Massiva hosts to bring the mums together over a delicious homemade meal to discuss important topics related to our children and how best we can support them and align in our approach.

Most importantly it's been an incredible blessing to find someone like Massiva that shares so many of my own concerns and values regarding nutrition and a blend of both traditional and modern, holistic approach to childcare. Her care is not only consistent with our approach at home but supports, amplifies and exceeds any expectations we could have for Camden's health, happiness and wellbeing.

reviews.author: Joyce Zhang
reviews.text:
We chose Auntie Siu's Modern Family Education in Mission Bay because of amazing reviews from friends, and she exceeded our already high expectations. We started sending my son to Auntie Siu's when he was around 8 months old and his younger sister at around the same age. Whenever I drop my kids off, they run excitedly inside and I know they are being loved and cared for as if they were at home. It makes me happy to see all their milestones and developments and how safe and secure they feel with Auntie Siu, who is now like family to us.

The daycare is in a safe and convenient location in Mission Bay, on the 2nd floor inside a doorman guarded building. There is a spacious outdoor turf area and a private outdoor patio connected to it. The inside is large and spacious, with everything childproof and many different toys, puzzles, books, and arts and crafts for the children.

My kids love spending time there, and receive so much love and care from all three of the adult caretakers. I get daily text messages with pictures and updates, which is a good way for me to practice my Chinese as well.

The daycare prepares healthy, home-cooked Chinese food without salt or sugars and makes sure the children have an assortment of different activities and games, from art and drawing, to daily song and dance. I really appreciate the Chinese immersion (Auntie Siu speaks both Cantonese and Mandarin) and especially the true love and care that she and all the other caretakers exhibit. She knows each child for his or her individual personality and attributes, and gives good parenting and healthcare advice given her decades of experience.

Modern Education Family Childcare truly goes above and beyond. Auntie Siu throws birthday parties for each child on his/her birthday and other themed parties for various holidays, always managing to cook a delicious Chinese feast. She dresses them up for Chinese New Year and has parents bring Halloween costumes so the children can dress up for Halloween and other holidays as well.

Even now that my son is in preschool and has graduated, he always looks forward to returning during school holidays. We are still friends with many of the families whose kids attended daycare at the same time.  Auntie Siu is like family, and we are very grateful to her.

reviews.author: Bianca Chen Hsiao
reviews.text: My daughter has been with Auntie Siu for the past year, starting from 6 months of age. It has been a truly amazing experience. She makes daycare feel like family. So many home-cooked treats, joyful birthday and holiday celebrations, but most importantly, she provides a loving and gentle environment for all of the kids. She speaks Chinese (Cantonese) to the children (an immersive experience that we value highly), and communicates regularly via text message with pictures from the day. I honestly would want to have another baby so Auntie Siu could look after them, and I cannot recommend her enough!

reviews.author: Veronica Antonova
reviews.text: Siu is a caring provider who feels more like a family member. She‚Äôs warm and instantly connects with little ones. Home cooked meals, outdoor time throughout the day, family festival celebrations, lots of play and reading, and learning Chinese. Love Siu and her family. Our kid still asks for her by name 2 years after we stopped daycare, now that she‚Äôs school age, and refuses to let anyone else watch her if we need to leave her for a few hours in care at odd hours. Siu is our go to for childcare!

reviews.author: James Harvey
reviews.text:
After two kids and five years, this past Friday was our last day at Modern Education Family Childcare, as our younger child is moving on to preschool. Auntie Siu has become a beloved part of our family, and we'll miss her dearly. She's gone above and beyond anything I've ever heard of at any other childcare, and her love for her kids is obvious. From working with us to manage our son's allergies to thoughtfully sending home-cooked food home to my wife when she was pregnant, she's been a gift to our family.

In the covid-era reopening, they've been particularly careful, and it's clear that they're following all precautions, from consistent mask use and disinfecting hands and surfaces to avoiding social contact outside of childcare hours. If you're lucky enough to join MEFC, I can't recommend them highly enough.

reviews.author: David Angel
reviews.text: Both my daughters went to pre-school here.  Amazing, gentle, play based, family run daycare!

reviews.author: Sakinah Williams
reviews.text:
First Choice Licensed Daycare is truly the best!
Ms. Katrina provides individualized care for each child, creating a warm, safe, and nurturing environment. She helped my son learn his numbers and letters‚Äîhe‚Äôs now super advanced, and I credit it all to Ms. Katrina‚Äôs dedication. This daycare has such a homey, intimate feel, which made the transition so much easier for both me and my child. The quality of care here is exceptional and offers incredible value. As a first-time mom who struggled with anxiety about sending my child to daycare, I can confidently say this has been the best decision we‚Äôve made. Highly recommend!

reviews.author: Jessie Kaur
reviews.text: Wonder Years is a brand new, fully renovated beautiful school. It is clean and in good shape, much different than most schools in San Francisco that are old and falling apart. The director, Parneet deeply cares for each child and the teachers also seem to enjoy their roles. The school is quite new but the community they're building is wonderful. I'm so thankful they have infant-toddler care, since its so difficult to find in the city. I highly recommend it if you're looking for quality care and wonderful staff.

reviews.author: Elissa Flandro
reviews.text: We feel so fortunate to have found The Wonder Years school and recently joined the community. The newly renovated building feels very safe, clean and a nurturing environment for kids. There's a great outdoor space for the kids to use. The caregivers are exceptionally attentive and nurturing, giving us complete confidence that our son is in wonderful hands. The school director is very professional and organized. We're very happy to  be part of the school!

reviews.author: Thao Le
reviews.text: We feel so lucky that Wonder Years opened right when we were starting to look for daycare for our 8 month old. It was nerve-wracking starting daycare as a first time parent, let alone at a brand new facility, but the director and the wonderful teachers at this school have made it a wonderful experience for our family. The primary caregiving model ensures that even in a daycare center, my baby is getting 1:1 attention and is familiar with the people caring for her. Her teacher knows her quirks and has helped her to learn new skills in the short time that she's been there. They helped us make the transition to daycare during peak separation anxiety and made sure that the entire process was gentle and focused on the well-being of the child. We love it here and have already recommended this school to other parents!

reviews.author: Nina C
reviews.text: As a first-time parent, finding the right daycare was really important, and I feel so lucky to have found Wonder Years right as they opened. The space is immaculate, bright, and thoughtfully designed, with a massive outdoor playground in the backyard. The Director is incredible‚Äîso organized, caring, and truly invested in every child‚Äôs well-being. The teachers are just as wonderful, and my son has completely taken to his teacher, which has made the transition so easy. One of the things I love most is how many pictures and updates they send throughout the day; it makes me feel like I‚Äôm right there with him, experiencing all the little moments I would otherwise miss. I couldn‚Äôt be happier with our experience at Wonder Years‚Äîit‚Äôs everything I hoped for and more!
